title: strawberry sweetheart salad
directions: Stir cream cheese and mayonnaise until well blended.
Add marshmallows, strawberries, pecans, pineapple and food coloring; blend well.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into 1 quart mold until firm.
Unmold on bed of lettuce and garnish with whole strawberries.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into the unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake for approximately 40 minutes.

title: orange sauce
directions: Mix together the cornstarch, sugar and salt in saucepan.
Add orange rind.
Gradually blend in orange juice.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cook until mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Add orange sections; heat.
Yields 12 cake servings.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Cream cheese with mixer until smooth.
Add pineapple and mix. Add both puddings and mix on low.
Put in prebaked pie shell and refrigerate.

title: apple slaw
directions: In large bowl, whisk together cider, sour cream, vinegar, caraway seed, salt and mustard.
Add cabbage, apple and onion. Toss, cover and chill 1 hour.
Toss before serving.

title: crawfish stew
directions: In an iron pot, heat fat or shortening until melted.
Add onion, green pepper, celery and garlic; saute until clear.
Add flour, stirring well to blend.
Gradually add tomato sauce, seasonings, water and crawfish tails; simmer on low heat for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Serves 8.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Add all ingredients together except biscuits.
Bring to a boil.
Pour in 2-quart baking dish.
Top with biscuits.
Bake at 400° until biscuits brown.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Mix pineapple preserves, apple jelly, dry mustard and horseradish. Blend well. Chill overnight to meld flavors.

title: ground beef and corn casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion together.
Cook noodles until tender. Mix all ingredients, except bread and butter, and pour in baking dish.
Crumble bread on top.
Pour melted butter on top.
Brown in oven at 350° and serve.

title: gelatin dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water; add 7-Up and marshmallows.
Cool; add fruit and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cheesecake pie
directions: In mixer bowl, beat together cream cheese, the sugar and almond extract until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each at low speed just until blended.
Pour into an ungreased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes or until set and knife inserted just off center comes out clean.
Stir together sour cream, 3 tablespoons of sugar and the vanilla.
Carefully spread on top of hot "pie".
Cool.
Sprinkle almonds on top.
Cover and chill until serving time.
Makes 6 servings.

title: turkey fruit cup
directions: Scoop out center of orange half (it helps to first cut along inside of rind).
Dice orange center and place it in small bowl. Dice and combine with other fruits.
Add chopped nuts, if desired. Fill orange cup with diced fruit.
Add toothpick for a neck, a carrot round for head and half a toothpick for a beak.
Stick celery leaves in back for feathers.
Set on lettuce leaf on plate.

title: quick peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter or margarine, then add remaining ingredients of heat until creamy.
Place in an 11 x 7 pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Any pan of this approximate size will work.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil 2 cups of sugar and 1 cup of Carnation milk to soft ball stage.
Add jar of Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter.
Stir well.
Pour into buttered dish.

title: coffee punch
directions: Scald milk; add coffee, sugar and spices.
Chill thoroughly. Put ice cream in a punch bowl.
Break up into small pieces.
Add coffee, milk mixture and almond extract; stir.

title: cheesies
directions: Mix margarine and flour to cornmeal consistency.
Add salt, cayenne pepper and Rice Krispies.
Mix well.
Add grated cheese. Mix thoroughly.
Form mixture into small balls; mash down with fork.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: microwave brownies
directions: Place margarine and cocoa in a 8 inch square microwavable baking dish.
Microwave for 1 minute, add sugar; mix until smooth. Add egg, milk, vanilla, flour, baking powder, salt and nuts. Place a small glass, bottom side down, in the center of dish to prevent soggy center.
Microwave 5 1/2 to 6 minutes.
Rotate dish 1/4 turn ever 1 1/2 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Let cream cheese and margarine soften at room temperature. Add sugar and teaspoon of vanilla.
Mix well.
Frost cake while hot.

title: tossed taco salad
directions: Simmer the first 7 ingredients for 15 minutes. Chop and mix the tomatoes, lettuce, onion and cheese.
Slightly crush the Fritos.
Add salad mixture to meat and toss.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Combine butter, sugar and vanilla in mixing bowl; beat well. Add eggs; beat well.
Stir in flour.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown sausage.
Add vegetables and water.
Cook until vegetables are done and season to taste.

title: almond bark bars
directions: Melt bark in double boiler; stir in peanut butter, then all remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoon on wax paper placed on cookie sheet.
Chill.

title: hawaiian spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions on package; drain after cooked.
Fry hamburg and onion in skillet; drain fat.
Combine mushrooms, soy sauce, salt and pepper to hamburg mixture; add to spaghetti.
Cook gravy according to package instructions; add to spaghetti mixture.
Mix well.

title: apple or crab apple butter
directions: Measure fruit pulp and sugar into a large saucepan.
Add spices.
Place over high heat and bring to a full rolling boil. Boil hard for 1 minute.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat and at once, stir in Certo.
Skim off foam with metal spoon.
Stir and skim for 5 minutes.
Ladle into glasses.
Cover at once 1/8-inch hot paraffin.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: In a pot, cover cabbage with water and cook 20 minutes; drain. Saute onions in butter. Mix ingredients together, except cornbread dressing. Pour into a baking dish. Put 1/2 bag dressing mix on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet corn cakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a bowl.
Mix the egg, corn and oil in another bowl. Combine the two mixtures and add enough milk to make a thin batter. Heat a griddle.
Grease and ladle about 1/4 cup batter for each cake.
Cook until the bubbles on top burst. Turn when golden brown on bottom.

title: date nut balls
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, dates, beaten egg and Karo syrup. Cook 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Don't boil; let simmer 10 minutes.
Add Rice Krispies, flavorings and nuts.
Cool and roll out on wax paper.
Let cool well, then coat with powdered sugar from a paper bag.

title: christmas thumbprint cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg yolk.
Add vanilla.
Combine flour with salt, then add to sugar mixture.
Roll in 1 to 1 1/2-inch balls and dip in egg whites.
Roll in chopped walnuts or coconut. Bake 5 minutes at 375°.
Then press thumb in center.
Bake an additional 5 to 8 minutes.
Cool and fill centers with red and green jelly.

title: amanda's egg sandwich
directions: In a mixing bowl, slightly beat egg, then fry in greased pan until done.
Place cheese on top of egg to melt.
Place bacon on top of cheese and put on toasted bread.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions and let cool. With fork punch holes in cake. Mix Cream of Coconut and condensed milk together. Pour this mixture over cake and refrigerate overnight. Mix cream cheese, cool whip, and powdered sugar. Beat this and spread on top of cake. Sprinkle coconut and pecans over top of cake.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together all above ingredients, except the chicken.
In a casserole, put 2/3 of the rice mixture, then lay the raw chicken breasts on top.
Cover with the remaining rice mixture.

title: brownie mounds
directions: Mix margarine and sugar until smooth.
Add syrup and eggs. Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: apple brownies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add egg, apples and nuts.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Mix together.
Spread into 10 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Doubles well in 9 x 13-inch pan too.
Freezes well also.

title: potato squares
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan. Stir in cheese.
Heat until cheese melts. Combine with potatoes in bowl. Add sour cream, onion and seasonings.
Mix well. Spoon into
greased shallow 3-quart baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Garnish with paprika, if desired.
Cut into squares to serve.
Yields 12 servings.

title: mid-summer pasta
directions: Let marinate at room temperature for at least 2 hours the olive oil, garlic, fresh basil, dried tomatoes, fresh tomatoes and fresh ground pepper to taste.
Cook pasta al dente (do not overcook). Drain and add immediately to oil marinade.
Toss well and serve. Quick, easy and delicious!

title: calico salad
directions: Mix all the vegetables together.

title: white chocolate surprise
directions: Melt chocolate over double boiler. Add peanut butter.
Add all ingredients.
Mix and drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Cool or chill in refrigerator.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Boil beef until tender.
Cool and shred.
Cook sauce 10 minutes, then add meat.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheese spinach squares
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs, milk, butter, cheese and onion. Drain and add spinach.
(Thaw and press between paper towels until moisture is gone.)
Grease a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 50 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: blender fruit smoothie
directions: Place everything in blender and blend until smooth.
Serve in tall chilled glasses. Garnish with an orange slice on the side of the glass.
Serves 8.

title: roy's mother's eggless cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well; bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° until done.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Mix all except vegetables together.
Cook vegetables until tender.
Pour mix over vegetables.
Let stand for 24 hours before eating.
Serve cold.

title: chicken paprikosh
directions: Mix salt, paprika and flour together and dust chicken lightly, then saute the pieces in bacon drippings to a golden brown.
Place the chicken in a casserole.
Cover with Paprika Sauce and simmer in a 325° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: mural brewer's coconut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs.
Beat after each egg.
Add milk, coconut, nuts and finely crushed vanilla wafers. Bake in an angel food cake pan at 350° for 1 hour and 40 minutes. Let cool in pan.

title: one step peach cobbler
directions: Over low heat, melt butter in a small saucepan; let stand. Combine sugar, flour and milk; stir in melted butter.
Add peaches and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients, then add egg and vanilla; mix well.
Add remaining dry ingredients.
Roll out dough until it fits into a pizza pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool, then spread the packages of cream cheese over the top of pizza cookie.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup powdered sugar over cream cheese.
Mix up 1 box of lemon meringue pudding and spread over powdered sugar. Top with your favorite fruits.

title: puerto rican custard
directions: To Caramelize:
In a small saucepan, over low heat, boil granulated sugar and 1 tablespoon water, stirring constantly, until the sugar melts and turns into a rich golden brown (approximately 15 minutes).
Pour caramel into an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch mold or glass dish.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Soak nuts in bourbon (overnight).
Drain.
Mix powdered sugar, butter and nuts.
Shape into ball; place in refrigerator until cool enough to roll into balls.
Melt paraffin and chocolate bits in double boiler.
Dip candy balls into chocolate.
Place on wax paper.

title: oreo pie
directions: Melt butter and mix with crushed cookies.
Press in 9 x 13-inch
pan.
Spread
softened ice cream over cookies and top with chocolate sauce.
Freeze.

title: apricot and pine nut pilaf(i got this recipe at a cooking demonstration about 6 years ago.)
directions: In a large heavy saucepan, brown pine nuts in butter over medium heat.
With slotted spoon, remove nuts and reserve.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and add brown sugar.
Cook together until bubbling.
Remove from heat.
In a bowl, put cornstarch and salt.
Gradually add the milk and egg yolks, beating until smooth. (Save egg whites for meringue.)
Add milk and egg mixture to brown sugar mixture and cook, stirring constantly, until starts to boil and eventually gets thick.
Pour into your favorite pie shell and top with meringue.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt oleo and cream cheese and heat peppers in pan on top of stove.
When completely melted, mix in corn.
Pour in dish and bake.

title: wild rice
directions: Boil water and pour over wild rice.
Let stand for 1/2 hour. Repeat this 2 or 3 times; let cool.

title: white bean soup
directions: Cover beans with cold water and let stand overnight.
Drain and add beans to ham hock, celery and onion.
Cover with water and simmer until beans are tender.
Press beans through sieve and remove fat and bone from ham hock.
Put lean meat and beans back together and simmer until thick.

title: no-cook marshmallow frosting
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until soft peaks form; add sugar, about 1 tablespoon at a time, beating until smooth and glossy. Add syrup, a little at a time, beating after each addition until frosting peaks.
Fold in vanilla.
Frosts 2 (9-inch) layers.

title: christmas damper
directions: Rub the butter into the flour.
Knead.
Mould into a Christmassy shape (a wreath or a star).
Bake in hot oven (or in ashes if you are cooking it in a fire).
Cook for 20 minutes until brown.
Serve with butter and jam, honey or golden syrup.

title: date nut bread
directions: Pour boiling water over dates; let stand about 5 minutes. Sift dry ingredients.
Add date mixture and eggs, mixing well. Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together.
Serve with grilled chicken or roasted chicken.

title: easy apple crisp
directions: Place apple filling in a pie pan.
Mix all ingredients, except cinnamon and oil, with a fork in a separate bowl until crumbly. Pour over apples, spread evenly.
Pour oil over everything; sprinkle cinnamon over top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350° until brown (not too dark).
Serves 6 to 8 people.
Delicious hot with ice cream on top.

title: mom's lasagna
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until golden.
Add remaining ingredients, except noodles and cheese.
Simmer sauce for 2 hours or use any prepared spaghetti sauce and save 2 hours.

title: raspberry dessert
directions: Soak marshmallows in sour cream.
Stir water into Jello.
Add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate before serving.
Serves 8.

title: grilled marinated chicken
directions: Using a glass jar or blender, dissolve sugar in vinegar and lemon juice.
Add remaining ingredients and shake vigorously until mixed.
Place chicken in shallow dish.
Pour marinade over chicken.
Cover and chill 4 to 5 hours.
Grill medium 10 minutes each side.
Brush with leftover marinade.
If chicken with bone is used, cook 50 to 60 minutes or until tender.
Turn and brush with marinade every 10 minutes.

title: venison sauerbraten
directions: Brown meat in oil in large skillet.
Remove meat.
Add to drippings in pan the gravy mix and water slowly so no lumps.
Then stir in all other ingredients and return meat.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours except last 15 minutes (to thicken).
Serve over hot buttered egg noodles or over mashed potatoes.

title: ham balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Make into balls, using 1/2-cup measuring cup.
Mix catsup and brown sugar; spoon on top of each ham ball.
(If freezing, this can be added on top when ready to bake.)
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
If frozen, bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: homestyle potato soup
directions: Cut potatoes into chunks with skin left on; add to 1/2 gallon boiling water with 2 tablespoons salt.
Saute in butter the carrots, celery, onions, bay leaves and basil.
Add sauteed vegetables to boiling potatoes and add 1 tablespoon pepper.

title: manicotti
directions: Precook meat; let cool.
Mix with crumbs, egg and cheese. Cook noodles 8 to 10 minutes; drain.
Stuff with meat and cheese mix.
Put in oblong pan.
Pour sauce on top.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: meal in a bowl stew
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef and chopped onion. Add beef broth, cream-style corn, potatoes, salt and pepper; mix well. Cover and cook over low heat for 20 to 25 minutes, stirring occasionally. Makes 4 or 5 servings.

title: chinese style pork
directions: Trim excess fat from pork.
Combine flour and ginger, use to coat pork lightly.
In hot oil, in a 3 1/2-quart Dutch oven, brown pork on all sides.
Remove pork as it browns.
While pork browns, drain pineapple, reserving liquid.
Stir cornstarch into pork drippings in Dutch oven.
Add reserved pineapple juice, vinegar, soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to a boil while stirring.
Add meat, sugar, salt and pepper.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Add pineapple and green pepper and cook, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Add bean sprouts, water chestnuts and chili sauce.
Cook 5 minutes longer.
Serve with rice.
If you like Sweet and Sour
this is great!
" And you will never order "Sweet and Sour" out.

title: potato salad
directions: Wash and really scrub potatoes.
Chop into small bite-sized cubes.
Place in medium sized saucepan.
Cover with water and bring to boil until potatoes are almost soft.
Hard boil eggs and place to side to cool.
Chop celery and onion into tiny pieces. Crush garlic and mix with potatoes.
Chop hard-boiled eggs and add to salad.
Add vegetables.
Mix/toss well.
Add dressing to taste. Let salad stand in refrigerator until cool.
Add a little more dressing and toss before serving.

title: stove top baked beans
directions: Mix in saucepan.
Cook over low heat until onion is tender.

title: gladys' black forest trifle
directions: Mix pudding mix with milk until thickened.
Add 1/2 of the Cool Whip to the pudding mixture.
Slice the chocolate rolls in half lengthwise and press cut side against inside perimeter of trifle bowl.
Layer pudding mixture, cherry pie filling and Swiss rolls cut in half lengthwise, continuing until all pudding is used.
Top with Cool Whip.
Decorate with cherries and any remaining Swiss rolls (cut crosswise).

title: chicken divan
directions: Melt butter or margarine in Dutch oven or large skillet over medium flame.
Add onion and celery and cook until onion is tender.
Add rice and seasoning and continue to cook until rice is golden.
Add water and remaining ingredients, except walnuts, and bring to a boil.
Lower flame and simmer, covered, for 20 to 25 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Add walnuts.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour oblong pan.
Sprinkle pecans and coconut in bottom of pan.
Mix German chocolate cake mix as directed on package and pour over pecans and coconut.

title: layered nacho dip
directions: Use 10-inch pie pan or 7 x 12-inch oblong dish.
Combine beans, seasoning mix and chili peppers.
Spread evenly in bottom of dish. Next, spread avocado dip over first layer.
Add chopped onion to sour cream, then spread over second layer.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over all, then olives and tomatoes.
Chill.
Serve with corn chips or tortilla chips.

title: combined dressing
directions: Crumble bread into large pan or bowl.
Melt butter and saute onion and celery.
Add to bread with other ingredients and mix well.
If dressing seems too dry, add a little more broth.
Bake in shallow pan at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: green bean recipe
directions: Melt butter; mix in crushed crackers.
In a bowl, mix all other ingredients except almonds together.
Press half the cracker crumb mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch Pyrex casserole.
Add the green bean mixture.
Place remaining crumbs and the almonds on top.
Cook at 350° until bubbly.

title: orange buttermilk salad
directions: Bring to boil the pineapple and juice.
Add the box of Jell-O; mix this thoroughly.
Add the Cool Whip and buttermilk.
This is low in calories.
Sometimes I add 1 cup cottage cheese.

title: seafood lasagne(betty crocker's cookbook)
directions: Heat margarine in 3-quart saucepan over low heat until melted. Add garlic.
Stir in flour and salt; cook, stirring constantly, until bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk and broth.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in Mozzarella cheese, basil and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until cheese is melted.
Spread 1/4 of the cheese sauce (about 1 1/2 cups) in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: white bread
directions: Dissolve the yeast and sugar in the 1/2 cup lukewarm water. Make sure the yeast mixture gets foamy.
Mix the 2 cups water, salt, sugar and shortening.
Then add the yeast mixture and gradually the flour.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in a greased bowl, cover and set in a warm place to rise until double. Punch down.
Let rise again.
Put in 2 large loaf pans or 3 medium ones.
Let rise until double again.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Makes 2 large or 3 medium loaves.

title: butter bars
directions: Mix together yellow cake mix, stick of butter and 1 egg; press this into a 10 x 20-inch pan.
Mix together confectioners sugar, cream cheese and 1 egg.
Spread this over the cake.
Bake all of this for 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: mamma's chicken chicken
directions: Dip chicken in lemon juice, then roll in seasoned bread crumbs and cheese mixture.
In a baking dish, place onion in and around chicken.
Sprinkle with olive oil and bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: oreo ice cream cake
directions: Break up Oreo cookies.
Mix together softened vanilla ice cream, Cool Whip and Oreos.
Put in 13 x 9-inch pan and freeze.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and sugar together.
Add oil, eggs and pineapple.
Mix by hand.
Add bananas and nuts; mix.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes or until done.
Let cool about 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Frost.

title: macaroni casserole deluxe
directions: Open the 'fridge.
Find three vegetables that won't clash (color is important) in the pot.
Always saute an onion first, with a bit of garlic.

title: rhubarb strawberry pie
directions: Slice strawberries.
If frozen, thaw partially.
Do not drain juice.

title: mom meloy's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together and pour over meat that has approximately 2 cups of liquid or broth.
If not, add 2 cups of water.

title: pineapple squares
directions: Cook pineapple with tapioca for 10 minutes.
Stir; let cool. Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Add to mixture; work until like pie dough.
Roll half of dough mixture into 9 x 13-inch cookie sheet.
Layer with pineapple; roll rest of dough on waxed paper. place dough on top of pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: play-doh
directions: Mix dry ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients and cook over medium heat, about 3 minutes.
Add desired food color while cooking.

title: homemade chilli
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain.
Add onions, pepper and remaining ingredients.
Cook 3 hours over low heat.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Saute beef with onion, but don't brown.
Add salt, pepper and thyme.
Layer noodles, beef mixture, cheese cubes and dot with margarine.
Repeat layering.
Then add 1 can cream of celery soup with 1 can milk and pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: red raspberry and pineapple cocktail
directions: Arrange the fruit in layers in sherbet glasses.
Pour some of the orange juice over each.

title: linguini with white clam sauce(8 servings)
directions: Drain clams; reserve juice.
Saute garlic in olive oil until golden.
Add drained clams; saute until coated.
Add clam juice, white wine, oregano, basil, pepper and parsley.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Cook linguini according to package instructions. Serve sauce over cooked linguini.
Add Parmesan to taste.

title: toffee chips
directions: Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil. Lay crackers on foil to edge of pan. Boil butter and sugar 3 minutes. Pour butter mixture over crackers. Completely cover. Sprinkle pecans over crackers. Bake at 350° 10 minutes. Cool and break into pieces.

title: mom's apple pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Toss with apples. Fill a 9-inch pastry with apples.
Dot with butter.
Put top crust on; seal and flute.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Cover edge with aluminum foil.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 20 to 25 minutes more.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Put in dish and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: wild dove delicious
directions: Salt and pepper dove breasts to taste and dredge in flour. Heat butter in a heavy skillet and brown dove breasts nicely. Sprinkle with thyme and add cream.
Cover tightly and simmer very slowly until tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Serve dove on a platter of wild rice.
Gravy may be thinned with milk, if necessary. Serve gravy separately.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Combine all in saucepan.
Cover; place over medium heat. Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: salmon spread
directions: In mixing bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Spread on a serving platter and shape into a loaf or ball. Top with sour cream. Serve with crackers.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake in hot oven (400°) for 1 hour or until filling is set.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook beans; drain well. Cook onions in butter until wilted and tender but not brown. Add mushrooms. Add flour; mix well, then add milk and stir until thickened. Add cheese; stir until smooth. Add seasonings and mix in beans and chestnuts. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and eggs together.
Add flour and beat until creamy.
Add milk and flavoring.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for about 40 to 50 minutes.

title: frozen citrus salad
directions: Mix and pour into foil lined cups.
Freeze.

title: spicy chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix together soups, milk, tomatoes, onion, pepper and chicken. Start with taco chips and make layers in a buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole of taco chips, soup mixture and cheese.
Make 2 to 3 layers.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 10 to 12.

title: hot spam-wich
directions: Split hamburger buns.
Grate into bowl:
Spam, American cheese and small onion.
Mix with mayonnaise to blend.
Spread on face of 24 buns and broil until brown and/or bubbly.

title: pizza pie
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain fat.
Stir in spaghetti sauce mix, tomato sauce and water; simmer for 10 minutes.
Put mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan; top with Mozzarella.
Put in oven to keep warm. Beat eggs, milk and oil in bowl until foamy.
Beat in flour until smooth.
(This will be runny.) Pour over meat mixture; cover with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Toast and crumble rye bread.
Set aside.
In a bowl, combine soup, milk, onion and mustard.
In order given, place in greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan, layer the sauerkraut, dry noodles, soup mixture, corned beef and Swiss cheese.

title: cheese sticks
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and red pepper; set aside.
Melt butter; let cool.
Pour over cheese; toss gently. Add to dry ingredients.
Put in until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Sprinkle water gently over flour mixture.
Stir with fork until all ingredients are moistened.
Shape into ball.
Roll dough into 1/8-inch thickness on lightly floured surface; cut into 3 x 1/2-inch strips.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets; bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: maple syrup cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add syrup and stir.
Add milk and flour alternately.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: dressing
directions: Mix bread, eggs, salt, pepper and parsley.
Add chicken broth to make it sloppy.
Add melted butter last.
Mix lightly with fork.
Put in a greased bowl or pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not cover.

title: burnt sugar cake
directions: Spread 1/2 cup sugar in iron skillet.
Put over medium flame and burn until a golden brown syrup forms.
Remove from stove. Add 1/2 cup boiling water; allow to cook until thick.
Remove from heat; let cool while you mix cake.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: ranch potato casserole
directions: Wash potatoes and parboil until nearly done, but slightly firm.
Can leave skins on.
Melt oleo and put into 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Slice potatoes 1/4-inch thick.
Put in casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: butterscotch roll
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Cut bread dough into 18 pieces.
Roll in dry pudding mix.
Put in pan.
Melt oleo, brown sugar and nuts. Heat to rolling boil.
Pour over dough.
Cover with waxed paper. Let raise 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let rest 10 minutes in pan, then turn onto plate.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour into 2 uncooked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, milk, salt, pepper and butter. Add corn.
Pour into a greased casserole and bake at 275° for 40 minutes or until set.
(Temperature may need to be increased as it cooks.)

title: filled cookies
directions: Mix together; refrigerate 2 hours.
Cut into squares.
Fill with your favorite filling (nuts, raisins, jelly, etc.).
Bake until done.

title: beef with gravy
directions: Cook beef in melted butter for 15 to 20 minutes or until light brown.
Add onion, mushrooms and soy sauce.
Cook slowly for 10 minutes.
Add water.
Cook for 20 minutes on low heat.
Makes own gravy.
Great over rice.

title: mexican dip
directions: Use a large round serving platter.
Spread bean dip over top in a thin layer.
Pour picante sauce over dip.
Decorate top with grated cheese, diced tomatoes and bite size lettuce pieces.
Be creative!
Serve with chips.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix ingredients to make sauce.
Pour over wings and soak 3 to 5 hours.
Stir often.
Pour sauce and wings in a roaster.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until done.

title: onion dip
directions: Thoroughly combine sour cream and onion mix.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Mix potatoes, sour cream, cottage cheese and salt in 3-quart greased casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: sarah's tea cakes
directions: Put flour in bowl; make a "nest."
Add other ingredients into nest; mix by hand, like making homemade biscuits.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick; cut out with cookie cutter.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: happiness cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare Bundt pan:
Spray with Pam and dust with flour.

title: never fail meringue
directions: Combine 2 tablespoons sugar, cornstarch and water in small pan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until soft mounds form.
Add 6 tablespoons sugar gradually to egg whites, beating well after each addition.
Add cornstarch mixture gradually. Continue beating until meringue stands in peaks.
Cover pie with meringue and brown in 375° oven.

title: vegetable marinade
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour over vegetables.
Chill 4 to 12 hours.
Best raw vegetables:
carrots, celery, broccoli, cauliflower, mushrooms, cucumbers.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar.
Add milk and butter, cut in fourths. Cook on high for 2 minutes.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and nuts. Stir. Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water for about 6 minutes. In saucepan melt butter, blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk, cook and stir until thickened.
Add cheese and onion.
Stir until cheese melts.
Stir in macaroni.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Top with tomato slices before serving.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Mix and bake cake following directions on box.
When cake is done, poke holes throughout it with fork.
Pour Eagle Brand milk and butterscotch topping over cake.
Let cool about 30 minutes. Spread Cool Whip over cake.
Crush Heath bars and spread over top of cake.
Chill before serving.

title: 5 hour oven stew
directions: Combine in roasting pan or Dutch oven.
Cover; put in oven at 275° and forget for 5 hours.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Pour cottage cheese, Cool Whip and Jell-O in a large bowl. Mix together and chill in refrigerator.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix well first 6 ingredients (it is stiff and seems dry) and shape into loaf.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.
Cut in about 1/2-inch slices and roll in flour.
Brown quickly on both sides. Place pieces in roaster.
Mix mushroom soup and 1 can water and pour over meat.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheese dip
directions: Blend Ro-Tel and water.
Add seasoning.
Heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Blend cheese in Ro-Tel mixture.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Bring to boil for 1 minute the sugar, canned milk and margarine.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: zucchini jam
directions: Mix zucchini and sugar.
Boil six minutes.
Add lemon juice and pineapple (undrained).
Boil for six minutes more, add jello right from box, stir and put in containers.
Refrigerate or freeze.

title: play dough(nonedible)
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Blend in the oil and water.
Stir in the food coloring.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until play dough thickens.
Let cool.
Store in a Ziploc bag.
(For playing, not eating.)

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Beat cream cheese with sugar.
Set aside.
In large bowl combine remaining ingredients.
Mix well and add cream cheese. Spoon into ring mold.
Freeze overnight.
Serve frozen.
Set out about 1/2 hour before serving.
Will keep frozen several months.

title: skillet enchiladas
directions: Fry tortillas in oil until they are limp.
Fry hamburger and drain. Add soup, sauce, milk, onion and green chilies. Fill tortillas with cheese and olives. Put them into the hamburger mixture.
Top with cheese. Simmer 10 minutes.

title: smoked turkey
directions: Dissolve Tender Quick and liquid smoke in the gallon of water. Soak turkey 24 hours or more.
Drain and put in roaster.
Bake for 2 to 3 hours.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Toss pecans and coconut together and sprinkle in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix as directed on box, pour over pecans and coconut.
Cream butter, powdered sugar and cream cheese together.
Drop by spoonfuls on top of cake mix.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.
Cool.
Cut in squares and serve upside-down.

title: butterfinger ice cream dessert
directions: Combine
graham cracker crumbs, soda cracker crumbs and oleo, reserving 1/2 cup crumb mixture for topping.
Press into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except coconut.
Cook until thick. Add coconut.
Frost cake.
Sprinkle coconut on top if desired.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Cook until soft ball. Cool. Spread.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cut up lettuce, cauliflower and broccoli into a bowl.
Then add chopped onions, topped with grated cheese.
Mix sugar and mayonnaise and spread on top.
Do not mix.
Cover with a lid or plastic wrap and refrigerate.
Salad is best when prepared 2 to 3 hours before serving.
When ready to serve, mix well.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream margarine and light brown sugar, then add eggs, corn meal, water, vanilla, salt and pecans.
Mix well.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, until firm.

title: stovetop salmon and rice casserole(can be prepared in 18 minutes.)
directions: Put water and peas into a large skillet or 4-quart Dutch oven and bring to a boil.
Peel and shred carrots.
Add to skillet with onion and thyme.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes or until carrots are tender.
Stir in soup and milk until blended, then rice.
Stir in salmon, breaking up any large chunks.
Bring to boil, cover and remove from heat.
Let stand about 5 minutes, stirring once, until rice is tender and most of the liquid is absorbed.
Sprinkle with potato chips.
Serve immediately.
Yields 4 servings.

title: punch
directions: Mix punch, orange juice and lemonade and chill.
Add chilled ginger ale and sherbet before serving.

title: frozen waldorf salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
In a saucepan, combine juice with sugar, eggs and salt.
Cook, stirring until slightly thickened.
Remove from heat.
Cool.
Stir in pineapple, celery, apples and pecans.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into 9-inch square pan.
Cover and freeze.
Let stand at room temperature for about 10 to 15 minutes.
Cut into squares or serve on a lettuce leaf.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil, sugar and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to sugar and egg mixture.
Add zucchini and nuts.
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans 1 hour or until done at 325°.

title: baked fish
directions: Soak fresh fish in milk 1/2 hour.
Prepare dressing as per instructions on package.
Bake, covered, 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover fish and baste with butter.
Bake an additional 1/2 hour.

title: amish walnut cookies
directions: Cream shortening, margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and salt. Add walnuts and mix well.
Mix together flour, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Blend with creamed mixture.
Put by teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Press down a little and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for about 12 or 13 minutes.
Makes about 7 dozen cookies.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Mix flour and baking powder.
Add vanilla to sour cream.
Add flour and baking powder alternately with sour cream and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: plum cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil.
Add plum baby food. Combine flour and nuts and add to other ingredients; mix well.
Bake in tube pan that has been buttered and floured at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Make a triangle.
Put bologna on it.
Put cheese on it.
Put sauce on it.
Cook for 10 minutes in the oven.
Take it out.
Let it cool then eat.
(Sprinkle cheese on top before you eat it.)

title: mary clara's oyster casserole
directions: A complement with turkey, chicken, pork or by itself.
Open can and pour oysters and juice into casserole dish.
Wash hands and mash oysters with hands.
Add bread and mix; mash with oysters. Pour milk over, but do not mix.
Place pats of butter or margarine on top.
Salt and pepper top as directed.
Bake in 375° oven about 45 minutes.
Will look juicy when you take it out, but will set like custard pie.
Serves 4, but can be doubled.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix powdered sugar and peanut butter until crumbly. Put 2/3 of crumbs in the bottom of pie shell. Cook pudding according to directions on package. Let cool. Stir 1 tablespoon crumbs into pudding. Pour pudding over crumbs in pie shell. Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle on remaining crumbs. Chill.

title: peanut butter swirl bars
directions: In large bowl, combine peanut butter, butter, brown sugar and granulated sugar; beat until creamy.
Gradually beat in eggs and the vanilla.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend into peanut butter mixture.
Spread into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1 (12 ounce) package chocolate morsels over surface.
Place in 350° oven for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven and run knife through to marbleize.
Return to oven for 25 minutes.

title: macadamia nut stuffing
directions: In large saucepan, cook sausage, celery and onion.
Drain off fat.
Dissolve bouillon in water; add to sausage mixture.
Add sage and pepper.
Stir in bread cubes and nuts.

title: crock-pot cheese potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes.
Peel.
Cut up.
Peel and cut up onion.
Mix soup, onion, sour cream and melted butter in crock-pot.
Put potatoes in.
Mix well.
Sprinkle onion flakes on top (optional). Cook on low 1 to 2 hours.

title: walnut cheese appetizers
directions: Combine cheese and next 5 ingredients.
Spread cheese mixture on pita triangles.
Place on baking sheet.
Broil 5 to 6 inches from heat source for 2 to 3 minutes, or until cheese is melted. Makes 48 appetizers.

title: cheese cake
directions: Grease 9-inch spring-form pan with margarine.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Beat cream cheese with cottage cheese until creamy.
Beat in sugar and eggs.
Beat in cornstarch, flour, lemon juice and vanilla.
Add melted butter and sour cream.
Pour into pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Turn off oven.
Let stand in oven 2 hours. Remove sides of pan and refrigerate.
Serve with fruit.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Break up sausage and fry together with hamburger.
Remove from heat; drain and add spaghetti sauce.
Cook shells according to package directions.
Rinse well with cold water.
Mix together cottage cheese, shredded Mozzarella cheese and eggs.
Stuff shells with cheese mixture.
Layer shells and sauce in deep baking dish. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: fiddleneck ferns
directions: Wash ferns, using brush to remove brown flaky coating; cut into bite-sized pieces and set aside.
Saute bacon and garlic in skillet until bacon is crisp.
Add ferns and water.
Simmer, tightly covered, until ferns are fork-tender, stirring occasionally.
Serve like asparagus.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: In medium saucepan, combine ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Cool.
Pour into pie shells.
Top with egg whites and 1/4 cup sugar beaten stiff. Brown in oven at 425° for about 3 to 5 minutes.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In skillet brown ground beef.
Add garlic, tomatoes, sauce, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer about 30 minutes.
In a Pyrex dish, layer sauce, noodles and cheese until finished.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: homemade vegetable beef soup
directions: Note:
May also add any leftover vegetables from refrigerator.

title: strawberry fig preserves
directions: Mix together. Bring to a boil. Boil about 3 minutes. Put in jelly jars and seal. May also use raspberry jello.

title: cream of coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box, using an oblong pan. Let cool.
Using a drinking straw, make holes all over the cake.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Crumble; set aside.
Place the potatoes in a large stockpot.
Add just enough water to cover. Add in the onion, instant broth, thyme, oil, bacon and ham.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer until potatoes are tender. Drain off excess water.
Return to heat; stir in the remaining ingredients.
Blend until smooth and heat through.

title: fresh churned butter
directions: In a gallon jug, empty whipping cream and buttermilk.
Let set at room temperature 15 hours until mixture becomes extremely thick.
When cream reaches this stage, it is ready to churn.

title: lemon bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Blend flour, butter and powdered sugar. Press in square 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes.
Beat remaining ingredients together.
Pour over crust and bake another 25 minutes.

title: lori's punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except club soda and fruit; chill.
When ready to serve, mix in cold club soda and gently stir in fruit. Add frozen water ring last.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and spread for first layer.
Mix the taco seasoning, Miracle Whip and sour cream and spread for second layer.
Sprinkle the cheese for the third layer.
Sprinkle the tomato for fourth layer.
Sprinkle the green onions for fifth layer.
Sprinkle the lettuce for the sixth layer.
Top with sliced olives for the seventh layer, if desired.
Use large corn chips with Taco Dip.

title: angel lemon-pineapple dessert
directions: Divide cake pieces evenly among eight 6-ounce custard cups or parfait glasses.
In medium bowl, combine gelatin and boiling water; stir until gelatin is completely dissolved.

title: "crock-pot" pork chops
directions: Just cook on low for 4 to 6 hours.
Gooooood!!!!

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill in refrigerator.
Do not cook pudding.

title: barbecue turkey loaf(microwave recipe)
directions: Combine 1 cup stuffing mix, vegetables, water and butter.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Combine remaining stuffing mix, turkey, eggs and 1/4 cup barbecue sauce; mix well.
tags: Stove Top chicken flavor stuffing mix

title: prize winning burrito
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown ground beef and drain the grease. Grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Mix Bisquick, water and beans.
Spread in pie plate.
Layer remaining ingredients on bean mixture, ending with cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Serve with sour cream, if desired.

title: applesauce fruit cake
directions: Combine applesauce, solid shortening and sugar in a saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Then cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Let cool.

title: hot milk sponge cake
directions: Heat butter and milk in microwave until butter is melted. Beat eggs until fluffy; add sugar.
Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix with egg mixture.
Add hot milk mixture.
Add vanilla.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Check at 30 minutes.
Some ovens are different.
Rub one stick of butter over hot cake.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over cake.

title: apple brown betty
directions: Wash and peel apples.
Pile in a 9 x 13-inch buttered dish.

title: russian tea
directions: In a large bowl, mix jello and sugar, then add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Put in slow cooker and simmer for 4 to 6 hours. Strain and serve hot or cold.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients, shape into cakes, fry in butter.

title: cuke-apple rings
directions: Soak cucumbers
in lime water overnight (1 cup lime and 1 gallon water).
Rinse
3 times until all lime is washed off; soak in ice water 3 hours.

title: spaghetti-vegetable salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain and rinse with cold water. Combine artichokes, olives, peas, bell pepper, zucchini, onion and cheese. Add spaghetti. Stir well. Combine mayonnaise, parsley, dill, pepper and Italian dressing. Stir with wire whisk; add to spaghetti mixture and stir well. Cover and chill.

title: vanilla milkshake
directions: In blender combine milk, ice cream and ice.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into a glass top with whipped cream.

title: prawns - garlic and spice
directions: Cut prawns along the back with a small pair of scissors from end to just before the tail, leaving the shell and tail on. Remove the vein; rinse and dry with paper towel.

title: salsa dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut hole in center of bread.
Hole has to be big enough for ingredients.
(Save bread pieces for dipping.)

title: maple-glazed salmon
directions: Prepare grill, heating to medium.

title: beau monde
directions: Toss all together; chill for at least 4 hours before serving.

title: poticia-nut bread
directions: Mix yeast with lukewarm milk.
Add sugar and flour; stir well. Cover bowl and set aside to rise in warm place.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Prepare a 9-inch graham cracker pie crust according to package directions.
Beat first 5 ingredients together; fold in Cool Whip. Pour into crust.
Do not bake.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chicken divan
directions: Layer broccoli and chicken in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Mix soup, mayonnaise and curry powder in a bowl.
Pour over chicken.
Top with bread crumbs.
Drizzle with butter.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with cheese, if desired.

title: french fudge
directions: Mix in bowl the butter, chocolate chips, nuts and vanilla. Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with waxed paper.
Combine in heavy pan the sugar and milk.
Bring to a rolling boil and boil for exactly 6 minutes.
(Start timing when mixture comes to a rolling boil.) Pour over ingredients in bowl.
Mix well until chips are dissolved.
Pour into pan and chill.

title: apple-butter pie
directions: Combine first six ingredients and mix well.
Blend in milk and butter.
Pour filling into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: salmon florentine
directions: Remove skin from salmon and cut in half lengthwise.
Drain spinach, pressing out excess liquid.
Combine cream cheese, onion and salt; divide into fourths.
Spread over fillets and roll up around filling.
Tie with green onion strip or kitchen string. Place in a microwavable colander/steamer with lemon slices.
In a 2-quart microwavable bowl or bottom of the steamer, pour the boiling water, bouillon and dill.
Cook, covered, on high for 5 to 7 minutes or until fish is flaky.
In a microwavable bowl, combine milk and cornstarch with the bouillon mixture; microwave for 30 seconds, stir and microwave for 30 more seconds or until thickened.
Spoon over fish and serve.

title: pan sausage casserole
directions: Saute pepper, onion and sausage until fully cooked; drain well.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, add rice, soup and cheese; mix well.
Add well drained meat mixture; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: In skillet, brown meat and cook onions until done.
Stir in corn, tomato sauce, rice, steak sauce and pepper.
Set aside.
Cut tops off the peppers; remove the seeds.
Spoon meat mixture into the peppers.
Place into a baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until peppers are done.

title: rice my way
directions: Melt margarine in medium size frying pan.
Saute rice and onion until rice looks pearly.
Add water, spices and bouillon cube.
Stir once, then cover and let cook over low heat for about 30 minutes.
Add mushrooms about 5 minutes before rice is finished cooking.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Bring to boil, then simmer 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Remove chicken to cool, then remove from bones.
Strain stock and add water, if necessary, to make 4 cups of stock.
In small bowl, stir 1/2 cup flour and 1/2 cup milk until smooth.
Stir in cooked vegetables.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and cook about 8 minutes or until sauce is thick.
Place hot chicken and vegetables into a 3-quart casserole.
Place crust on top or use a ready-made pie crust. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 450°.

title: giant ground beef sandwich
directions: Slice top crust off bread.
Hollow crumbs from the center, leaving only the side crusts.
Mix ground chuck, onion, bell pepper, Ro-Tel, mushrooms and crumbs from inside of bread.	Put ground chuck mixture inside loaf of bread.	Cover with cheese. Put top crust on top of mixture.
Wrap in foil and bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Slice and serve.

title: strawberry frost
directions: Put half the strawberries in the refrigerator.
Half the remaining strawberries.
Chop the banana coarsely and freeze together until solid.

title: blackberry cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix flour, sugar, eggs, shortening, cinnamon, buttermilk, vanilla and water.
Add blackberries.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake springs back when touched. Bake in well-greased pan.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Put cabbage, onion, and green pepper in a bowl. Pour sugar over it and set aside.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat all ingredients very good.
Spray a large pie pan with Pam.
This will form its own crust.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: lemon-pepper pasta with clams
directions: Drain clams and reserve juice.
In skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat; add onion and cook until soft, about 5 minutes. Add garlic and cook 1 minute more.
Stir in reserved clam juice, broth, lemon juice and lemon peel; bring to a boil.
In small bowl, combine cornstarch with 1 tablespoon water and whisk into boiling broth mixture; boil 1 minute.
Reduce heat to low and stir in clams and parsley.
Cook pasta according to package directions and combine with clam sauce.

title: mama teal's seafood lasagna
directions: Mix spaghetti sauce and seafood; heat until warm.
Cook noodles according to directions on package.
Mix Ricotta, Parmesan, parsley and beaten eggs.
Add salt and pepper to taste. In a casserole dish, place a layer of noodles, then sauce mix, then cheeses and cover with grated Mozzarella; repeat layers. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: french creme pie
directions: Cook flour, sugar, Milnot and milk until thick.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cool and serve.

title: best ever cake
directions: Blend sugar, flour and soda.
Whip eggs and vanilla.
Dump together pineapple and nuts.
Combine.
Using sheet cake pan bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients.
Shape into meatballs.
Arrange meatballs in a greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Using a slatted spoon, transfer meatballs to a Dutch oven or large pan.
Pour barbecue sauce over meatballs and cook slowly for 3 to 4 hours.
Cocktail franks can be added at anytime if you wish.
(Also can be cooked in a crock-pot.
The secret is to make sure they are cooked thoroughly and slowly, so the sauce blends.)

title: lemon sour cream pie
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Slowly stir in milk.
Cook and stir until mixture is boiling and thickens. Blend small amount of hot mix into 3 slightly beaten egg yolks; return to hot mixture.
Cook and stir 2 minutes over medium heat. Add butter, lemon peel and lemon juice.
Cover and cool.
Fold in sour cream.
Spoon into a 9-inch cooked pastry shell.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar and vanilla.
Gradually add 6 tablespoons sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Cover pie filling and brown in oven.
Chill several hours before filling.

title: white bean and olive salad
directions: Combine all ingredients. Toss gently to mix.
Taste and add more lemon, if desired.
Makes 6 servings, 160 calories per serving.

title: wild strawberry marmalade
directions: Boil strawberries, rhubarb, sugar and pineapple for 20 minutes.
Add strawberry jello.
Put in sterilized glasses and seal.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, water and 1 box strawberries.
Cook until thick and clear.
Add jello; mix well. Add the other box of strawberries.
Put in cool crust and chill. Top with whipped cream.

title: dilly bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Let rise 45 minutes.
Put in greased loaf pan; let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Brush with melted butter and salt, after it cools some.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix shortening, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Add gradually to creamy mixture.
Chill overnight.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper in skillet.
Add rice, chili powder and tomatoes.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Put in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: brunch special
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan. Layer bread cubes, cheeses, crumbled bacon and ham.
Pour liquid mixture over and refrigerate, covered, overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes until browned.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: snickersnack
directions: Mix in a large bowl toasted oat cereal, peanuts and raisins. Heat in saucepan over low heat, the margarine or butter until melted.
Pour margarine or butter over cereal mixture, using fork to toss lightly until mixture is coated.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over the mixture and toss again.
Makes 7 cups.

title: sea voice inn peach kuchen
directions: Combine flour, salt, baking powder and 2 tablespoons sugar together.
Cut in margarine or butter to form coarse crumbs. Press mixture onto bottom and sides of well-greased 8-inch baking dish.

title: guacamole
directions: Mash avocados together with lemon juice, seasoned salt, garlic salt and hot pepper sauce.
Cover.
Chill thoroughly.
Stir in all but 1 tablespoon bacon.
Garnish with remaining bacon.
Makes 2 cups.

title: triple chocolate biscotti
directions: Beat butter, 1 cup sugar, baking powder and 1/8 teaspoon salt until combined.
Beat in 2 eggs, 1 egg yolk and creme de cacao, then add cocoa, flour, chocolate pieces and nuts.
Divide dough in half.
Shape into an 11-inch roll and flatten to 2-inches in width.

title: horseradish sauce
directions: Mix together ingredients until well blended; chill.
Serve with seafood, onion rings, poultry, etc.

title: taco dip
directions: In 8-inch pie plate, cream cheese on bottom.
Brown ground beef; drain grease.
Mix taco seasoning in ground beef.
Top the cream cheese with ground beef mixture.
Spoon salsa on top to cover.
Top with cheese.
Microwave 5 to 8 minutes.

title: chocolate chip rum cake
directions: Put all ingredients into a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 7 minutes.
Pour in a greased Bundt or angel food pan.
Bake for 60 minutes at 325° to 350°.
Cake may need 55 to 65 minutes, depending on oven.
Let stand in pan for 10 minutes to cool.
Turn out onto plate.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Brown chicken with olive oil and garlic.
Add broth; bring to boil.
Add mushrooms, soy sauce and sesame oil.
To thicken (if desired), add cornstarch.
Add snow peas 1 minute before turning it off.
Serve over hot rice.
Serves 4.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix spinach, bean sprouts, eggs and bacon.
Mix dressing ingredients together and toss with spinach.

title: frozen pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, onions and peppers in large bowl.
Mix sugar, vinegar, salt and celery seed.
Pour over cucumber mixture. Refrigerate 24 hours.
Put into plastic containers with lids and place in freezer.

title: cherry fluff
directions: Drain the pineapple tidbits.
Mix cherry pie filling and drained pineapple tidbits.
Fold in marshmallows and whipped topping.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 2 pie shells (unbaked).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Turn on oven and set at 375°.
Mix brown sugar, flour, spices and salt in a 3-quart bowl.
Add pumpkin, evaporated milk and egg and stir until smooth.
Pour into unbaked shells.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes until knife inserted 2-inches from edge comes out clean. Serve warm or cold.

title: hot tomato dip
directions: Chill for 2 hours and serve with Doritos.

title: plain and simple potato salad
directions: Peel and wash potatoes.
Dice potatoes and place in large pot and cover with enough water to boil.
Add a couple of shakes of salt.
Boil potatoes until tender.
While potatoes are boiling, put eggs on to boil until cooked, about 12 to 15 minutes. When potatoes are tender, drain.
Peel cooked eggs and put in potatoes. Mash together.
Add mayonnaise just until smooth and creamy.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over quick oats.
Let stand while mixing remaining ingredients.
Add oatmeal to mixture and blend well. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
As soon as cake gets done, add topping and put back in oven on broil until brown.

title: noodles and apples
directions: Wash, core, peel and cut apples in 1/8's.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in baking dish.
Place 1/2 of noodles in dish; then the apples.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of the sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Cover with remaining noodles.
Dot with remaining butter.
Sprinkle remaining sugar and cinnamon mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: nat's renowned world famous road kill chili(not for the faint of heart.)
directions: *Tom Greve says to make sure you soak the beans long enough!

title: wassail
directions: Put cinnamon, cloves and red hots in basket of coffee pot. Put apple juice in coffee pot and perk. Serve hot. Reduce portions for small bottle of juice.

title: manhattan deli salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions.
In a large bowl, combine olives, pepper, salami, onion, cheese, parsley and Italian dressing.
Add pasta and toss well.
Serve at room temperature or chilled.
Best served same day.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Put red and green peppers through a food grinder using the medium blade; reserve juice.
In a large saucepan, combine ground peppers and juice, sugar, vinegar and optional jalapeno peppers; bring to a boil and remove from heat.
Add pectin, stirring until mixture thickens.
Fill hot sterilized jars, leaving 1/8-inch headspace.
Wipe rims with a damp cloth.
Seal with lids according to manufacturer's directions.
Process in a boiling water for 5 minutes.
Makes 3 pints.

title: mamie eisenhower's fudge
directions: Put these ingredients into a large bowl.
Pour boiling syrup over the ingredients in bowl.
Beat until chocolates are melted. I use an electric mixer.
Pour into 2 greased 8 x 10-inch pans. Let stand a few hours before cutting.
Can be refrigerated.
You can also make 1/2 recipe plain and 1/2 recipe with nuts.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: vegetarian walnut oat burgers
directions: Mix well together; add just enough hot water to hold together. Mix well.
Brown in oiled skillet on both sides.
Serve in burger buns or with gravy as a meatless main dish.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix ingredients and refrigerate before serving.
Great as a celery dip for hot wings as well as a salad dressing.

title: chicken n' stuffing
directions: Prepare stuffing per directions.

title: easy taco dinner
directions: Cook and stir ground beef and onion in 10-inch skillet until lightly browned; drain.
Stir in water and seasoning mix.
Heat to boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally for 10 minutes.
Layer tortilla chips in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Spoon beef mixture over chips.
Top with remaining ingredients. Makes 6 servings; 635 calories per serving.

title: braised butternut squash and turnips(serves 8)
directions: Cut each squash in half lengthwise and quarter into thin slices.
Cut turnips the same way.
Place vegetables in a large heavy skillet; sprinkle with thyme and pour chicken style seasoning and water broth over.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered.
Stir occasionally for 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Remove vegetables to a serving bowl with slotted spoon.
Sprinkle vegetables with parsley, lemon juice and salt.
Pour reduced broth over and stir well.

title: rainbow finger jello
directions: Separately dissolve each package of jello with 1 cup boiling water.
Cool.
Dissolve the unflavored gelatin and sugar in 1 1/4 cup boiling water.
Add enough milk to make 3 cups.
Oil a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour 1 jello mixture into pan and refrigerate until set; approximately 25 minutes.
Pour 1 cup milk mixture over first layer of jello.
Refrigerate until set.
Alternate jello and milk mixtures.
Cut into cubes or desired shapes.

title: canning peaches
directions: Wash and peel peaches.
Put peaches in quart jars.
Pour hot syrup over peaches and seal.
Microwave the sugar and water for 3 to 5 minutes.
Process in pressure cooker for 8 minutes at 5 pound pressure.
Makes 1 quart at a time following this process.

title: potato soup
directions: Wash potatoes thoroughly; peel and dice.
Simmer with water in soup pot.
When potatoes are almost done, pour off enough water so that potatoes are barely covered.
Add onions, celery, carrot and canned milk.
Simmer until onion and celery are tender.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook and drain fat off meat or rinse meat.
Follow cooking instructions on package.
Use whole grain rolls.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, mixing well.
Spread half of this mixture in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Cover this layer with chili peppers and cheese.
Spread remaining batter over top.
Bake in hot oven at 400° about 30 minutes or until browned.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Saute parsley, onion and celery in 1/2 cup butter. Simmer for 20 minutes. Add ground beef. Cook 15 minutes longer, stirring constantly. Stir in shrimp and cook an additional 5 minutes, continuing to stir. Place bread in large baking pan. Pour water over until bread is dampened. Squeeze dry. Add egg. Mix well. Add beef/shrimp mixture. Mix well. Season with thyme, salt and pepper. Bake at 325° for 2 hours, stirring well every 30 minutes. Remove from oven. Cool and refrigerate. Stuff pepper with cooled mixture. Top with bread crumbs. Brush with 1/4 cup melted butter or margarine. Brown under broiler.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook pasta shells until al dente.
Drain and rinse with cold water; drain well.
Saute sausage and ground beef until crumbly. Drain and discard fat.
In large frying pan, saute garlic and onions until transparent.
Add the spinach and cook until collapses and liquid evaporates.
Combine sauteed meat with spinach/onions in a bowl.
Add remaining ingredients, except pasta sauce and Mozzarella.
Mix well using hands.
Place 2 1/2 cups (pasta) tomato sauce into 2 (13 x 9-inch) baking dishes.
Fill shells with meat mixture, close and place seam-down in sauce.
Top shells with remaining sauce; cover with Mozzarella and sprinkle of Parmesan.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Uncover and broil to brown cheese slightly.

title: spinach lasagne
directions: Mix the beaten egg, spinach, salt, pepper and oregano.
Brown the beef with the onion.
Add the spaghetti sauce; cook about 5 minutes.
Mix the Ricotta, Mozzarella, egg, spinach and seasonings.
In a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish, put 1/2 cup sauce, 1/3 of uncooked noodles and 1/3 cheese mixture.
Make 2 more layers with cheese mixture on top.
Push away from sides of dish; pour water around edges.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: worms in jello
directions: Follow directions on jello pack.
Pour into 4 small bowls. Put in refrigerator approximately 1 hour or until jello starts setting.
Remove bowls from refrigerator and suspend gummy worms into center of bowls, then replace bowls in refrigerator.

title: crispy herb baked chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease or line with foil, 15 x 10-inch baking pan or 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: frosted lime-walnut salad
directions: Pour boiling water over gelatin; stir until dissolved. Chill.
Add pineapple, cottage cheese, celery, pimiento and walnuts.
Pour into 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Frost with combined cream cheese, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Cut into squares; arrange on salad greens.
Garnish with walnut halves.

title: vegetable beef egg rolls
directions: In skillet, cook beef, sesame oil, garlic and pepper until done; drain fat.
On medium heat, add cabbage, oyster sauce and onion.
Cook 20 minutes, stirring occasionally, until cabbage is 3/4 cooked.
Add carrots.
Cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; let cool.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt and flour.
Add pumpkin and lightly browned butter.
Add eggs and milk.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Sprinkle with cinnamon on top.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes. Lower to 350° for approximately 35 minutes (until center of pie is rounded).
(If a spicy pie is desired, add spices to the sugar mixture.)

title: potato soup
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in a large Dutch oven; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Cook bacon in a large skillet until crisp.
Remove bacon, reserving 3 tablespoons drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon; set aside.
Add flour to drippings in skillet; stir until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened and bubbly.
Gradually stir milk mixture and bacon into potato mixture.
Simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil and chop chicken.
Chop celery, eggs, pickles and olives. Mix all ingredients.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice and milk gently in 3-quart saucepan, stirring occasionally until mixture is creamy (about 5 minutes). Meanwhile, combine eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla, slowly stirring rice mixture into egg mixture.
In processor, stir in raisins (optional).
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with cinnamon, if desired.
Place in pan containing 1-inch of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Layer beans and corn in casserole dish.
Mix soup, cheese, sour cream and onion.
Pour over corn and beans.
Melt butter. Mix with Ritz crackers (crushed) until all are well moistened. Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: sweet and sour kielbasa
directions: Slice kielbasa in 1/4-inch slices.
Boil about 10 minutes on medium fire.
Set aside.
Mix Grey Poupon and jelly in saucepan and cook until well blended, about 10 minutes.
Add kielbasa to jelly mixture.
Serve as an appetizer.

title: bread pudding
directions: Break bread to bite size pieces and place in buttered 1 quart baking
dish;
set aside.
Heat margarine and milk until milk is hot
and
margarine
melted.
Do not boil.	Beat eggs with sugar, vanilla
and
salt.
Add milk mixture to egg mixture, stirring constantly, then pour over bread.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle top
with
nutmeg and cinnamon sugar.
Put baking dish in pan of hot water half the depth of dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° about 50 minutes or until set.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix the Eagle Brand milk, whipping cream, half and half milk, chocolate syrup and candy bars, chopped.
Mix well.
Finish filling canister the rest of the way with whole milk.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel and slice or dice cucumbers.
Put in bowl with 2 teaspoons salt.
Mix and let stand at room temperature at least 1 hour.
Drain and pat dry.
Meanwhile, mix green onions, salt and pepper with cream.
When ready to serve, shred lettuce.
Add cucumbers and cream mixture.
Mix well.
This salad requires a good amount of pepper.
Serves 6.

title: rich biscuits
directions: Blend together with fork.
Knead briefly.
Roll out and cut. Bake 9 minutes at 425°.
Brush top with butter when taken out of oven.

title: 20 minute chocolate cake
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 20 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Place crescent rolls in pizza pan to make crust.
Brush beaten egg on crust.
Bake at 375° for 11 to 13 minutes.
Mix cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing and put over crust.
Place vegetables over cheese mixture.

title: yellow angel food cake
directions: Measure flour, sift
times
and
then measure again. Add baking powder
and
sift
again.
Beat
egg
yolks and the water for 10 minutes with the egg beater, then add salt, cream of tartar, sugar
and
flavoring;
then fold in flour mixture. Bake in an angel food tube pan 1 hour at 325°.
Ice with lemon custard pudding.

title: boiled dinner
directions: Cover corned beef with cold water and bring to a boil.
Simmer in tightly covered pan for one hour.
Add all vegetables except cabbage and simmer 1/2 hour longer.
Add cabbage and cook uncovered for 15 minutes.
Yield:
8 servings.
Carbohydrate 14 g, protein 21 g, fat 21 g, calories 284.
One serving = 3 meat medium fat exchange, 1 bread starch exchange.

title: cheese danish
directions: Grease bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread 1 package of crescent rolls on bottom of pan.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and egg yolk.
Spread on top of crescent rolls that are in the pan.
Spread second package of crescent rolls on top of cream cheese mixture.
Brush with beaten egg white on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: florentine squash bake
directions: Place flour and red pepper in a bowl.
Gradually add milk, blending with a wire whisk until smooth.
Set aside.
Coat a large saucepan with cooking spray and place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add onion and garlic; saute 1 minute.
Add milk mixture and cook 6 minutes or until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add cheese and spinach; stir well.
Remove from heat; stir in squash and Prosciutto.
Spoon mixture into a 13 x 9-inch casserole coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: glazed carrots and pineapple
directions: Cover and cook the carrots with water and salt until barely tender.
Drain liquid from carrots into measuring cup and add reserved pineapple juice until you have 1 cup.
Pour into saucepan and mix with cornstarch.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and clear.
Stir in butter.
Add carrots and pineapple tidbits.
Heat.
Serves 4.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into a casserole dish.

title: one dish dinner
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salt water until tender; drain.
Fry onion in hot shortening until yellow.
Add meat, salt and pepper. Brown and then drain.
Add tomatoes, cheese and macaroni.
Mix well.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: coconut buttermilk pie(this makes two pies)
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake 1 hour or until done at 325°.

title: custard pie
directions: Mix well.
Mix all with hot milk and bake in unbaked pie shell at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes until firm and golden brown on top and inserted knife comes out clean.

title: fancy franks
directions: In small skillet, blend the chili sauce and jelly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for at least 15 minutes before serving.
Serve with toothpick.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix all ingredients with enough Miracle Whip salad dressing to hold it together.
Chill at least 2 or 3 hours before serving.

title: chuck roast
directions: Place the chuck roast in the center of a large piece of Reynolds Wrap in a roasting pan.
Brush the meat with A.1. steak sauce and sprinkle the onion soup mix over it.
Spread with the mushroom soup.
Wrap loosely in foil and bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: banana crunch punch
directions: Mash bananas. Add lemon and orange juices. Add water, sugar and pineapple juice. Mix well. Freeze in 1 or 2 pint containers. When ready to serve, remove containers from freezer and set out at room temperature for 15 to 30 minutes. Cut in pieces and place in blender. Blend, gradually adding 7-Up until slushy. Pour into glasses.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix tuna, soup, peas and pimentos in small baking dish.
Place biscuits on top, best if not touching.
Cut 10 strips of cheese. Place one strip on each biscuit.
Place in a 375° oven for about 20 minutes or until biscuits are brown.
Make sure they are not gooey on bottom.

title: chicken soup
directions: Using small pan, bring a cup of water to a boil and drop in porcine.
Cook uncovered over medium to high heat for 10 minutes, drain, pat dry and slice thinly.
Set aside.
In a large saute pan, melt butter over low heat.
Add leeks, carrots, onion, celery and chicken; stir gently and cover to cook over low heat for five minutes.
Stir vegetables, turn chicken and check for doneness (should be about half done).
Cover and cook 5 minutes or until chicken is just done.
Remove chicken from pan.
Sprinkle flour over melted butter, vegetables and pan juices, stir and cook over low heat for 2 minutes.
Slowly add wine and two cups of broth. Stir and cook until bubbly and thickened.
Add sour cream very slowly and allow to cook gently while you slice chicken into bite sized pieces.
In a large frying pan, bring the remaining stock to a boil and add fideo.
Cook four minutes, until almost done.
Do not drain.
Slowly add the noodle mixture to the hot vegetables, etc. Add chicken and bring back to a boil.
Serves 4.

title: english muffin pizzas
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Place English muffin on a baking sheet. Top with 1 or 2 tablespoons spaghetti sauce, shredded cheese and pepperoni.
Bake for 5 to 7 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: date roll
directions: Crush crackers and set about 2 cups aside.
Combine remaining ingredients; will be sticky.
Roll mixture in reserved cracker crumbs to shape of a log.
Should be firm enough to handle.
Wrap in foil and chill.
To serve, slice and dot with whipped cream.

title: harvest rice
directions: In a large skillet, cook carrots in oil about 5 minutes over medium heat. Add green onions and apples. Cook 3 - 5 minutes longer. Stir in remaining ingredients. Cook until thoroughly heated. Makes 6 servings. 193 calories per serving.

title: potato and ham casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes in large baking dish.
(I usually baked covered, then uncover last 10 to 15 minutes.)
Double and you have lots of "filling food" for hungry teenagers!

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Brown in oleo the ground meat and onions.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer one-half hour.
Serves 3 to 4.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Cook and drain peas.
Cool.
Layer lettuce, onion, celery, peppers and peas.
Spread mayonnaise over peas.
Then add cheese and bacon.
Chill one day or overnight.
Serve.

title: indian cake
directions: Mix together the flour, sugar, cocoa, eggs, soda and salt. Carefully add hot coffee, a little at a time, so as not to cook eggs. Add hot water and melted butter.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan (works well in Bundt pan). Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Frost with fudge frosting.

title: chocolate macaroon bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine graham cracker crumbs, sugar, cocoa and margarine; press firmly on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: german sauerbraten
directions: Marinate with spices and meat for 2 days in refrigerator, covered. After first day turn to other side.

title: cornmeal drop biscuits
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a large bowl; make a well in center of mixture.

Combine milk, oil, honey and egg; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened. Drop dough by heaping tablespoons 2 inches apart, onto baking sheet sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yield:
1 dozen (98 calories each).

title: taco dip 2
directions: Mix together cream cheese and sour cream. Spread on a platter. Spread salsa on top of cream cheese mixture.
Spread diced onion and pepper on top of salsa. Cover this layer with shredded lettuce.
Cover the lettuce with shredded cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: blueberry cream cheese cake
directions: Mix as directed; cook in 6 layers for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: crunchy mocha drops(club member: leslie jordan)
directions: In top of double boiler, melt butter in milk. Stir in frosting mix and instant coffee until smooth. Heat over rapidly boiling water 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
