Stir in coconut. Keeping mixture over hot water, drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper. Cool until firm.

title: italian sweet-sour dressing
directions: Thoroughly combine all ingredients in a jar or blender. Refrigerate.
Makes 2 cups dressing.

title: hush puppies delicious
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add onion and corn.
(Add milk, if needed.)
Drop with teaspoon into hot fat until golden brown.

title: shrimp spread
directions: In a small mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese until smooth. Add sour cream and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Spread on a 12-inch round serving plate.
Cover with the seafood sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese, shrimp, onions and tomato.
Cover and chill.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.
Serve with Triscuits or Hi-Ho's.

title: sun dill pickles
directions: You will need a gallon glass jar.

title: red velvet cake frosting
directions: Boil and stir flour and milk until thick.
Refrigerate and cool. Mix together butter, sugar, and vanilla until smooth.
Add flour mixture until smooth.

title: baked eggs
directions: Place bread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix milk, salt, mustard, meat, pepper, mushrooms and eggs.
Pour over bread. Cover with sliced cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk together in large, heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until it reaches soft ball stage or 236° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and stir in remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour into buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cool and cut.

title: raisin cake
directions: Boil raisins in 2 cups water for 5 minutes.
Cool and drain, reserving the raisin water.
Sift all dry ingredients; add sugar, oil and raisin water.
Mix well.
Add raisins and mix well.
Add nuts, if using them, and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Cut apple into slices. Place dip in a small bowl and put in the middle of a plate with apple slices around the bowl.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Roll out on floured paper and cut size desired. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt or 2 small loaf pans.
Preheat oven to 325°.

title: venison
directions: Roll venison in flour.
Fry quickly in hot skillet in small amount of oil. Fry until crispy.

title: green bean bake
directions: Place beans and garlic salt in saucepan, bring to boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Drain beans.
Mix soup and milk in a separate bowl.
In an ungreased baking dish, place alternate layers of beans, soup, pimento and cheese, ending with cheese.
Top with crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: marbled brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Soften cream cheese and butter; beat together.
Add sugar, eggs, flour and vanilla; beat until smooth and set aside.
Mix cakelike brownies as directed on package. Pour half the brownie batter into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Pour all the cream cheese mixture over the brownie layer.
Spoon remaining brownie batter in spots over the top.
Swirl the two mixtures together with a knife or spatula.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until done.
Cool.

title: brownies
directions: Mix very little; bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: texas hash
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown beef, onion and green pepper. Drain.
Pour into casserole dish.
Add salt, pepper, chili powder and rice.
Stir well.
Pour tomatoes and juice over top.
Bake for 1 hour, covered.

title: turkey wings and rice
directions: Cut up onion and pepper.
Spread one stick of butter on defrosted wings all over.
Season to your own taste.
Broil rice (with 1/2 stick butter) until done; serve separately.
Place wings in oven pan or roaster; add 2 to 3 cups water or however many you want.
Cook until brown and make sure you baste every 20 minutes until done.
Once you have tasted this, you won't want any of the rest.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix well and pour into a greased casserole.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes at 350°.
Stir 3 times while baking.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Fry bacon; reserve and crumble.
Fry hominy and onion in 2 cups bacon fat until lightly browned.
Add flour, tomatoes and season.
Cook over medium heat about 15 minutes.
Remove from heat; add crumbled bacon.
Pour into greased casserole.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: creamy green beans
directions: In saucepan, cook bacon.
Remove and crumble.
Pour off all but 1 tablespoon drippings; add onion with dill and cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat; stir now and then. Garnish with bacon.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix above until well blended.
Chill 1 hour.
Serve with fresh, cut fruit.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine with the wet mixture and mix together well.
Pour into two large greased loaf pans. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Remove from pans and place on wire rack to cool.
May be served warm or cold.
Stores well in freezer.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook meat, garlic and onion together.
Crush 1/2 bag of nacho chips and place in bottom of casserole dish.
Put half of meat on crushed chips.
Mix soups, Ro-Tel and enchilada sauce together. Put 1/2 on top of meat.
Add next half of crushed chips, rest of meat, remainder of soups and place shredded cheese on top of casserole and cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Combine warm water (115°), sugar and yeast; let stand 10 to 15 minutes.
Add eggs, margarine and salt.
Whip.
Add enough flour to handle; knead until smooth.
Test by putting your finger into dough.
If it comes out with not much sticking to it, it is kneaded enough.
Put in bowl; let rise to double.
Make into rolls.
Put in pan.
Let rise to edge of pan.
Cook in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together and press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: lemon broccoli chicken
directions: Cut 4 thin lemon slices.
Squeeze 2 teaspoons of juice from remaining lemon.
Set aside.
In skillet, in hot oil, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned.
Remove and set aside.
Spoon off fat.

title: hearty beef 'n potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes on bottom and up sides of 8 x 12-inch casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 10 minutes. Brown beef in large chunks; drain. Place beef, broccoli, 1/2 can French fried onion rings and tomatoes in potato shell.
Combine soup, milk, 1/2 cup cheese and seasonings; pour over beef mixture. Bake, covered, at 400° for 20 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onion; bake, uncovered, 2 or 3 minutes longer.

title: eggplant parmesan for two
directions: Cut eggplant crosswise into 1/2-inch slices.
Dip into beaten eggs, then in bread crumbs.
Slowly heat oil in large frypan. Saute eggplant until lightly browned, about 2 minutes each side. Drain.

title: sour cream enchilada casserole
directions: Combine water and 2 tablespoons picante sauce in a large , shallow dish.
Place tortillas in picante sauce mixture; let stand 5 minutes.
Drain.
Cook ground beef until brown; drain.
Stir in salt, pepper, cumin, chili powder, garlic powder and 1/4 cup picante sauce.
Simmer meat mixture 5 minutes.
Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat and add sour cream; stir until well blended.
Place half of tortillas in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour half of sour cream sauce over tortillas.
Spoon half of meat mixture evenly over sauce.
Sprinkle half of cheese over meat mixture.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: bailey's chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix with beater.
Add 1 (12 ounce) package of mini semi-sweet morsels.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Test with a toothpick.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: potato soup
directions: In a large sauce pan (Dutch oven) combine chicken broth, chopped onion, potatoes and dill weed.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and cover and simmer until potatoes are tender.
In another sauce pan melt the butter, blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add the milk all at once and cook and stir until thick and bubbly. Stir into potatoes and cook until heated through.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine and mix with stuffing.

Place 1 layer of stuffing in casserole dish, followed by 1 layer chicken, 1 layer celery soup, 1 layer of 1 cup broth, another layer of stuffing, 1 layer of chicken, 1 layer of cream of chicken soup and 1 layer of 1 cup broth.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: mexican pecan candy
directions: Mix sugars, milk and syrup.
Bring to boil; boil to soft boil stage.
Test by dropping a small amount of syrup in cold water. Remove from heat.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Beat until cool; drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: lane cake
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar, beating constantly until stiff peaks form.
Set aside.
Cream butter and 1 1/2 cups sugar until light and fluffy.
Add flour alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Beat well after each addition.
Fold in beaten egg whites and vanilla.
Turn into four greased and paper-lined pans (8-inch).
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.
Cool completely on wire racks.
Place one cake layer on serving plate, spread with 1/3 of cooled Grape Filling.
Top with second layer, spread with 1/3 Grape Filling.
Repeat.
Spread Seven Minute Icing over top and sides.

title: red snapper with mustard caper sauce
directions: Combine sugar, mustard and salt.
Beat into egg yolks.
Put in blender and mix, gradually adding oil 1/4 teaspoon at a time until thick and creamy.
Add lemon juice, capers, and onion.

title: old-fashioned peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in ovenproof dish.
Mix peaches and 1/2 cup sugar, if using fresh peaches.
In a separate bowl, mix sugar, milk, flour and vanilla.
Pour peaches over melted butter.
Pour batter over peaches.
Do not stir!
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: miniature cherry cheese cake
directions: Cream
cream
cheese,
eggs,
sugar
and
vanilla until smooth.
Place a wafer in midget foil cupcake liner.
Fill 3/4 full with cream cheese
mixture.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°. Take out of oven and
place
a
teaspoon of pie filling on top while warm.
Refrigerate until served.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: chicken enchilada(low-fat)
directions: Wrap tortilla around chicken and Cheddar cheese.
Place in baking dish and pour salsa over tortillas.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or microwave for 2 to 3 minutes.
Dab on sour cream. Serves 1.

title: mediterranean casserole
directions: Brown beef in butter; add onion and green pepper and cook lightly.
Blend in tomato soup, catsup, salt and pepper.
Cook, uncovered, about 8 minutes.
Stir several times.
Blend cream cheese, milk, lemon juice, garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce; mix with noodles.
Spread in a buttered glass baking dish.
Pour meat sauce over top; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: winter potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes.
Peel and dice. In saucepan, melt margarine. Add flour.
Stir in milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring all the time until thick.
Add mayo, salt, pepper and dill weed.
Pour over potatoes in baking dish.
Bake without a lid for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: billy goat cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening. Add beaten eggs.
Mix soda in warm water.
Add flour, cinnamon, dates, nuts and raisins. Drop on greased sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes on bottom rack. Bake an additional 4 minutes on middle rack, if you feel it is needed.

title: lumpia
directions: Cook ground beef or pork; drain.
Transfer beef or pork to a large pan.
Put in all ingredients.
Add garlic salt and soy sauce to taste.
Stir occasionally and cook on medium heat for 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain in colander.
Fill egg roll wrappers with ingredients, then deep fry until golden brown.

title: poppy seed coffee cake
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and set aside.
Cream margarine; add egg yolks and sugar and beat.
Sift remaining ingredients together.
Add alternately with buttermilk mixture to creamed mixture.
Beat the 4 egg whites and fold in.
Pour 1/2 batter into greased tube pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon on batter.
Add remaining batter and sprinkle other 1/2 of sugar mixture on top.
Cut through with a knife to give a marbled effect.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
(May use 2 bread pans.)

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes, peel and drain off water.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into casserole dish.

title: apple bread pudding
directions: Toast bread lightly and cut diagonally into fourths.
Arrange a single layer of bread in bottom of lightly greased 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Core and dice apples.
Spread half the apples evenly on bread.
Sprinkle raisins over apples.
Arrange remaining bread on diced apples.
Spread remaining apples over bread.
Heat milk and butter only until butter melts.
Combine eggs, sugar, spices and salt.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
Pour over bread and apples.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream sugar and Philadelphia cream cheese.
Add peanut butter; mix well.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crusts.
Chill for approximately 2 hours before serving.

title: crostini di fegatini(chicken liver croutons)
directions: *Vin Santa is a Tuscan dessert wine.

title: dump it cake
directions: Use large casserole dish and empty peaches in bottom. Add cake mix; sprinkle coconut and pecans. Melt margarine and add brown sugar to margarine; stir until sugar is dissolved. Pour over mixture and bake about 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pear conserve
directions: Cook together until thick.
Cook very slowly, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add chopped nut meats when cooking is done, as heat toughens the nut meats.
Put into jars and seal.

title: quick homemade chili
directions: Lightly brown beef in skillet, add onions and garlic.
Cook until tender; drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring occasionally.
Cook 45 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Put strawberries into pie shell.
In saucepan, mix sugar, cornstarch, salt, jello and water.
Cook until clear and thickened, stirring constantly.
Add food coloring to make syrup a deep red.
Pour syrup over the berries.
Chill.
Serve with whipped cream.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: buttermilk candy
directions: Combine sugars, soda and buttermilk in heavy 3-quart saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches soft ball stage (234°); use candy thermometer for accuracy. (I put margarine around top rim of saucepan to keep mixture from boiling over because it's pretty foamy at first before it begins to boil down.)
Add butter and vanilla.
Beat with electric mixer until candy begins to thicken and loses its gloss.
Stir in nuts. Spread mixture in well buttered 9 x 9-inch square pan. Cool and cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: sinfully rich chocolate cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until boiling.
Mix next 3, then add next ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet and spicy pork chops
directions: Brown chops in shortening.
Add onion towards end of browning time.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Combine tomatoes with ketchup and oregano leaves.
Pour over chops.
Cover and simmer 55 to 60 minutes or until chops are tender.
Baste occasionally.
Serve with rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: marinated chicken breasts
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Marinate chicken for 2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 34 to 40 minutes or grill until golden brown.
May be served hot or cold.

title: ridge row cookies(cutout)
directions: Cream first four ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients. Chill dough.
Roll and cut out.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until it is lightly browned and bubbly. Top with a few green onions. Serve with Fritos Scoops.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes into bowl and cover with buttermilk. Let stand about 5 minutes. Mix flour and salt. Take each tomato slice from milk and dredge in flour mixture. Place slices on wax paper and let stand until flour is moist. Pour enough oil in pan to cover bottom. Heat oil until ready for frying and place slices in pan. Cook until tomatoes are browned on each side. Drain and serve warm.

title: cheesy mustard cauliflower
directions: Trim
leaves
from
cauliflower.
Leaving
head
whole, remove as
much
of core as possible by cutting a cone shaped piece from bottom of head.
Combine water and salt in 4-quart Dutch oven.
Cook
over
high heat until water boils, about 4 minutes. Place
cauliflower in boiling water, stem side down. Cook
until water boils again, about 1 minute.
Reduce heat to low and cook, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes
more or until cauliflower is tender.
Drain in colander.
Return cauliflower
to Dutch oven.
Combine mayonnaise, onion,
mustard and
cheese
in
bowl;
mix to blend.
Spread mayonnaise
mixture over cauliflower.
Cook, covered, over low heat 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Transfer cauliflower to serving
platter,
using two
pancake turners.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Makes 4 servings.

title: 12 hour salad
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch or larger dish, cut up head of lettuce and shred on bottom of dish.
Mix onion, celery and peas.
Spread evenly over lettuce.

title: no bake strawberry bottom cheesecake
directions: Pour strawberry pie filling in the bottom of the pie crust. Chill in freezer while you mix the topping.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add sugar, sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Place the topping on the top of the strawberry pie filling. Ready to serve.
Store all leftovers in the refrigerator.

title: asparagus quiche
directions: Brush pie shell with small amount of beaten eggs.
Pierce bottom and sides with tines of fork.
If using metal pie pan, bake shell in preheated 450° oven until golden brown, about 5 minutes. If using pie plate, bake shell in 425° oven until golden brown, about 5 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Reduce oven temperature to 375° for metal pan or 350° for pie plate.

title: caesar salad
directions: Prepare coddled egg as follows:
Place cold egg in warm water. Heat enough water to boiling to cover egg completely.
Immerse egg in boiling water with spoon; remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 30 seconds.
Immediately cool egg in cold water to prevent further cooking; refrigerate.

title: orange dream salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and sugar together; dissolve in boiling water. Stir in ice cubes until dissolved.
Cool to egg white consistency. Fold in the nuts, pineapple and cheese, then the whipped cream. Cool in 8 x 8-inch pan until set; cut in pieces and serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix together yellow cake mix, brown sugar, butter, eggs, water and chopped pecans.
Makes a stiff batter.
Grease and flour 2 pizza pans.
Spread batter evenly.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. (Pat dough down after each 5 minutes.)
Then cool completely.
Now spread with Cool Whip, then arrange fruit on top.
(Dip all fruit in pineapple juice before putting on pizza.)
Sprinkle with pecans and coconut.
Refrigerate 2 hours before serving.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cover bottom of glass casserole dish with Bisquick and water mixture.
Be sure to spray bottom and sides of dish with Pam before spreading the dough.

title: mixed meat sauce(salsa di ragu)
directions: My Mother
Nicoletta made this Ragu sauce every Sunday. She usually served
it
with
ziti
or
rigatoni.
This sauce, however, can be
used
with any shape pasta (plain or filled). The meat is
served
after
the pasta dish, as a second course with a salad.
You
can
use
a variety of different meats and any combination works well.

title: christmas rum cake
directions: Before you start, sample rum and check for quality.
Good, isn't it?
Now, go ahead, select a large mixing bowl, measuring cup, etc. and check that rum again for quality.
It must be just right.
Try it again.
With an electric mixer, beat one cup butter in a fluffy bowl.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar and beat again.
Meanwhile, make certain that rum is of best quality.
Add eggs and dried fruit and beat until very high.
If fruit gets stuck in beaters, pry it out with a screwdriver.
Sample rum again checking for consistency. Next, sift in three cups baking powder, and add a pinch of rum, one seaspoon toda and one cut of pepper - or is it salt.
Anyway, don't fret; just test the rum again.
Zowie!
Now, sift in half pint of lemon juice, fold in chopped buttermilk and add strained nuts. Shample rum again.

title: sake-steamed clams - asari no sakamushi
directions: Dissolve 1 tablespoon of salt in 3 cups of water.
Soak the clams in the solution in a dark place for 2 to 3 hours to draw out the sand, then rinse well.
Cut the scallions into 1-inch lengths. Put the clams and Sake into a large pot and cover.
Cook over high heat for 2 to 3 minutes.
When clam shells open, sprinkle in the scallions and remove from heat.
Transfer the clams, scallions and any remaining Sake to individual serving bowls.
Serves 4.

title: mound balls
directions: Mix melted butter, milk and 1/2 tsp. vanilla.
Then add sifted sugar and coconut.
Mix well and refrigerate 1/2 hour. Take out of refrigerator and
make into balls.
Refrigerate again for 2 hours.
Melt chocolate and wax in double boiler and dip balls into chocolate mixture.
Place on wax paper to dry.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: In large soup kettle, warm oil over low heat.
Add onions, carrots, garlic, peppers and jalapenos.
Cover and cook vegetables until soft, 10 minutes.
Remove lid; add chili powder and cumin. Cook additional 2 to 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add beans, tomatoes and juice.
Increase heat to medium and bring chili to simmer.
Adjust heat to maintain a simmer and let chili cook for 20 minutes.
Stir in salt, pepper and cilantro; serve.

title: homemade tomato soup
directions: Saute in a small amount of oil the first 3 ingredients.
Add barley and flour.
Then add the tomatoes and seasonings and cook 45 minutes.
Heat the milk.
Do not boil.
Add the butter; add to the tomato mixture.
Warm the soup but do not boil.
Serve piping hot. Delicious!

title: brownies
directions: Pour into 9 x 13-inch prepared pan and bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes (it may take a little longer).

title: quick cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar together until smooth; fold in cool whip. Pour into crust and chill for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Mix butter, crackers, sugars, cream cheese and eggs.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Chill.
Add pie filling and top with whipped cream.

title: baked corn with cheese
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in a greased baking dish.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Beat egg white until stiff; beat yolks and add together. Continue beating.
Add persimmons, milk, sugar, flour, salt, butter, baking powder and soda.
Beat slightly.
Add spices and nuts.
Bake in a 9-inch square pan or rectangular.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until a knife blade comes out clean.
Top with whipped cream when cool.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Beat in sugar.
Add vanilla and bananas.
Mix well.
Add flour, cinnamon and nuts.
Pour in loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple-apricot pie
directions: Combine the fruit, cornstarch and sugar.
Pour into a pastry lined pie pan; dot with the butter and adjust the top crust. Prick crust and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 15 minutes; reduce temperature to 350° and continue baking for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Put in a buttered casserole dish. Combine eggs, mayonnaise, soup and cheese.
Pour over broccoli. Top with onions.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: wedding soup
directions: Meat Balls:
Bread crumbs, sirloin, 1 egg.
Mix together and form balls.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Melt shortening in a 4-quart saucepan, cool.
Add sugar, molasses and egg; beat well.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Mix well.
Chill 1 hour.
Make 1-inch balls and dip in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Mix cornstarch and 2 Tbsp. sugar with water and cook together until clear; then set aside.
Add salt to egg whites and whip until foamy or standing in peaks. add the mixture you set aside. Continue beating until creamy, add 6 Tbsp. sugar gradually.
Beat until very creamy.
Pile on pie and bake at 325 degrees for 30 minutes or until a golden brown.

title: icebox cheese cake
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Cool.
Whip Milnot thick and add vanilla.
Beat, then add 1 cup sugar.
Beat, then add cream cheese.
After jello is cooled, add to whipped mixture and beat until creamy.
Pour over cracker crust.
Place in refrigerator for 2 hours or overnight.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Mix juices and heat to boiling point and add to jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Add the Coca-Cola and stir well.
Place in refrigerator (partially set).
Add cherries, pineapple and nuts. Put in mold or Pyrex.
Serves 12.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Combine tomatoes, water (1/4 cup), oil and tomato paste in saucepan.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Peel eggplant.
Cut in round slices about 1/4-inch thick.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Beat eggs slightly with 2 tablespoons water.
Dip eggplant in Italian style seasoned bread crumbs, dip in egg and again in bread crumbs.

title: plum pudding
directions: Coat 6-cup mold with cooking spray.
Combine raisins, cherries, apple, lemon peel, juice and brandy.
Let stand 1 hour. Add rest of cake mixture to the fruit mixture.
Pour into mold and set mold pan in large saucepot.
Add boiling water to halfway up side of mold pan.
Cover and steam 4 hours.

title: fudge
directions: Put cheese and butter into a large bowl and melt in microwave about 1 to 2 minutes, stir often.
Mix cocoa with sugar.
When cheese is melted, add sugar mixture.
Mixing well.
Add pecans. Press on cookie sheet with wax paper on bottom.
Use wax paper on top to press into pan.
Garnish with whole pecan halves on top. Let set until cool then cut.

title: cream pralines
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan combine sugar, salt, evaporated milk and butter.
Stir over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Add pecans. Increase heat to medium; continue cooking and stirring to softball stage (234 degrees F.)
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla, then cool 5 minutes.
(Meanwhile, place a large sheet of aluminum foil on counter surface in readiness for dropping patties.)
Stir rapidly until mixture begins to thicken and coats pecans lightly.
Drop rapidly from a tablespoon onto foil.
(Use a teaspoon for small pralines.)
If candy becomes too stiff to handle easily toward the last, stir in a few drops of hot water. Let patties stand until cool and set before removing from foil.

title: oven rice
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Pour all ingredients into baking dish and cover.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: katherine hepburn's brownies
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°.
Butter and flour an 8-inch square baking pan.
Melt the chocolate with the butter in saucepan over low heat.
Remove from the heat and stir in the sugar.
Stir in the eggs and vanilla and mix until smooth.
Add the flour, salt and nuts and stir until smooth.
Pour into the prepared pan.
Bake until a toothpick inserted in the center of the brownies comes out clean, 40 minutes.
Makes 16 brownies.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: granny's pork potato casserole
directions: Place prepared potatoes in bottom on greased 9x13-inch baking dish.
Place pork chops on top.
Combine soup with milk using fork or wire whisk.
Pour evenly over chops and potatoes.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Bake covered at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
Remove covering and bake at 375 degrees for 30 minutes. Adjust cooking time down for boneless chops.
Serves 4-6.

title: dessert pizza
directions: Take Pillsbury sugar cookie mix and bake as directed on pizza pan.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar together. Spread over cookies.
Then decorate with choice of fruits, sliced strawberries, kiwi or blueberries.
Looks and tastes great!

title: berry cobbler
directions: Mix together the butter, flour, baking powder, 1/2 cup sugar, salt and milk.
Pour in casserole.
Then drain berries or peaches. Put berries or fruit over batter.
Over this, pour 1 cup of the fruit juice.
Add water, if necessary, to make 1 cup.
Then add 1 cup sugar.
Bake 45 minutes in 375° oven.

title: washboard cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Put Jell-O in hot water; stir until dissolved.
Add cranberry sauce.
Chill until it starts to jell, then add celery and nuts.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together, except cornflakes and and 1/4 cup butter. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix remaining butter (melted) and cornflakes. Sprinkle on top of mixture. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: bobby's potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and eggs until done.
Salt potatoes according to taste.
Place chopped eggs over potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: funnel cake
directions: Beat milk and egg.
Blend dry ingredients and gradually add milk to mixture.
Heat Crisco in pan.
When hot, put a little batter in funnel.
Using circular motion, drip batter into hot Crisco.
When brown on one side, turn over.
When brown on both sides, put on a plate.
With a sifter, put 10x sugar on the Funnel Cake.

title: becky's divinity
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup, water and salt. Cook, stirring, until mixture boils.
Cook over medium heat to 260° without stirring.
As temperature nears 250°, beat egg whites to stiff peaks in large mixing bowl.
Gradually pour hot syrup in a thin stream over egg whites, beating at high speed of electric mixer.
Add vanilla.
Beat 4 to 5 minutes more or until mixture holds shape.
Drop from a teaspoon onto wax paper or spread in a buttered 10 x 6 x 2-inch pan.
Cool and cut.

title: fruit sauce for pancakes or waffles
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender or food processor.
Whirl until the ingredients are smoothly blended.
Heat, if desired (to preserve vitamin C, serve cold) and serve over hot pancakes or waffles.
Makes 8 (3/4 cup) servings.
Keep a supply in the freezer and reheat it whenever you serve pancakes or waffles.

title: cheesy, spicy biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening until blended into fine crumbs.
Add the preseasoned shredded "taco" cheese.
Stir in milk.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain and flake salmon.
Add cheese, lemon juice, onion, horseradish, liquid smoke and salt.
Combine well.
Shape into a loaf.
Chill overnight.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix the ingredients and place in a 9 x 12-inch pan, which has previously been coated with a small amount of cooking oil.
Bake for 45 minutes at 450°.

title: peach fruit salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Add milk and mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: honey mustard dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients with a wire whisk. Do not use an electric mixer. Store in refrigerator. This keeps really well.

title: curried chicken-coconut soup
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in pot and bring to simmer and add chicken boiling till cooked. Add spinach and simmer until spinach wilts, about 1 minute. Add lime juice. Season soup to taste with salt and pepper. Add cilantro just before serving.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in fruits and nuts. Pour half of mixture into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill until firm. Store the rest of the jello mixture at room temperature.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Add butter, flour, vanilla, salt, and buttermilk,
Beat until well mixed.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350 degree for 55 to 60 minutes or until well done.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Peel and dice tomatoes into large saucepan; add remaining ingredients and cook on medium heat, stirring occasionally until thick like a gravy.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Crust:
Mix flour, margarine and powdered sugar.
Bake on a greased pan at 375° until brown.

title: vegetable salad
directions: To make the dressing, combine sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and cool completely.

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa.
Boil 1 minute; add salt and vanilla.
Turn off heat.
Blend in peanut butter and oats; mix well.
Drop by tablespoon onto wax paper.
Yields approximately 4 dozen.

title: triple good bars
directions: Heat oven 375°.
Grease 13 x 9 baking pan.
In med saucepan, combine first 4 ingredients.
Cook over med heat stirring constantly, until it begins to boil.
Remove from heat, cool slightly; set aside.
Beat oleo, sugar and
vanilla until fluffy. Add remaining and blend until mixed and crumbly.
Reserve 2 c. Press remaining mixture onto bottom of prepared pan.
Spread raisin mixture 1/2 inch of edge and sprinkle with remaining mixture.
Pat lightly.
Bake 25 - 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.

title: chipped beef with toast
directions: Melt butter. Add milk, salt, pepper and beef. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Add flour/water mixture and continue to stir until thickened. Serve over toast.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix sugar, salt, Crisco and hot water. Cool to lukewarm. Beat egg and mix with yeast and cold water. Stir until dissolved. Combine the two mixtures. Mix well. Beat in about 4 1/2 cups of flour. Knead in bowl with hands. Add rest of flour; work real good with hands. Grease top of dough. Cover with cloth. Let rise in warm (not hot) place until double in size. Then oil a large bowl and put dough in. Turn to cover all over with oil. Cover tightly and put in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: excellent banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter, sugar, eggs and bananas and beat until blended.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, cornstarch and salt, and add alternately with sour cream to banana mixture.
Blend until smooth.
Add nuts.
Bake in a greased, floured pan, large loaf 55 minutes; 2 small loaves, 45 minutes.

title: ann's key lime cake
directions: Mix the beaten eggs and the next 4 ingredients with the yellow cake mix.
Beat 2 minutes on high speed.
Spray Bundt pan and pour in the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Top with powdered sugar and 1/3 cup of squeezed Key limes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: On a pizza
pan, roll out cookie dough evenly into a circle. Bake as directed until light golden color.
In a bowl, mix together the cream cheese and marshmallow cream until well mixed and smooth (mixer works great).
Spread over cooled cookie crust and refrigerate.
Just before serving, decorate with fruit and cut like a pizza with a pizza cutter.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients except bacon.
Pour in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Place bacon on top of beans.
Bake 30 minutes, covered, at 350°.
Uncover; bake until bacon is done.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except bacon.
Lay bacon on top of beans and bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: italian meat loaves
directions: Put all ingredients into bowl, mix thoroughly with hands. Mold into 3 loaves.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Garnish with parsley.

title: blueberry bread
directions: Beat egg and stir in sugar, oil and juice.
Sift flour, baking powder and soda; mix well.
Fold in nuts and berries.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: meg's fried chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper and soak in buttermilk overnight.
Add all ingredients in a large bowl and then roll chicken in flour mixture one piece at a time until covered.
Heat canola oil in skillet to 350°.
Fry until golden brown, approximately 15 minutes on each side.

title: kentucky omelette
directions: Combine mushrooms, onion and celery.
Saute in butter until celery is tender-crisp.
Add sour cream and set aside.
Beat eggs and milk and pour half into skillet.
Add 1/4 cup ham and spread with half of filling.
When eggs are firmly set, fold in half and top with cheese slice.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Makes 2 large omelettes.

title: strawberry pretzel jello salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and 3 teaspoons sugar. Spread in a 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 400° for 8 minutes (don't overbake).

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Use 2 to 3 teaspoons per cup of water.

title: moc pecan pie
directions: Thaw pie shell, prick with fork.
Mix all other ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into shell.
Bake 350° for 1 hour or until set. *Note - this does not contain the fat that pecan pie has but is a good substitute.
Serve with low fat whipped topping.

title: quick chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Add Coke and ketchup.
Bake for approximately 1 hour at 400°.
The liquid will make a sauce.

title: white jello
directions: Dissolve gelatine in cold water.
Mix pineapple and sugar together in saucepan.
Add gelatine mixture and bring to a boil. Cool.
Cream the cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme together.
Add gelatine mixture.
Refrigerate until it starts to set.
Add Cool Whip to chilled mixtures.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over top. Refrigerate until firm.

title: mom's homemade ice cream
directions: For 2 quarts, reduce all by half; for 6 quarts, increase by half.

title: 24 hour slaw
directions: Boil 2nd ingredients for 3 minutes and pour over vegetable mixture.
Keep in refrigerator for 24 hours before serving.

title: butter beans
directions: Saute onions in oil until tender.
Blend in flour then add tomatoes; bring to boil.
Cook stirring until thickened.
Add milk, beans, Worcestershire sauce, pepper, spike and basil.
Heat thoroughly.

title: quick garlic-cheese biscuits
directions: Mix the baking mix, milk and cheese until a soft dough forms; beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake about 10 minutes at 450° or until lightly browned.
Mix butter, garlic powder and parsley flakes; brush over warm biscuits before removing from cookie sheet.
Serve warm.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Cut beef into 1/8-inch thick strips.
Combine soy sauce, garlic and ginger.
Add beef.
Toss and set aside.
Heat oil in large frying pan or wok.
Add beef and toss over high heat until browned.
Taste meat; if not tender, cover and simmer for about 30 minutes over low heat.
Turn heat up and add vegetables.
Toss until vegetables are tender-crisp (about 10 minutes).
Mix cornstarch and water.
Add to pan.
Stir and cook until thickened.
Add tomatoes and heat through.
Serves 4.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix together flour, powdered sugar and melted butter.
Pat in a
9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 20 minutes.
Beat eggs.
Mix beaten eggs with sugar, lemon juice and baking powder.
Pour over cooked dough and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top when done.
Let cool and cut.

title: golden fried fish
directions: Combine flour, salt, oil and water; blend well.
Beat egg white until soft peak forms.
Fold into flour mixture.
Dip both sides of fish in batter.
Fry fish in 1/2 inch of oil heated to 370° until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: honey glazed new potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into quarters.
In a large saucepan, cover potatoes with salted water, bring to a boil and cook potatoes until tender; drain.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli using package instructions; drain.
Melt butter; blend in flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.

title: strawberries
directions: Mix ingredients and chill.
Then shape like strawberries. Roll in red sugar.
Make a stem out of slivered almonds dyed green.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Mix and add margarine and nuts last.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until set good.

title: baked roast beef
directions: Mix lemon juice, mushroom soup and Worcestershire sauce. Sprinkle roast with salt, pepper and onion powder.
Pour mixture over roast in Dutch oven.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours.
Remove roast and add 1 package beef gravy mix with 1 cup water to liquid that is left in Dutch oven.
Serve over roast.

title: party mix
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in seasoned salt until dissolved.
Add Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over cereal and nuts.
Toss until well coated.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring often.
Store in airtight container.
Very good.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Brown your beef and onion and drain the grease; combine the other ingredients.
Put the mixture into a casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: microwave marshmallow treats
directions: Microwave margarine in a large mixing bowl for 1 minute until margarine is melted.
Add marshmallows and toss until well coated. Microwave 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth
when stirred, stirring after 45 seconds.
Immediately add the cereal and mix thoroughly. Press into a 9 x 13-inch greased baking pan.
Allow to cool and cut into bars.

title: orange roughy with creamy mushroom sauce
directions: Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Place over medium heat until hot.
Add next three ingredients, saute 3 minutes and set aside.
Let cool.

title: hearty bean soup
directions: Cook bacon in large heavy saucepan until crisp.
Drain and set aside.
Leave a small amount of drippings in pan (about 1 tablespoon) and add green pepper, onion, carrot and garlic.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes which have been mashed or cut into small pieces.
Stir in beans, salt, pepper and sugar.
Simmer 30 minutes to one hour.
Add crumbled bacon and parsley flakes.
Cook 5 minutes more.
Serve in warmed soup bowls.
This is delicious with fried cornbread.

title: creamy stuffed celery
directions: Separate celery into ribs; clean.
Combine cream cheese, sour cream and butter until smooth.
Add capers, anchovy paste, onion, mustard, salt, pepper and paprika.
Fill stalks with mixture. Sprinkle with paprika before serving.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate fudge(microwave candy)
directions: Optional:
May also add 8 ounces of Hershey's dark chocolate bar for more intense chocolate taste.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into 2 pie shells.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Add broccoli until separated.
Add onion and saute for 5 minutes.
Stir cooked rice.
Mix Cheez Whiz, soup and milk.
Add all ingredients and cook for 25 minutes at 400°.

title: hot pickles
directions: Wash and drain cucumbers; slice into spears.
In quart jar, put garlic, dil seed, pepper, alum, dill and cucumbers.
Boil water, vinegar and salt together.
Pour into each jar and seal.

title: cherry salad
directions: Bring cherries (juice and cherries) to boil; add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat; stir in jello.
Add drained pineapple and nuts or celery.
Place in mold for at least 4 hours.

title: applesauce raisin cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and nuts in a bowl.
Plump raisins by placing in hot water for 10 minutes and drain off water.
Melt margarine in a saucepan and heat until bubbling.
Add applesauce and baking soda.
Remove from heat. Combine wet and dry mixtures.
Fill a greased pan 3/4 full and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until firm on top.
Frost, if desired, when cool.

title: monkey bread
directions: Shake sugars and cinnamon in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut biscuits into 4 quarters.
Toss into casserole dish and shake.
Pour melted butter over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain spinach. Add dry onion soup and sour cream.
Blend.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: lemon crumbles
directions: Prepare lemon pie filling; set to cool.
Mix remaining ingredients together to make crumbs.
Save 1 cup of crumb mixture for topping.
Grease a pan with butter.
Pack crumb mixture in pan.
Add lemon pie filling and sprinkle the remaining 1 cup of crumb mixture on top.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: easy macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: blueberry-oat bran muffins
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
Coat a 12-cup muffin tin with vegetable cooking spray or line with paper muffin cups.
In a large mixing bowl, gently mix the dry ingredients with blueberries to prevent the blueberries from sinking into the batter by coating them.

title: grilled turkey steaks
directions: Mix marinade in large Ziploc bag.
Buy a turkey breast.
Have the butcher cut it in half, then cut crosswise in 1 to 1 1/2-inch slices.
Marinate in Ziploc bags overnight.
You may need 2 bags. Grill until done.

title: unleaded banana dessert
directions: In a mixing bowl, prepare instant pudding with milk according to package directions. Add sliced bananas and chill. Serve with cookies.

title: easy spaghetti and cheese
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over top of spaghetti.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until cheese is melted.
Cut and serve with warmed sauce and garlic bread.
Serves 8.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Soak beans overnight; discard any that float to top.
Bring to boil; simmer until tender.
Combine salt, sugar, vinegar and oil; mix well.
Add vegetables; mix gently.
Chill at least 1 hour. Pour off liquid.
Gently stir in eggs before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: yummie cheese balls
directions: Soften cheese.
Add pineapple, onion, pepper, Lawry's seasoned salt and 1 cup of nuts.
Chill and roll in remaining nuts.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 1 very large or 2 small balls.

title: jellied vegetable salad
directions: Pour boiling water over Jell-O. Add vinegar and salt. When slightly thickened, fold in finely shredded vegetables. Serve on lettuce leaf with dressing.

title: brunch puff
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay 1/2 of the bread on the bottom of pan.
Use 1/2 of bacon, cheese and onion spread evenly over bread. Repeat.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper and pour over top.
Let sit overnight in fridge.
Put in a cold oven if glass pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa together in saucepan.
Stir until mixed well. Add milk and cook until thick.

title: oreo pie
directions: Crumble Oreo cookies in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with the softened ice cream.
Dribble chocolate syrup over ice cream.
Top with Cool Whip.
Add a few Oreo crumbs on top to decorate.
Freeze.
Keep frozen until ready to serve.

title: cheese blintzes
directions: Roll each slice of bread flat with rolling pin.
Spread cream cheese, egg and sugar mixture.
Roll in melted butter.
Roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Freeze overnight.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients; make into patty forms and fry in frying pan.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix lightly and chill real good.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Melt together 2 sticks margarine and 1/2 cup cocoa.
Add sugar and eggs, beaten in one at a time, salt, nuts and flour.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes at 350°.
After baking, sprinkle with marshmallows.
Make topping with remaining ingredients; mix and spread on top of marshmallows.

title: sorghum cake
directions: Mix together and bake in one pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry lovers' muffins
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and spices. Set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, combine Kellogg's 40% Bran Flakes cereal and milk.
Let stand 2 minutes or until cereal is softened. Add egg whites and oil; beat well. Add dry ingredients, stirring only until combined. Gently stir in blueberries.
Portion batter evenly into 12 lightly greased 2 1/2-inch muffin pan cups. Bake in a 400° oven about 23 minutes or until light golden brown. Serve hot.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook and cut up chicken breasts.
Cut up margarine and put on top of chicken.
Combine chicken broth and cream of chicken soup. Pour over chicken.
Mix Bisquick and milk.
Pour over chicken.
May add vegetables if you wish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: In mixer bowl beat together eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin until light and fluffy.
Presift flour, then measure and sift your dry ingredients together:
baking powder, cinnamon, salt and soda.
Add to pumpkin mixture and mix thoroughly.
Spread batter in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 or 35 minutes, then cool.

title: chocolate peanut butter fudge
directions: Blend sugar, cocoa and milk in large heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat with wooden spoon until thick.
Pour onto buttered plate.
Let cool.

title: pink banana pancakes
directions: *Use pancake mix recipe for 12 to 16 pancakes.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Mix in large bowl and set aside the cinnamon, salt and sugar. Slightly beat one egg white and 1 tablespoon of water and coat pecan halves with egg mixture.
Add pecans to sugar mixture and coat thoroughly.
Bake on Pam sprayed baking sheet at 225° for 45 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs.
Add apples, raisins, coconut and nuts; stir thoroughly.
Add soda, salt, cinnamon and vanilla. Stir in flour until batter is very stiff.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
Cake may be iced with creamy icing, if desired.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and confectioners sugar together; spread over graham crust.
Spread nuts over cream cheese mixture, then whipping cream and cherries next.
Chill.
Makes 2 pies.

title: pork with chives
directions: Brown pork chops in an electric skillet.
Allow pork chops to cook thoroughly and then remove them from the pan.
Add sherry to drippings.
Bring mixture to a boil, then add the cream cheese. Stir cream cheese until melted, then add chives.
Allow mixture to cook approximately 10 minutes.
Spoon mixture onto pork and serve.

title: foil stew
directions: Place patties on heavy duty broiling foil.
Add potato, carrot, onion, salt and pepper to taste.

title: steak casserole
directions: Roll steak in salt, pepper and flour.
Brown each side quickly in oil.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and eggs well.
Add milk and margarine.
Mix well with mixer.
Pour into pie shells.
Sprinkle with a little nutmeg.
Bake on lower rack at 350° until brown on top, about 45 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make paste with food coloring and cocoa.
Add to mixture.
Combine salt and flour and add to mixture along with buttermilk and vanilla.
Alternately add soda and vinegar; don't beat, just blend.
Stir in butter flavoring.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans or a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool about 10 minutes and split layers to make 4.
Frost.

title: lasagna roll-ups
directions: Cook lasagna noodles per package instructions; drain.
In medium bowl, mix egg, Ricotta cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Spread cheese mixture equally on lasagna strips.
Roll up each strip. Spread 1 cup sauce on bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Arrange lasagna rolls, seam side down.
Pour remaining sauce over rolls, top with Mozzarella cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix all vegetables in a bowl.
Mix the vinegar, sugar, oil, salt and paprika
and pour into vegetable mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Keeps well.

title: luscious pizza rolls
directions: Make your favorite roll recipe.
Meanwhile, grate cheese and set aside.
Then, brown hamburger.
Add onion and saute 5 minutes. Add the remaining ingredients; stir together and simmer.
Roll dough into 2 rectangles, 1/4-inch thick.
Spread with cooled hamburger mixture and sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Roll up and slice.
Let rise and then bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. They freeze well.
(Optional:
serve hot, topped with a sauce, cream of mushroom soup with peas added.)

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Blend sugar and flour in bowl.
Add eggs, melted margarine and vanilla and stir until well mixed.
Stir in chocolate chips, pecans and coconut.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until firm.
Allow to cool before cutting.

title: salmon stew
directions: Cook potatoes and onions until well done.
Do not drain.
Add can of tomatoes, seasoned with fried out meat grease.
Add corn, salmon and tomato soup.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and when it stops boiling, add can of cream, stirring constantly.
Serve with cornbread or crackers.

title: cheese-sprinkled chili
directions: In large skillet, cook ground chuck and onion until brown; add flour, salt, pepper and water, stirring to thicken.
Add soup, kidney beans and chili.
Serve with sprinkled-on grated Cheddar. May be served with corn bread or saltines.
Recipe doubles easily.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: In a large, nonstick skillet, fry sausage pieces over moderately high heat for 6 to 7 minutes until lightly browned. Transfer sausage to a large bowl and pour off fat from skillet. In the same skillet, heat oil over moderate heat; add garlic, onion and carrot and cook 2 to 3 minutes, stirring occasionally until onion is soft but not brown.
Add vegetable mixture to sausage; add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pat mixture into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Let stand in pan 10 minutes before serving or serve cold.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix sour cream, soup and chilies. Soften tortillas in oil; don't overcook.
Spread 1 to 2 tablespoons of soup mixture on tortillas. Add 1 tablespoon chicken, onion and cheeses.
Roll and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. After all tortillas are rolled in pan, then cover with remaining soup, cheeses and onion, in that order.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: coffee cup
directions: Beat together margarine and sugar until creamy.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Beat until light and creamy.
Add flour and blend until smooth.
Pour 3/4 batter into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spoon filling on top. Put remaining batter on top and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until golden brown.
Cool.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Combine all ingredients together well; do not beat.
Grease pan, 13 x 9-inch.
Pour in batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Mix well and pour onto cookie sheet with sides.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown.
Frost lightly with thin white glaze (powdered sugar, margarine and milk).
Cut into bars.

title: devil's delight(a nice change from baked beans)
directions: Mix ingredients well and place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: crab cakes or crab casserole
directions: Combine and make cakes or casserole.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Combine all ingredients except tortillas.
Arrange tortillas on flat surface.
Divide cheese mixture evenly and spread to edges of each tortilla.
Roll tortillas tightly.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet, seam side down.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Slice off 2 ends.
Slice through remaining roll every half-inch.
Serve with extra salsa for dipping.
Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: stirring fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add one egg at a time and beat well. Add flour, flavoring and spice.
Beat well.
Add fruits and nuts which are chopped coarsely.
Pour into a large greased pan and bake in 375° oven for 15 minutes.
Stir; repeat 3 times.
Have tube cake pan greased and lined with brown paper.
Pack hot cake mix in it and bake for 15 minutes longer.
Let stand in pan about 15 minutes before turning out.

title: easy sausage balls
directions: Crumble the sausage and mix with cheese.
Add biscuit mix, one cup at a time.
Form into small balls (about one inch in diameter) and place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a preheated 350° to 375° oven until light brown (13 to 15 minutes).
Cooking may take a few extra minutes if balls are frozen.
Serve warm.
Makes about seven dozen.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: In 1 quart bowl mix tuna or chicken with celery, green onion, garlic salt, salt, pepper, salad elegance and mayonnaise until mixture is stiff.
Cut each tomato vertically into eighths.
Put 2 Tbsp. tuna or chicken mixture in middle of each tomato.
Top with dried parsley flakes and/or additional salad elegance.
Serve immediately.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix cheese (grated) and butter together.
Add flour and Rice Krispies.
Mix with hands and form into balls.
Press flat with a fork and put in an ungreased sheet pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: coney island sauce
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Add all other ingredients. Simmer 1 hour.

title: raspberry juice
directions: Wash, clean and crush raspberries.
Place in Earthenware bowl or crock and let ferment 5 days.
Drain through a cheesecloth. Measure the liquid and take double that amount of sugar.
Cook sugar with a little water to make syrupy.
Add juice to sugar; cook 15 minutes.
While the juice is cooking, continue to clear the top of the juice with a spoon.
While still warm, pour into bottles and cap securely.
Good over ice cream and as a refreshing healthy beverage.
Can use with soda water.

title: low-fat oven fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to
Melt butter or margarine in rectangular pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Mix baking mix, paprika, salt and pepper. Coat chicken.
Place
in pan.
Bake 35 minutes, turn and bake 15 minutes or until done.

title: vanilla sugar cookies
directions: Beat sugars, butter and oil until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Chill overnight or for a few hours.
Roll into small balls.
Place 3 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until brown.
You can flatten and spread beaten egg whites on and sprinkle with white or colored sugar.

title: grandpa's sauerbraten
directions: Sprinkle beef with salt and pepper.
Place in an earthen dish (do not use metal).
Add bay leaves, peppercorns, cloves, vinegar and enough water to cover.
Let stand 5 days in refrigerator. Turn daily.
Brown meat and add 2 cups of the spiced vinegar mixture, carrots and onions.
Cover and cook on stove until tender, about 3 hours.
For gravy, dissolve gingersnaps in water and use to thicken mixture.
Serve with red cabbage.

title: sour cream frosting
directions: Beat egg yolks,
add cream, sugar, cornstarch and nuts. Cook in a
double
boiler,
stirring
constantly
until thick, before spreading on cake let frosting cool.

title: chicken breasts parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray cookie sheet with nonstick spray. On large plate, combine cheese, crumbs and spices.
Dip chicken pieces in melted margarine or Butter Buds, then in bread crumbs. Place on cookie sheet and bake 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.

title: prime rib
directions: Prime rib must be served medium to rare.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together except ginger ale.
When ready to serve, add ice cold ginger ale.

title: bailey's irish cream
directions: Mix all together and put in refrigerator.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Combine green pepper, celery and onion.
Add enough grease to microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Mix all ingredients and place in a greased 2-quart shallow casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: five-hour stew
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Prepare ingredients.
Mix together and place in ovenproof, covered casserole or Dutch oven.
Bake at 300° for 5 hours.
Do not uncover or stir while cooking.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar; sift dry ingredients and add them with milk and eggs.
Cook in 350° oven about 30 minutes.

title: creamy cranberry shake
directions: Place 1/2 of milk and 1/2 of cream cheese in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Add 1/2 of ice cream and 1/2 of cranberry sauce. Blend until combined.
Scrape down sides of blender container if needed.
Pour into large pitcher.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Pour into pitcher and stir.
Serve immediately. Makes 7 (8 oz.) servings.

title: picante sauce
directions: Mix together and simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until thick.
Pour in jars and seal.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix crumbled sausage, grated cheese and Bisquick.
Add enough milk to let mixture form a ball.
Mix with hands.
Roll into balls and store in plastic bag.
For best results, freeze before cooking.
Put frozen balls on ungreased cookie sheet and bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Spread butter on all 15 slices of bread; crumble each slice. Put a layer of bread in bottom of 8-quart baking dish.
Next, shred cheese.
Put a layer of cheese on top of bread.
Put a bread layer, then cheese layer until you come to top.
Put the Mozzarella cheese on top.
Pour milk over top.
Beat eggs and pour over top. Add salt and pepper to your taste.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until brown.

title: spicy pinto beans
directions: If using dried pintos, pick over and wash beans.
Soak overnight in water to cover.
Cook 1 hour or until tender. Reserve 1 cup liquid from cooking.
If using canned pintos, do not drain.
Cut chorizo into bite-sized pieces; add to pinto beans and cook over medium heat for 30 minutes.
Serve with fajitas.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13 x 2 inch baking dish.
Spread chicken over margarine.
Sprinkle Veg-All over chicken.
Mix broth with soup and pour over Veg-All.
Mix milk with Bisquick and pour over all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hearty vegetable stew
directions: In a 4 1/2-quart pot, combine all ingredients.
After bringing mixture to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, covered, about 30 to 45 minutes or until lentils are tender.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender; remove from bone.
Tear in small bite size pieces.
In separate bowl, mix soups and sour cream.
Add chicken.
Pour mixture in buttered casserole dish.
Top with crumbled Ritz crackers.
Use plenty of crackers.
Pour 1/4 to 1/2 cup melted butter on top of crackers.
Bake at 375° until crackers are brown.

title: banana-nut pudding
directions: In microwave dish, melt peanut butter.
Stir in yogurt and add banana.
Stir once more.
Divide into 2 dessert dishes. Yield: 2 servings.

title: sugar coated peanuts
directions: Stir peanuts into water and sugar.
Cook until all water is gone.
Pour onto cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 20 minutes, stirring 3 times.

title: caramel walnut tart
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, ground walnuts and sugar in a medium bowl.
Cut in 6 tablespoons cold butter with a pastry blender until coarse crumbs form.
Press dough evenly onto bottom and up side of an 11-inch tart pan with removable bottom. Bake until lightly browned, about 20 minutes.
Remove from oven. Reduce oven temperature to 350°.

title: sugarless, eggless applesauce cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add applesauce, oil and raisins.
Blend in nuts.
Pour in 2 loaf pans or 1 large tube pan, greased.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.
Test with toothpick.

title: hamburg chow mein
directions: In large skillet, fry hamburg and onion until meat is light brown.
Add salt, pepper, celery, onion and water.
Bring to a boil and cover.
Let simmer for 20 minutes.
Add rinsed bean sprouts and heat.
In separate bowl, combine 2 tablespoons water, soy sauce, sugar and gravy.
Add to meat and stir until thickened.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream 1 pound butter.
Add sugar, vanilla and baking powder. Slowly mix in flour.
Knead for 5 minutes.
Cut into shapes.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil.
Mix together remaining ingredients, then add boiled mixture and stir.
Pour on a greased and floured jelly roll sheet (cookie sheet with sides).
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Crumble pan of corn bread into a bowl.
Cover with rest of ingredients; put in just enough real mayonnaise to make it moist.

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: Beat cream cheese; add strawberries and liquid.
Add sugar and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into 8-inch graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place butter in 13 x 9-inch pan and place in oven to melt butter.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter and press down with a fork.
Sprinkle coconut, then add chocolate chips, and then pecans.
Drizzle surface with condensed milk. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Let cool, then cut.
Makes 30 bars.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding mix in Cool Whip.
Add crushed pineapple, well drained.
Add marshmallows and pecan pieces.
Stir well. Refrigerate at least four hours before serving.

title: whipped butter
directions: Put the butter or margarine in small bowl until softened. Beat at low speed until smooth, then beat on high speed until light and fluffy.

title: easy chicken
directions: Place chicken in buttered baking dish.
Top with rice and spread around.
Cover with mushroom soup and dry onion soup and spread around.
Add seasoning (salt, pepper, paprika).
Add the 1 cup of water.
Cover and bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover and bake another 1/2 hour.

title: orange salad
directions: Stir pudding, gelatin and hot water together and boil, stirring constantly until it thickens.
Completely cool.
Add pineapple with juice and drained oranges.
Fold in whipped cream and chill about 3 hours.
Excellent holiday salad.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat margarine and Crisco together until fluffy. Beat in sugars.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Stir in vanilla.
Gradually sift in flour, baking soda and salt. Add chocolate chips and nuts by hand. Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: beef rouladen
directions: Season meat slices.
Add 1/4 of bacon and onion on top of each meat slice and roll up jelly-roll style.
Wrap with thread to hold together.
Brown in hot oil all around, then add water to pan and simmer until meat is tender (may have to add additional water). Remove rouladen carefully from pot and thicken gravy with flour or cornstarch.
Add more spices if needed.
Pour gravy over rouladen (after removing thread carefully).
Heat thoroughly and serve with noodles and vegetables.
Serves 4.

title: california bean salad
directions: Put beans in large bowl.
Add Italian dressing mix.
Add onion, thinly sliced and separated into rings.
Add pimientos. Into small bowl, put oil and enough vinegar to cover beans.
Add sugar to taste.
Pour over bean mixture.
Toss lightly.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
To add texture, add 1/2 cup of drained garbanzo beans.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in 325 degree oven for 45 minutes.

title: japanese chicken
directions: Mix soy sauce, ketchup, sherry and garlic.
Place in a large bowl.
Place chicken in marinade.
Marinate in refrigerator for 1 1/2 hours, turning the chicken occasionally.
Transfer chicken to baking dish and bake for 45 minutes at 350° or until chicken is cooked through.
Serves 4.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole dish and bake 1 hour at 350°, uncovered.
Stir after 30 minutes.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Mix in order given and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Rinse the chicken and coat with flour.
Cook in a large skillet with oil over medium heat, turning occasionally, until lightly browned.
Add bell pepper and cook about 1 minute.
Add mushrooms and pour spaghetti sauce over chicken.
Cover and simmer 25-35 minutes or until chicken is done.
Sprinkle with cheese before serving.

title: chow mein
directions: Saut chicken or shrimp until done.
Remove and saut celery and onion.
Then add bean sprouts, bamboo shoots and water chestnuts.
When celery and onions are half-tender, add liquid from canned vegetables to cornstarch and pour in.
Add soy sauce to taste.
Return chicken or shrimp to pot and cook until thickened.
Serve over rice.
Top with browned chow mein noodles. Serves 6 to 8.

title: onion and potato casserole
directions: Season meat and brown in oil.
Remove any excess fat.
Peel and slice potatoes thinly.
Make alternate layers of potatoes, onions and meat.
Pour mushroom soup on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cover casserole with foil and remove the foil after 30 minutes.
Continue baking for 15 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: sweet potato pie 2
directions: In a large bowl, mash the yams to remove strings.
Add egg, milk, sugar, vanilla, salt, ginger, nutmeg and cinnamon to bowl and beat until smooth.
Prick holes in crust.
Pour mixture into prepared crust and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center of pie comes out clean.
Serves 8.

title: hello dollies
directions: Crush crackers and add melted butter.
Spread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: xeno snax for earthlings(child-approved)
directions: Mix powdered sugar with a small amount of milk to make frosting of a good consistency for spreading.
Add flavoring if desired.
You will have to estimate amounts based on how many graham crackers you want to use.
Spread graham crackers with frosting and make alien designs on top with raisins, nuts or candies.
These should be eaten upside down, accompanied by a glass of milk.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown the ground beef and onion.
Add the rest of the ingredients and cook until noodles and vegetables are done.

title: one pot pork chop supper
directions: In a large skillet, brown chops. Pour off fat. Split the carrots lengthwise and cut in 2-inch pieces. Add all the ingredients to the pork chops. Cover and simmer 45 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Put chicken in casserole dish.
Pour broth over chicken. Spread soup over chicken and broth.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add mixed vegetables.
Mix melted butter, flour and milk together and pour over mixture evenly.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: hot or cold string bean salad
directions: Mince garlic; slice onion into thin strips.
Put string beans, garlic, onion and parsley in a shallow baking dish.
Toss until well mixed.
Sprinkle with grated cheese, bread crumbs and shredded Mozzarella.
Pour in vinegar and oil or plain vinegar (balsamic is best, red wine is also acceptable).
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° approximately 20 minutes; stir.
Uncover and bake another 10 to 12 minutes, until onion and beans are tender.
Toss with more bread crumbs if too fluid.
May be served hot or cold.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients (except egg whites and pie crust) and cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Whip egg whites to make a meringue then put on top of the pie.

title: electric frypan fudge
directions: Put sugar, butter, salt and milk in frypan and let come to a boil. Let boil for 4 minutes at 280°, then add chips, walnuts, vanilla and marshmallows.
After all have melted, pour onto a buttered plate and let cool.

title: st. nick cookies no. 2("a dutch favorite at christmastime")
directions: Cream shortenings and sugar; blend in sour cream.
Sift dry ingredients and add.
Form into long roll and chill in refrigerator.
Slice and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: hearty burger joes
directions: Brown
ground
beef in skillet along with celery; remove excess fat.
Add rest of ingredients, except cheese.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in cheese and serve on rolls.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken breasts. Place in bottom of casserole. Top with asparagus spears. Melt butter and saute onion until onion is clear. Add Cheddar cheese and melt in butter and onion, stirring all the time. Add evaporated milk and mushroom soup. Add soy sauce and hot sauce. Mix well and pour over chicken and asparagus. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: sweet sour chicken
directions: Mix dressing, soup mix and peach preserves.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Add salt and pepper.
Add pineapple and green pepper on top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°, uncovered.
Serve with rice.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Generously butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Arrange bread cubes in dish and sprinkle with cheese.
Beat eggs, milk, dry mustard, salt, dash of fresh ground pepper and onion powder together and pour over cheese and bread.
Sprinkle with bacon, mushrooms and tomato.
Cover and chill up to 24 hours.
Bake at 325°, uncovered, until set (about 1 hour).
Tent with foil if top begins to overbrown.

title: mom's apple cake
directions: Cut apples (peeled).
Pour sugar over apples and refrigerate 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix oil, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, soda and salt and mix well.
Add all of this to apples and mix well.
Add nuts now.
Grease and flour pans.
Bake in sheet pan for 1 hour or bake in large tube pan 60 to 70 minutes.

title: sesame meatballs
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except onions and sesame seed; blend well.
Shape into 16 to 24 meatballs with an onion in the center of each; coat with sesame seed.
Place on a broiler pan in the oven at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes until browned and desired doneness.
You can use an almond or green olive in place of the onion.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Skin chicken breasts.
Season with lemon pepper, salt and paprika.
Mix sour cream with mayonnaise.
Spread on both sides of chicken breasts.
Sprinkle crushed Cheese Nips on chicken and pour melted oleo over them.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender, uncovered.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Saute onion, green onions and celery in the stick of butter. Add soups and Ro-Tel tomatoes to the sauteed onion mix and simmer 20 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook another 15 minutes.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Melt margarine and cocoa in skillet.
Mix together eggs, sugar, flour and salt.
Add cocoa mixture.
Mix well.
Add pecans. Pour into greased 10 x 14-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes.
Place marshmallows close together on cake.
Place in oven until marshmallows soften.
Remove from oven and press marshmallows down with fingertips.
Let cake cool completely before icing.

title: zucchini
directions: Slice zucchini and onion into rings.
Saute in margarine for about 8 minutes, until they get a little soft.
Place in baking dish and add tomato sauce.
Sprinkle with oregano, Parmesan cheese and cracker crumbs.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: velvet cream
directions: Blenderize cookies to crumbs.
Add butter, melted.
Put into pie tin and press to sides for a crust.
Put aside.

title: nancy sherman's welsh currant cakes
directions: Mix together the flour, sugar, baking powder and nutmeg.
Cut the Crisco and margarine in thoroughly, using pastry cutter or 2 knives.
Stir in the currants.
Beat together the eggs and milk; add milk mixture to flour mixture.
Stir with fork until dough forms.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness on lightly floured surface. Cut into 3-inch circles.
(Or, divide dough into 12 parts; pat or roll out each piece to 1/4-inch thickness.)
Bake on electric skillet set at 350°, or use heavy frying pan or griddle on low or a little above.
Pan should be hot enough to sizzle water.
Bake until set and lightly browned on bottom.
Turn like a hot cake; bake until other side is slightly browned and cake is cooked through (takes 5 to 8 minutes per side).
Cool on rack.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: snowy ice cream
directions: Blend the ingredients well and add clean, fresh snow until absorbed and it looks like ice cream.
(Tastes like frozen custard.)

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Grease 9 x 12-inch Pyrex dish. Crush potato chips and use half of them to line dish. Add chicken mixture and cover with other half of crushed chips. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: bacon broccoli salad
directions: Cook sugar, water, vinegar and flour over medium heat until clear.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Cool, then add mustard and mayonnaise.
Pour over broccoli, onion and bacon just before serving.

title: garden minestrone
directions: In a 6-quart kettle, saute garlic and onion until soft.
Add stock, beans and their liquid, vegetables, basil, oregano and rosemary; bring to simmering.
Reduce heat; cover and cook for 30 minutes.
Stir in tomato paste and macaroni and continue simmering for 15 minutes or until macaroni is tender.
Add cabbage and cook, covered, about 5 more minutes.
Season with salt and pepper and serve.

title: sausage strata
directions: Cook sausage and pour off grease.
Cube bread and place in bottom of greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover bread with a layer of sausage and a layer of cheese.
Use remaining sausage and cheese to make two more layers.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper together.
Pour over ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Good to make ahead and refrigerate overnight before cooking.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers.
Good hot or cold.

title: cavotini
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and brown in skillet.
Cook and drain noodles.
Mix all ingredients (except cheese).
Place mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cheese.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 3 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Use any kind of berry or canned fruit.
If fruit is sweetened, use less sugar; if apples are used, bring to a boil before putting in cobbler.

title: chipped beef tart
directions: Saute onion in butter until lightly browned.
Mix remaining ingredients except rolls.

title: butternut squash soup
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Cook and simmer on low heat until tender.
Puree in blender; take out and strain.
In new pan, melt butter; add flour all at once.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add cream, salt and white pepper.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook on low heat.
If too thick, add some extra cream.

title: shrimp curry
directions: Simmer all but shrimp 5 minutes.
Add shrimp and heat.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: sweet and spicy barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium size saucepan.
