Heat over medium-high heat and cook for 15 minutes, stirring frequently. Makes about 2 1/2 cups sauce.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat together for 3 or 4 minutes the eggs, sugar, buttermilk, margarine and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 375° until knife inserted into filling comes out clean.
This takes about 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: crock-pot pizza
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Brown and drain ground beef.
Add spaghetti sauce to ground beef.
Layer noodles, then ground beef and sauce.
Layer pepperoni, mushrooms.
Sprinkle cheeses over top.
May repeat layers, if desired.
Cook until cheese melts.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour in buttered baking dish.
Dot top with additional butter.
Bake for approximately 35 minutes or until set and lightly browned.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, carrot and onion together until tender; drain well.
Add soup, sour cream and 1/2 cup stuffing; mix well.
Place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350°
for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: arizona casserole
directions: Brown meat in large skillet.
Saute onions and garlic.
Combine with meat.
Sprinkle chili powder over meat.
Add tomato sauce, salt, sugar, half the olives and all the green chiles.
Simmer over low heat 15 minutes.
Fry tortillas in hot oil (much easier to use corn chips or Fritos).

Beat cottage cheese and eggs together. Spread 1/3 meat mix in bottom of 2 (13 x 9-inch) baking dishes. Cover with 1/2 the Jack cheese, half the cottage cheese mixture and half the tortillas (or chips).
Repeat, finishing with a final layer of meat.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 40 minutes or until cheese is melted and casserole is heated through.
Garnish with sour cream, green onions and rest of black olives.
Freezes well but defrost before baking.
Serves 12 to 16 hungry people.

title: goulash
directions: Cook noodles according to directions while preparing beef. Saute ground beef. Add onions, seasoned salt, pepper and garlic powder. Drain grease off meat. Add cooked noodles and can of Ranch Style beans. Simmer in skillet until hot. Serve on plate or in bowl. Add cheese if you like.

title: corn flake macaroons
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend the butter and sugars thoroughly. Add egg and beat well.
Add the nuts, coconut (if desired) and corn flakes; mix well.
Shape cookies using a tablespoon and pressing filled spoon against side of bowl.
Then drop lightly on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen cookies, 49 calories each.

title: fish or shrimp creole court bouillon
directions: Saute chopped vegetables in margarine until tender.
Add tomato and picante sauces.
Cook on simmer for 15 to 20 minutes. Add fish and/or shrimp.
Cover; cook 10 minutes, until fish is flaky.
If adding shrimp, add them last; cook only 5 minutes. Serve over cooked rice.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Prepare cake batter according to package directions using eggs, water and oil.
Blend in peanut butter.
Spoon 1/2 batter into pan.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup chocolate chips over batter.
Spread remaining batter over top.
Sprinkle remaining chips and peanuts over batter.
Bake 45 minutes.
Cool in pan.
May be frosted or served plain.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Put cut rhubarb in 2-quart pan.
Pour sugar over it and let stand until juice forms.
Cook and bring to a boil.
Time for 11 minutes.
Stir while cooking.
Take off heat and pour in Jell-O. Stir and pour in jars.
Cover jars with lids.
Cool.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: crockpot round steak & mushroom gravy
directions: Cut steak in bite size pieces.
Put in crock pot and add remaining ingredients.
Cook on low 8 - 10 hours.

title: avocado with mustard paste salad
directions: Peel and pit avocados, cut into chunks and arrange on a plate. Remove seeds of pepper. Rinse with cold water.
Wipe dry and dice. Sprinkle over avocados.
Mix mustard powder into 3 tablespoons cold water. Blend well.
Let sit a minute or two, then add evaporated milk, salad dressing and salt; mix well and pour over avocados and red bell peppers.

title: butter pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar and butter until light with mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing after each.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Gradually add to sugar mixture and fold in sour cream, a little at a time, along with vanilla.
Mix well or until combined.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or 1 hour and 15 minutes in a Bundt size pan or two loaf pans.
When cool, garnish with powdered sugar.

title: peter paul mound cake
directions: Mix cake mix,
egg
yolks, buttermilk and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat as
directed
on
box,
then fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in 3 layers at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Put sugar, oil, salt and egg in bowl and mix together.
Add boiling water, then add yeast and flour.
Let rise for minutes.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: aunt lorraine's sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients with electric mixer and pour into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Pop the corn.
Combine molasses, sugar, vinegar and oleo in saucepan and cook to soft-ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add soda; stir to mix thoroughly.
Pour over popped corn, mixing well. Shape into balls with greased hands.
Makes about 24 popcorn balls.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Add sour cream.
Sift flour and baking soda together; add to creamed mixture.
Add flavoring.
Do not overbeat. Pour into a tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until cake tests clean.

title: catfish soup
directions: Put all ingredients, except the milk and butter, in a kettle or stewpan.
Cook over low heat until the meat falls apart.
Add milk and butter.
Bring to a boil.
Serve hot.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all together.
Melt 1/2 to 3/4 stick of butter in pan. Pour mixture into pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: quick cherry salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; toss lightly.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves with lime wedges as desired.

title: grape conserve
directions: Cook pulp, sugar and raisins until the consistency of jam.
Add lemon or orange slices 10 minutes before taking off the fire.
Add nuts 5 minutes before taking off the fire.
Pour into hot, sterilized jars and seal.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: In saucepan, mix sugar, cornstarch, flour and salt.
Gradually add hot water, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir over high heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cook and stir 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat.
Stir small amount of hot mixture into egg yolks, then return to hot mixture.
Bring to boil and cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add butter and lemon peel.
Slowly add lemon juice, mixing well.

title: curried fruit
directions: Mix margarine, brown sugar and curry powder.
Pour over fruit. Heat in a 325° oven for 45 minutes.

title: millionaires
directions: In double boiler, melt caramels in the milk.
When melted, remove pan from heat and add pecans.
Stir well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on buttered greased cookie sheet.
Refrigerate until cold.
Meanwhile, wash pan.
Melt paraffin and chocolate in the pan.
Take candy out of refrigerator and dip in chocolate with a toothpick.
Put back into refrigerator until morning and then put in container.
May want to leave in refrigerator or not.
Check to see if it's melted if left out.

title: lazy peach cobbler
directions: Combine sugar and flour and stir until well blended.
Add milk, stirring until smooth.
Melt butter in 1 1/2 to 2-quart baking dish.
Pour batter mixture into butter and then pour peaches in last; do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until top is well browned.

title: champagne punch
directions: Combine juices with frozen concentrate, sugar and mulling spices.
Mix thoroughly until sugar and concentrate are dissolved. Chill for at least 10 hours to allow spices to draw.
When serving, remove spices.
Stir in ginger ale and champagne. Garnish with fresh fruit slices.
Makes 1 1/4 gallons (about 35 four ounce servings).

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in loaf pan.
Bake in 350 degree oven for 1 hour.

title: perfect roast beef
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Prepare roast as you like it with spices.
Cook roast:
5 minutes per pound for rare, 10 minutes per pound for medium rare, 15 minutes per pound for well done. Turn oven off.
Leave in for 2 hours.
Do not open oven door for full 2 hours.

title: german potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes if desired and slice 1/4 inch thick and set aside.
In a large skillet over medium heat, fry bacon until crisp. Remove with a slotted spoon.
Drain on paper towels.
Discard all but 3 tablespoons of the drippings.
Over medium heat, saute celery and onion in bacon drippings until crispy tender.
Stir in flour, sugar, salt, and pepper until blended.
Stir in water, vinegar, and spicy brown mustard.
Stirring constantly over medium heat, bring to a boil until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Crumble bacon.
Stir potatoes and half of the bacon into hot dressing in skillet. Stirring gently, cook over medium heat until heated through and potatoes are well coated.
Transfer to a serving bowl and sprinkle remaining bacon over top.
Serve hot or warm.

title: cinnamon-applesauce ornaments
directions: Mix applesauce and cinnamon together until they make a dough. Roll out 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick and cut with cookie cutters.
Make a hole with a toothpick to use to hang.
Air dry ornaments on wax paper 2 days, turning frequently to avoid warping.
Ornaments will be color of cinnamon and they make your house smell wonderful!

title: mexican nut candy
directions: Stir both of the sugars, milk and margarine together in a large pan.
Cook over a medium heat, stirring occasionally, until the mixture forms a soft ball when a little bit of it is dropped into a glass of cold water.
(It is too soft if the mixture covers the bottom of the glass; it should hold together loosely.)
Add the vanilla and salt; cook about 1 minute longer.
Remove from heat and add nuts.
Beat with a spoon until candy starts to get very thick (a wooden spoon is best).
Drop by large spoonfuls onto wax paper. Let cool.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Dilute unflavored gelatin in cold water. Bring tomato soup (undiluted) to a boil and add gelatin mixture.
Remove from heat. Cool a few minutes. Add cream cheese.
Mix with mixer and add shrimp, celery and onion.
Mix with mixer and refrigerate.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: cape cod cranberry bread
directions: Grind seeded orange and place in one-cup measure; fill with boiling water.
Combine cranberries, sugar, egg and orange mixture in a bowl.
Let stand.
Sift flour, powder, salt and soda.
Cut in butter.
Pour in cranberry mixture.
Blend until just mixed.
Do not beat.
Fold in nuts.
Put in 9 x 5 x 3-inch greased pan.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: pickles (icebox)
directions: Heat sugar, vinegar and salt, then cool.
Slice onions and pickles paper thin.
Pack in a jar.
Pour sugar mixture over pickles.
Put in refrigerator.
Can use in a few days.

title: sweet potato surprise
directions: Cut cooked sweet potatoes in halves and arrange on buttered 7 1/2 x 12-inch baking dish.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, orange rind, cinnamon and apricot juice in saucepan and cook until thick. Stirring constantly.
Stir in apricots, butter and pecans.
Pour over sweet potatoes.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 25 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: easy bake potatoes
directions: Melt enough margarine to completely cover a 2-quart baking dish.
Place potatoes in dish.
Cover with flour and cheese (mixed together).
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 375° until potatoes are done.

title: white cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar together five times.
Mix with hot water and beat until smooth.
Add egg whites, beaten with the salt, then add vanilla.
Sprinkle baking powder over the mixture and stir.
Start baking in oven at 250° and gradually raise to 400°. Hold there until done.

title: beef casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except noodles or rice.
Place in casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 300° about 3 hours, or until beef is tender.
Serve on the noodles or rice.

title: cottage cheese muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Combine egg, milk and oil into the dry mixture.
Add cottage cheese and mix well.
Pour into greased muffin tins; fill 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Makes 15 to 18 muffins.

title: skillet enchiladas
directions: Brown meat in
electric
skillet;
drain and set aside. In skillet, combine
sauce
and soup together on 200° setting. Cook until bubbly.
Dip
enchilada
shells, turning once.
Set aside on wax paper.
When
you have finished all 12, pack each with meat, shredded cheese and olives.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce temperature to 350° and bake 50 minutes longer.

title: stromboli
directions: Let dough thaw and rise all day.
Pat out dough on cookie sheets.
Layer meats and cheeses on half of dough.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and oregano.
Roll up side over meats and cheeses to close.
Sprinkle with more grated Parmesan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or longer.
Slice into eating portions.
Heat up Garden Spot spaghetti sauce to pour over pieces.

title: hot dill pickles
directions: Place cucumbers in quart jars.
In each jar, place 1 garlic clove, 1 hot pepper and dill weed.
Combine water, vinegar and salt.
Pour over cucumbers; seal.
Process in hot water bath for 10 minutes.

title: no knead yeast butter rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast with lukewarm milk add 2 tbsp sugar. Melt butter in large bowl. Add cold milk, 1/2 cup sugar, salt, and eggs. Mix well. Alternately add yeast and flour to the above mixture, mixing well after each addition. When mixed, leave dough in same bowl, cover and refrigerate over night. On a lightly floured surface, divide dough into 4 parts. Roll each separately in as large a circle as possible. Dough should be very thin. Cut each circle into 16 wedges. Roll each piece from wide outside edge to center point. Lay point side down on ungreased cookie sheet. Let rise in warm room till double in
bulk. Approximately 2-4 hours. Bake at 350° for 15-20 minutes. Yields 64 rolls.

title: tuna and macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients with mayonnaise (sparingly). If it seems a little dry, add some of the pineapple juice.
Chill and serve with chopped green onions on top.
Very good with Ritz crackers.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze water out with hands.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill.
Serve with crackers, chips and bagel chips.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Cut in the shortening, beaten eggs, milk and sugar.
(Mix together.)
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sugar banana bread
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in bananas.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Spoon into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour or until bread tests done.

title: soft ginger cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Sprinkle with sugar. Bake in a moderate oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: uncle zeb's all balled-up olives
directions: Mix flour, margarine and Cheddar cheese spread together in a bowl until it is dough consistency.
Take about one tablespoon of the mixture in the palm of your hand and flatten.
Wrap the mixture around the olive and place on a cookie sheet.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika and bake at 300° until golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: yummy salad
directions: Mix and drain vegetables in bowl with 2 or 3 layers of paper towels in bottom for 2 to 3 hours.
Remove and toss with mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef; drain off grease and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan or Pyrex dish (or 3-quart casserole).
Mix together the soups and 1 can of water, then stir in the mixed vegetables, including juice.
Pour this mixture over the ground beef.
Top with a layer of Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Very good!

title: hawaiian milkshake
directions: Combine pineapple juice, orange juice, lemon juice and sugar. Stir to dissolve sugar.
Add crushed ice and milk.
Shake vigorously or beat until well blended and frothy.
Pour in tall glasses and garnish with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream. Serves 4.

title: baked brie
directions: Lay brie on 3 or 4 fillo sheets.
Spread on top of brie the mustard and preserves and top with pecans.
Bring the fillo sheets up and seal.
Coat the dough sheets with melted margarine.

title: chicken soup with almonds
directions: Melt the butter in a saucepan; add almonds and very lightly brown.
Set aside.	In a large saucepan, add the chicken broth, onion, bay leaf and almond mixture.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Stir flour and 1/4 cup of the milk until well blended.
Add the flour mixture, remainder of the milk, half and half, salt and pepper. Stir and simmer for 5 minutes or until hot.
Yields 6 servings.

title: 5 "p" salad
directions: Dissolve jello; add liquid and remaining ingredients. Allow to gel in an 8 x 8 or 9 x 9 pan. Cut into squares to serve; place on a lettuce leaf. A dollop of mayonnaise is optional.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer thawed broccoli, chicken, cheese and water chestnuts. Mix mushroom soup and mayonnaise and pour over chicken mixture. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
When almost done, put can of onion rings on top and brown.
Watch because they burn easily.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Soak gelatine in crab juice.
Add hot soup, undiluted, to the mashed cream cheese.
Add gelatine mix to this while hot, then cool.
Add mayonnaise and vegetables and pour into mold. Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: fruit tarts
directions: Make and bake tart shells.
Scald milk.
Mix sugar, salt and flour with beaten egg and pour scalded milk slowly over this mixture, stirring constantly; then return to double boiler and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla; cool.
Just before using, fold in half the whipped cream; place layer of berries on top.
Heat currant jelly until it melts and put about 1 tablespoon on top of each tart.
Top with teaspoon of whipped cream.
Serves 6.

title: christmas punch
directions: Bring sugar and water to boil.
Add all juices and heat well. Add cloves and cinnamon.
Serve hot.

title: maple milkshake
directions: Mix the milk and maple syrup in the electric blender.
Add ice cream to the mixture by the spoonful.
Blend a few minutes, until smooth.
Makes 4 cups (1 quart).

title: lots o' cookies
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and cream well. Add dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° approximately 8 minutes or until done.
Makes 1,680 cookies.

title: whatchamacallit
directions: Mix cake mix, melted or softened butter and 1 egg.
Press in bottom of a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan; set aside.
Mix together cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar.
Beat with mixer until smooth and well blended.
Pour over bottom layer.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: sugar-free carrot salad
directions: In a bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add lemon juice and enough cold water to the pineapple juice to make 1 cup liquid.
Stir liquid into dissolved gelatin.
Chill until slightly set.
Stir in pineapple and carrots.
Pour into oiled 4-cup mold or round glass dish; cover and chill until firm.

title: cherry-o cream cheese pie
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine; mix well.
Press evenly and firmly on bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie pan.
Chill.
Let cheese stand at room temperature until soft; beat until fluffy. Gradually add milk, stirring until well mixed.
Add lemon juice and vanilla; stir until well mixed.
Turn into prepared crust. Chill 2 to 3 hours.
(Do not freeze!)
Top with can of cherry pie filling, chilled.
If you prefer, another fruit pie filling may be used.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: ice cream cone cake
directions: Put dry cake mix in a bowl and add dry pudding.
Mix cake according to directions on box.
Put cones on a cookie sheet and fill 1/2 full of cake batter.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean when inserted into middle.
Frost and decorate as you like.

title: heavenly orange fluff salad
directions: Mix gelatin with hot water.
Stir in undiluted orange juice. Cool.
Add mandarin oranges and pineapple to gelatin mixture. Pour in 8 x 12-inch dish.
Chill until firm.
Top with the topping.

title: poke cake
directions: Combine the first five ingredients in large mixer bowl. Blend, then beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Dissolve gelatin as directed on package. Poke holes in cake with fork.
Pour warm gelatin over cake.
Chill for 4 hours.
Spread prepared whipped topping over cake.

title: warm weather frozen salad
directions: In a bowl, blend the softened cream cheese, mayonnaise and mustard.
Fold in whipped cream.
Add the drained fruit and the strawberries.
Pour mixture into an oblong dish or square baking pan.
Freeze for about 2 hours or until firm.
Remove from freezer.
With a sharp knife, cut into even squares.
Then let sit at room temperature for 15 minutes until just starting to thaw. Place on individual salad plates.
Garnish with fresh lettuce leaves and sliced red pepper, if desired.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Combine broccoli, celery, onion and chicken broth.
Heat to boiling; lower heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
In a medium saucepan, melt butter.
Add flour and mix, then add 1/2 cup milk to make a white sauce.
Stir the white sauce into broccoli mixture. Add the rest of the milk, half and half and cream.
Add seasoning and mix well.
Heat until the soup thickens, about 20 minutes.

title: hash
directions: Cut beef and pork as for stew.
Cook ingredients slowly 3 hours or more until hash like consistency.
A little water may need to be added.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put apples in bottom of 8-inch pan.
Cover with nuts and then put dry cake mix.
Add butter on top.
Put in oven and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° until firm.

title: sweet tooth dessert
directions: Cook rice in 2-inches of water for about 5 minutes.
Add coconut and sugar.
Cook another 4 minutes.
Let cool for about 3 minutes.
Then add marshmallows on top.
Eat after chilled.

title: summer squash
directions: Brown onion in butter or oleo.
Add squash.
Cook slowly until tender.
Do not use additional water.

title: hot and sour soup
directions: Heat broth to boil.
Add vegetables and cook 1 minute.
Add cornstarch mixture and cook until thick.
Drop in beaten egg and stir.
Turn off heat and add 3 tablespoons vinegar.
Season with Tabasco.

title: spiced lamb chops
directions: Mix the spices in a bowl.
In another bowl, cream the butter with a fork, adding 3 teaspoons for the spice mixture, the mint and the parsley.
Add garlic to the butter with the salt; mix well.
Set aside to allow the flavors to mellow at room temperature.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add barbecue sauce, sugar and onions. Place each biscuit in ungreased muffin pan pressing dough up sides to edge of pan.
Spoon mixture into cups and add a little cheese in each cup.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes in 400° oven.

title: club day chicken and dressing
directions: Mix together stuffing mix, melted oleo, broth, chicken, celery, onion and salt.
In a separate bowl, mix eggs, milk and soup.
Place first mixture in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan or a casserole dish.
Pour second mixture over it.
(May refrigerate at this point and bake the next day.)
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and bake 10 more minutes.

title: tomasina's fab meat loaf(a.k.a. 72 market st. meat loaf)
directions: Saute first 8 ingredients.
After sauteing these ingredients, mix altogether with spices and meats.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: tomato broccoli bake
directions: Cook pasta 8 to 10 minutes; drain.
In saucepan, cook onion and garlic in butter until tender.
Add tomatoes, parsley, broth, oregano, basil and salt.
Bring to a boil; add broccoli.
Cover and simmer 4 minutes.
Add pasta to tomato mixture. Turn into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, covered in 375° oven for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes more.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: stewed peppers with tomatoes peperonata
directions: Pour oil into skillet.
Add onions, garlic and bay leaves. Saut over moderate heat until onions are golden, stirring constantly.
Add the peppers, then season with salt and pepper. Cook over brisk heat for about 10 minutes, stirring frequently. Add tomatoes to skillet and cook for another 15 minutes.
Then serve.

title: tomato spaghetti
directions: Fry bacon.
Place on a napkin to drain.
Remove all but a small tablespoon of grease from a frying pan.
Place onion in grease.
Lightly brown.
Heat tomatoes in a small pan.
Put onions and bacon (now diced) into tomato pan.
Salt and pepper to good taste and bring to a boil.
Taste again and add salt and pepper as needed.
Boil spaghetti until tender but not soft or mushy.
Put spaghetti in colander and strain with hot water poured over.
Put spaghetti into pan again and add tomato sauce.
Fini.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Mix all ingredients until crumbly.
Press into 9 X 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Strain zucchini through cheesecloth to drain excess water. Combine all ingredients except buns.
Shape into six patties. Heat oil.
Fry patties until brown, turning once.
Split buns and toast.

title: meal in one pan!
directions: Heat oven to temperature recommended for corn bread.
Brown meat; drain.
Add Ro-Tel, beans and corn.
Heat to boil (bubble). Mix corn bread by package directions.

title: peach meringue cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour two 8-inch round cake pans.
Cream butter and sugar with mixer; add egg yolks and mix thoroughly.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture alternately with milk.
Pour into cake pans.
Set aside while preparing meringue.
Beat egg whites until foamy but not dry.
Gradually add sugar by tablespoon until all is used.
Add vanilla.
Divide meringue and spread over unbaked cake batter.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes, being careful not to overbake.
Cool.
Cut into wedges to serve.
Top with sweetened, sliced peaches.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: graham cracker loaf
directions: Grind crackers, dates, marshmallows and nut meats through the grinder.
Mix well with cream.
Form into a log and place in a cool place until ready to serve.
Slice and serve with whipped cream.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini, vanilla and nuts.
Mix lightly, but well.
Add flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and baking powder.
Mix until blended in one bowl with electric mixer. Put in two loaf pans.
Bake one hour at 325° to 350°.

title: strawberries
directions: In large bowl mix nuts, coconut and dry Jell-O.
Add Eagle Brand Milk and vanilla, and work with a wooden spoon until well mixed.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Pour water in small bowl; color green with food coloring.
Add almonds and color deep green.
Sift almonds onto paper towel to dry.
Shape chilled mixture into strawberries (using 1 teaspoon for each), roll in red sugar, and dip ends is green sugar.
Use the almond sliver for the stems. Makes about 85 candies.
Store in airtight container or in the refrigerator.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: In a small skillet, saute onion until clear; add tomato sauce and water, simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cook macaroni as directed; drain.
In a buttered baking dish layer the macaroni and cheese starting with the macron i. When finish layering, pour tomato and onion mixture over it.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes for 350°.

title: corn fritters
directions: Combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Beat eggs with milk; add melted Crisco and whole kernel corn.
Combine two mixtures lightly.
Drop from a tablespoon into shallow Crisco heated to 365°.
Fry until brown and cooked in center.

title: chop suey cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pineapple nut cake
directions: Mix altogether; pour into large, greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool.
Frost.
May be frozen without frosting.
Also good with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: easy cole slaw
directions: Mix milk, dressing, sugar, salt and pepper; set aside while you shred cabbage.

title: quick and easy cake mix cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, combine cake mix, oil and eggs.
Stir by hand until thoroughly moistened.
Stir in decorator sprinkles from cake mix.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake for 6 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Spread frosting over cookies.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: date torte grandma style
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar; beat well until creamy, then add vanilla.
Add graham crackers, then nut meats, then dates.
Pour in prepared pan (grease bottom of 9 x 13-inch or 4-sided cookie sheet and put wax paper on it and grease wax paper).
Pour on wax paper and bake 30 to 35 minutes in 350° oven.
Let cool for 10 minutes.
Turn upside down; peel off wax paper.

title: barbecued spare or short ribs
directions: Brown the ribs a little in pressure cooker and drain off fat. Add balance of ingredients and cook about 15 minutes at 15 pounds pressure.
Open and simmer until tender enough.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoonful on baking sheet.
Bake at 350°.
Frost when cool.

title: chocolate nut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate in top of double boiler.
Add salt and nuts. Drop from tip of teaspoon onto wax paper.
Set aside to harden.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Blend ingredients; pour into greased and floured loaf pans (2).
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: artichoke and green bean casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake for 1 hour, covered, at 350°.
Bake the last 10 minutes, uncovered.

title: english sherry trifle
directions: Break up ladyfingers and line bottom of trifle bowl.
Pour sherry over ladyfingers.
Cover ladyfingers with raspberry preserves.
Cover preserves with raspberries.
Distribute peaches over entire layer of raspberries.
Spread cooked and cooled custard over peaches.
Distribute sliced bananas over custard. Spread whipped cream over bananas and garnish with cherries and almonds.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cucumber and onion salad
directions: Layer onions and cucumbers in a jar or bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight, stirring or inverting jar several times.

title: vinegar-flavored grilled chicken
directions: In a small saucepan, place vinegar, water, margarine, Texas Pete, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil. Marinate the chicken for 2 to 3 hours before grilling for better flavor.
Brush sauce on chicken on prepared grill, skin side up, about 8-inches from heat.
Cook, turning and basting liberally with sauce every 5 to 10 minutes, probably only have to cook for 30 to 40 minutes or until fork can be inserted with ease.
Makes 4 servings.

title: snap beans
directions: Fry bacon and
let
cool.
Cover
beans with hot water. Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook 20 minutes, then add potatoes. Cook until potatoes are	done.
Add
water if beans get to low on water.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix well and store.
To prepare, use 1/3 cup of mixture and fill with hot water.

title: valentine's raspberry passion
directions: Place partially thawed raspberries, egg whites, sugar, lemon juice and Amaretto into a large mixing bowl and beat with an electric mixer at high speed for 15 minutes.
Whip cream until stiff, add vanilla and brandy, then fold cream and almonds into raspberry mixture.
Pour into a pie shell and freeze for at least 4 hours.
Decorate with chocolate hearts or chocolate sprinkles. Serves 12.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Line a cake tin with wax paper and pack in tin.
Seal airtight and let set in refrigerator for 1 week.
This can be put into any size can or box as long as it is airtight.
Fruit cake can be kept as long as a year.

title: sausage pie
directions: Place sausages on a rack in a baking pan; bake at 350° for 15 minutes, or until lightly brown.
Cut into 1-inch pieces; set aside.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix thawed hash browns, 1/2 cup margarine, onion, soup, milk, sour cream and cheese.
Stir thoroughly.
Spoon into greased casserole dish.
Crush cereal and stir in rest of the margarine. Sprinkle this on top of the casserole.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: three bean hot dish
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain fat. Put beef in crock-pot. Brown bacon and onions; drain. Add to beef. Add all remaining ingredients to crock-pot. Stir well; cover and cook on low 4 to 6 hours.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into small flowerets
and add rest of ingredients.
Mix well, cover and refrigerate.
Will keep for several days.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix together in a large mixing bowl the flour, sugar, salt, soda and cinnamon, then add the oil, eggs, applesauce and vanilla. Beat 5 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Has better flavor if cooked a day or two before eating.
Very moist; keeps well.
Freezes well. Good plain or frosted.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Melt fat in heavy saucepan.
Add onion, garlic and bay leaf. Cook gently 5 minutes or until lightly browned.
Add rice and salt. Stir.
Add other ingredients.
Stir and bring to a boil; taste and season.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Place in 375° preheated oven.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
When cooking, remove bay leaf and bell pepper.
Serves 6.

title: crunchy veggie sandwich
directions: Slice as many vegetables as you want and put on Italian bread. Pour dressing over the whole loaf.
Cut into individual sandwiches and serve.
To make an individual serving, cut a piece of Italian bread off and use less dressing.

title: no bake cookies
directions: First mix sugar and cocoa. Mix well.

Then add milk. Stir and then add margarine, stirring constantly. Boil for 2 minutes. Then take off heat and add vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal. Spoon out on aluminum foil. When cool, it will set and will be able to be picked up and eaten.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ketchup, well. Shape into loaf pan. Spread ketchup evenly on top of loaf. Cover with foil and bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes. Uncover and cook another 10-15 minutes or until meat starts to break apart.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Place cucumbers and onions in 2 tablespoons salt.
Let stand for 3 hours.
Drain well.
Pack pickles and onions in a large jar. Pour liquid over pickles and refrigerate.

title: banana chocolate chip cupcakes
directions: Mix the dry ingredients.
Mix shortening, bananas, milk, water and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients; beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs; beat 2 minutes.
Add chocolate chips.
Fill muffin cups 1/2 full. Bake for 20 minutes at 375°.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Cook until thick and meat done.
Put in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add 16 ounces cheese (your choice).
Cover with 3 cans crescent rolls. Bake at 350° until rolls are light brown, dish out, upside-down.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Cut cauliflower and broccoli into bite-size pieces in a large salad bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Serve over cauliflower and broccoli.

title: shaggy date nut balls
directions: Mix oleo, dates, sugar and egg together and cook over low heat, stirring constantly for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and then add vanilla, Rice Krispies and pecans.
Let cool.
Shape into balls and roll in coconut.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni first, then rinse.
Mix in a bowl the macaroni, butter, salt, pepper, eggs and all 3 cut up cheeses just enough to blend in.
Pour milk in almost covering the macaroni.
Use Longhorn cheese, sliced in squares and lay on top of macaroni.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake in oven, in casserole dish, for 45 minutes on bottom rack first; halfway through, bake on top rack to brown.

title: hawaiian kabobs
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/2 cup juice.
Put chunks and vegetables in large bowl.
Set aside.
Combine reserved pineapple juice with soy sauce, olive oil, brown sugar and seasonings.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Pour over vegetable mix.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Remove pineapple and vegetables from marinade and reserve marinade.
Place vegetables, pineapple and mushrooms on skewers.
Grill for 20 minutes or until soft.
Turn and baste with marinade.

title: strawberry dip
directions: Combine Cool Whip with yogurt; add strawberries and mix well. Seve as a dip with fresh fruit.
Recipe can be halved.

title: mock filet mignon
directions: Will also need toothpicks.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer vegetables in glass
bowl
in
order listed.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar.
Spread on top of salad.
Put cheese and bacon on top of
mayonnaise mixture.
Cover with plastic wrap, then aluminum foil.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken tamale pie
directions: Pan-boil chicken approximately 30 minutes or until tender with the garlic, cloves, onions, salt and basil.
Remove chicken and take flesh from the bones.
Strain the water the chicken was boiled in and save 2 cups for tamale mix.
Chop chicken and onions (it was cooked with) and combine with chiles, olives, sugar, chili powder and salt to taste.
Mix in sour cream.
Place mixture in a casserole pan and top with grated cheese.
(Preheat oven to 375°.) Cook until top has browned.

title: chocolate apple cake
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and cocoa. Add eggs.
Mix dry ingredients together in a small bowl.
Add dry ingredients to butter mixture, alternately with water, beating after each addition.
Fold in shredded apple.

title: blonde chocolate chip brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together in one bowl, brown sugar, water, beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add in melted butter.
In separate bowl, mix together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add both mixtures together, then add chocolate chips and nuts.
Put in greased cake roll pan and spread evenly.
Bake for 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: "excellent" brownies
directions: Melt caramels and evaporated milk together slowly and set aside.
Combine German chocolate cake mix and melted margarine. Put 1/2 cake mixture in a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 6 to 7 minutes.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add cranberries and stir well.
Let set in refrigerator.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream and powdered sugar together and add vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip and top with pecans and cherries.

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (moderate).
Combine all ingredients except chicken in saucepan, place over heat, and simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Place chicken in large baking pan.
Pour half of the barbecue sauce over chicken and bake uncovered for about 45 to 60 minutes.
Baste with remaining barbecue sauce every 15 minutes during cooking.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake per directions on box in sheet pan. Poke holes in cake with handle of wooden spoon when cake is done. Pour Eagle Brand over cake. Pour strawberries and juice over cake. Refrigerate. Top with Cool Whip when ready to serve.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until frothy. Add sugar and oil. Beat well. Add remaining ingredients and beat 5 minutes at moderate speed.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Cool in pans 15 minutes, then remove.

title: meringue shells dessert
directions: Add salt to egg whites.
Beat until fairly stiff.
Add sugar gradually.
Add vanilla and fold in nuts.
Drop by large serving spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Make hole in middle.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes in 250° oven until firm and dry.
Fill with anything you like: whipped cream with Heath bar shavings is very good.
Make any size you want by varying size dropped, so long as you make shell for filling.

title: clam and shrimp soup
directions: *Two 6.5 ounce cans of chopped clams with juice may be substituted for 40 small clams.

title: crispy chocolate peanut bars
directions: Butter an 8-inch square baking pan.
Mix corn syrup, brown sugar and salt in saucepan and boil.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter, stirring until smooth.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Stir in vanilla and cereals.
Before firm, add chocolate chips.
Stir until blended.
Press into buttered pan and chill.
Cut and serve.

title: maggie's jello salad
directions: Melt in a double boiler the marshmallows, milk and lime Jell-O.
Cream and add cream cheese; add pineapple, Cool Whip, pecans and mayonnaise.
Stir constantly until all ingredients are well mixed.
Pour into a mold and refrigerate.

title: roast chicken(greek style)
directions: Wash chicken and place in roasting pan.
Mix other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake 1 1/2 hours or until done in a 350° oven.
(marinate some during baking.) Good!

title: party punch
directions: Combine the juices.
Boil water, sugar and spices together for five minutes.
Cool and strain out spices. Add spiced syrup to juices.
Chill thoroughly.

title: turtlettes
directions: On greased cookie sheet for each candy arrange 4 pecan halves in 4 point star.
Spoon about 2 teaspoons hot caramel mixture over nuts almost to cover.
Let stand until caramel is set.
Spread about 1 teaspoon chocolate on center of each turtlette.
Let stand until set.
Store in airtight place.

title: prize sugar cookies
directions: Mix all together and form balls placing them on cookie sheet. Flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 minutes.

title: sour cream beef enchiladas
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add rest of ingredients, except cheese and tortillas.
Simmer a few minutes.

title: cranberry salad 1
directions: Mix water, jello and lemon juice until dissolved.
Then mix remaining ingredients.
Chill.

title: unbaked chocolate cookies
directions: In a saucepan, bring the sugar, cocoa and milk to a boil, continue to boil for 30 seconds.
Remove from the heat and stir in the peanut butter, butter, vanilla and oatmeal, mix well.
Drop onto waxed paper and allow to cool.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: chocolate fudge pudding
directions: Mix together and pour into glass baking dish or 6 individual dishes; place dish in pan of water in the oven when baking.
Bake on slow oven at 300° until set.
May be served with whipped cream.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Drain green beans.
Brown meat and onion together.
Add seasonings, tomato	soup
and beans.
Mash potatoes; add milk, egg and
butter.
Place
meat
mixture	in
greased casserole. Spoon mounds
of mashed potatoes over meat mixture.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.	Makes 6 servings.

title: egg casserole
directions: Mix milk, eggs, salt and mustard.
In 9 x 13-inch casserole, layer bread and cheese, ending with cheese.
Pour milk mixture over.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Crumbled bacon may be spread over top before baking.
Recipe can be made the night before and baked in morning.

title: brown rice casserole
directions: Melt oleo.
Brown the rice in the oleo.
Add celery and onion. Cook on low heat 20 minutes or more.
Add 2 cups beef bouillon liquid and 1 can mushrooms.
Bake in casserole 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Serves 8.

title: grandmother's beef stew
directions: Mix all ingredients in covered casserole.
Bake 5 hours at 250° or 2 1/2 to 3 hours at 325°.

title: pork roast with gravy
directions: Have a heavy piece of foil, 30 x 18.
Place onion soup mix in center of foil, then place pork roast on soup mix.
Fold over and seal.
Place into a 9 x 13 pan.
Cook at 300° for 3 1/2 hours. Then remove roast to plate and make gravy with the drippings, flour and water.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 7 x 11-inch baking pan and place apples in bottom.
Combine cinnamon, salt and water; sprinkle over apples.
In a separate bowl, pinch together the flour, sugar and margarine until the mixture resembles corn meal.
Place on top of apples.
Bake for approximately 40 minutes, or until the topping is bubbly and lightly golden.
Serve with Cool Whip, whipped cream or French vanilla ice cream while still warm.
Serves 6.

title: lemon squares
directions: Sift 2 cups flour and powdered sugar.
Cut in butter until creamy.
Press into greased 9 X 13 baking pan and bake 325 degrees for 20-25 minutes.
Beat sugar, eggs, and juice.
Sift together 1/4 cup flour and 1/2 teaspoon baking powder.
Add to egg mixture. Pour over baked crust.
Bake again 325 degrees for 25-30 minutes. Cool; sprinkle with powdered sugar and cut into squares.

title: sweet corn bread
directions: Combine the cornmeal, flour, baking powder, salt and sugar. Combine the egg yolk, milk, vanilla and melted butter.
Stir into the dry ingredients until they are thoroughly moistened.
Beat the egg whites until stiff and fold into the batter carefully. Pour into a 3-quart shallow baking pan that has been buttered well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until it tests done.
If desired,
two 8-inch square pans may be used.

title: cooked cabbage
directions: Chop cabbage into large casserole dish (2 to 3 quarts). Add seasoning and margarine.
Cover and microwave for 15 to 20 minutes (microwave temperatures may vary).
Delicious and low calorie.

title: shoe box cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add well beaten eggs last.
Pour into a large shoe box lined with wax paper.
Bake 3 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: zucchini dollar cakes
directions: Mix zucchini,
egg yolks and rest of ingredients except egg whites.
Beat
egg	whites	stiff
and
fold into zucchini mixture.
Fry to golden brown.
If necessary, use more flour.

title: oreo delight
directions: Crush 24 cookies; save 1/2 cup.
Press in a 12 x 9-inch pan.

title: crabmeat casserole(serves 100)
directions: Boil and drain noodles.
Prepare cream sauce from butter, flour and milk.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add mustard, lemon juice and soup base to taste.
Combine noodles, crabmeat, broccoli and mushrooms.
Divide into 2 (6-inch deep) steam table pans.
Add sauce to both.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix in top of double boiler the milk, sugar, cornstarch, vanilla flavoring and egg yolks.
Put aside egg whites for later use.
Cook on medium heat until mixture thickens, stirring often. Beat egg whites; add sugar a little at a time until stiff.
Layer in casserole dish the wafers, bananas, pudding.
Makes 3 layers of each.
Add meringue and brown in oven at 350°.

title: hard candy
directions: Combine sugar, water and syrup.
Boil to 290°.
Remove from heat and add desired flavoring and food color.
Stir only until blended.
Pour onto lightly oiled cookie sheet.
Cool slightly and score in squares or cool completely and break into small pieces. Dust in powdered sugar.
Store in covered jars.

title: old fashion soft molasses cookies
directions: Cream first nine ingredients together.
Add milk and flour. Roll out on cheesecloth or pillow cases. Sprinkle with sugar lightly.
Cut out and bake at 350°.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Blend baking mix and milk.
Turn onto surface dusted with baking mix and knead about 20 times.
Pat or roll 1/4-inch thick in rectangle 8 x 14-inch.
Spread with soft margarine and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Roll as for jelly roll.
Cut into 1-inch pieces.
Place in prepared pan.
Bake 15 minutes in a preheated 425° oven.
Use a greased 13 x 9-inch pan or muffin pans. Makes 15 rolls.
Serve warm.

title: coconut-cream cheese frosting
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons of butter in skillet; add coconut.
Stir constantly on low heat until golden brown.
Spread coconut on absorbent paper to cool.
Cream 2 tablespoons of butter with cream cheese.
Add milk and sugar alternately, beating well.
Add vanilla; stir in 1 3/4 cups coconut.
Spread on tops and sides of cake layers.
Sprinkle with remaining coconut.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Cook Karo syrup and sugar on High for 4 minutes.
Add peanuts and cook on High for 4 more minutes.
Add butter and cook on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Add vanilla and baking soda.
Stir well and pour on greased cookie sheet.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix first three ingredients. Press in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: easy coffee can bread
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups flour with yeast.
In saucepan, combine milk, water, oil, sugar and salt.
Heat until warm.
Add to flour and yeast.
Beat at medium speed until smooth; blend in eggs and add 1 more cup flour at lowest speed.
Stir in remaining flour. Use 2 coffee cans, grease really good (13 ounce size).
Cover with lids, let stand in warm place.
When rises almost to top, bake 30 minutes or so at 375°.

title: applesauce salad
directions: Heat the applesauce.
Add the jello and 7-Up.
Put in mold and chill.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Mix flour, sugar, pineapple, egg and vinegar over medium heat until thick.
Cool.
Fold Cool Whip with mixture, apples and 1/2 cup peanuts.
Sprinkle the rest of peanuts on top.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper.
Drain off grease; boil noodles in salt water and drain.
Add chicken soup, corn and meat mixture.
Mix and bake 1 hour at 350° in a 2-quart casserole.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Blend together first
ingredients,
then add next 3. Press mixture into a 1
quart
glass pan and freeze overnight. Serves 12 to 16.

title: sharon's chicken wings
directions: Break wings into separate parts.
Arrange in 13 x 9-inch pan. Top with sugar and garlic powder and soy sauce.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir several times.
These are sweet, not hot!!

title: south of the border burrito
directions: Heat tortilla until soft.
Spread pinto beans on tortilla. Spoon on salsa and green chilies.
Place lettuce leaf in center of tortilla with cucumber slices and sprouts.
Roll up to enclose fillings.

title: honey spice acorn squash(yields 4 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Scrub squash.
Cut in half lengthwise; remove seeds and stringy fibers.
Arrange, cut side down, in shallow baking pan.
Surround with 1/2-inch of hot water.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour off excess liquid from baking pan.
Turn squash, cut side up.
Pour sauce into cavities; bake 15 minutes, basting now and then with sauce. Enjoy!

title: trigger fish cocktail
directions: Steam fish in/over boiling water, containing spices.
Chill fish; break into small pieces and set aside.

title: pizza soup
directions: Make tomato soup as directed on can.
Chop pepperoni into quarters and add to soup.
Simmer.
Top soup with 1 tablespoon Mozzarella and 1 tablespoon croutons per serving, when ready to serve.

title: stromboli
directions: Roll bread dough into a rectangle 15 x 10-inches.
Arrange a row of salami, a row of Provolone cheese, row of salami, row of cheese and end with a row of salami down center of rectangle (about 20 slices salami, 16 slices cheese).
Top with pepper salad.
Fold long side in 1/3.
Then fold over completely.
Brush with oil from drained pepper salad.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Bask with oil while baking.

title: bread pudding
directions: Tear bread into pieces.
Soak in milk until well mixed.
Add sugar, eggs, vanilla, raisins and coconut.
Stir well.
Pour pudding into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake until very firm at 325° for 60 minutes.
Cool.
Serve with ice cream.

title: rio grande chili
directions: Prepare chili as directed on package.
Top with cheese, sour cream, onions and pepper.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add flour and sour cream alternately.
Add baking powder, soda and vanilla.
Mix well.

title: sauerkraut chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 (8-inch) square or round baking pans.
Thoroughly cream margarine with sugar. Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift together cocoa, flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add dry mixture.
Stir in sauerkraut. Spoon into prepared baking pans.
Bake about 30 to 35 minutes. Let cool.
Spread with whipped cream frosting.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in uncooked pie shell, top with remaining pie shell.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: keepsake biscuits
directions: Knead well and mold into neat small biscuits with your hands. Bake well and you have a good sweet biscuit that will keep for weeks in a dry place.

title: turkey lasagna
directions: Saute onion and garlic in liquid Butter Buds.
If using fresh mushrooms, also saute
them.
If using canned mushrooms, wait to add them later.
After
onion is cooked, add tomatoes, tomato paste, salt, pepper and other seasonings.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in frying pan.
Empty 1 can cream of mushroom into 2 cup measuring cup and mix.
Add milk to get 2 cups.
Empty into baking dish.
When chops are browned, spread them out in the baking dish.
Mix second can same as first and pour over top of pork chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in preheated oven, uncovered.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together all ingredients and store in plastic container.

title: ambrosia mold
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving liquid.
Add cold water to make 1 cup.
Stir boiling water into gelatin in a large bowl (2 minutes to completely dissolve).
Stir in measured liquid.
Refrigerate until slightly thickened.
Stir in whipped topping; stir until smooth.
Refrigerate until mixture will mound (about 10 minutes). Stir in oranges, pineapple, marshmallows and coconut.
Pour into mold or molds.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Cook ziti rigati; drain.
In medium saucepan, melt butter. Stir in flour, mustard and pepper.
Blend in milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Combine ziti, cheese sauce, corned beef and onions; mix well.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, layer one-half each of the ziti mixture and sauerkraut.
Repeat layers.
Top with bread cubes.
Bake at 350° until hot, about 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: connecticut apple cake
directions: Into large bowl of electric mixer, sift together flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and spices.
Add apples, shortening, nuts and eggs.
Beat until well mixed.
Turn into greased and floured round spring-form pan or divide into 2 (9-inch) layer cake pans.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 45 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool. Remove from pans.
Frost with caramel frosting, if desired.

title: overnight buns
directions: Start at 4:30 to 5:00 p.m.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add melted shortening and butter, sugar, salt and eggs.
Beat and add flour until you can't beat anymore.
Then knead the rest of the flour in.
Dough will be sticky.
Knead, then cover with towel. Set in warm place.
Punch down every hour until 9:30 or 10.
Make into buns and put on greased pans.
Cover with towel and plastic. Set overnight.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook ground beef and onion until meat lightly browns.
Drain off fat.
Add water, tomato paste, sugar, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil, then let simmer 2 to 3 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Cook lasagna until tender.
Drain and wash with cool water until able to handle.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes for about 15 minutes.
Add soup, salt, pepper and crumbled bacon.
Cook until tender.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Layer half the green beans and water chestnuts. Combine the next 5 ingredients together. Use half of this mixture over the first layer of green beans. Layer remaining green beans and water chestnuts and spread remaining cheese mixture. Sprinkle on paprika. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes until bubbly and just beginning to brown.

title: thin pizza crust
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a mixing bowl; sprinkle yeast over mixture, stirring until dissolved.
Gradually add flour, mixing well after each addition.

title: gingerbread boys
directions: Beat sugar and butter until well blended.
Add eggs and molasses.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill 1 hour. Roll out to about 1/4-inch thick and cut out Gingerbread Boys. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Decorate before baking with M&M's. When cool, make icing and decorate with bow ties, etc.
Makes 24 cookies.

title: heavenly bits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pinch off small pieces and shape into fingers.
Cook at 325 degrees for 20 minutes or until light brown.
Roll gently into powdered sugar while hot.

title: broccoli
directions: Mix together; place in a 9 x 13-inch pan, which you place in a pan of water to bake.
Bake 40 minutes, or until done in a 350° oven.

title: sue's hot appetizers
directions: Mix and spread on Melba toast rounds.
Broil until cheese bubbles.

title: double chocolate cookie bars
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine; press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In medium saucepan over medium heat, melt 1 cup chips with sweetened condensed milk and vanilla.
Pour evenly over crust; top with nuts and remaining chips.
Bake 20 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain sauerkraut and wash in cold water.
Squeeze out all excess water.
Add sugar and set aside until sugar dissolves.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Flavor improves if kept in refrigerator overnight.

title: vidalia onion casserole 1
directions: Saute onions in bacon drippings.
(Requires 2 frying pans with 2 tablespoons of bacon drippings per pan.)
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer onions, cheese and bacon.
Finish top with crumbled Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hamburger and beans
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain.
Combine all the ingredients with meat; simmer for 10 minutes.
Really good served with fried potatoes.
This is a family favorite.

title: tandy cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients except peanut butter and Hershey bar. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes in 11 x 17-inch greased cookie sheet with sides.
Remove from oven and spread with peanut butter while cake is still hot.
Refrigerate until peanut butter hardens.
Melt chocolate bar.
Spread over cake and cool again.

title: chocolate cupcakes
directions: Cook 2 handfuls of macaroni in milk.
Add 5 cans of corn and stir in with macaroni.
Cook 1 chicken in pan and take out bones. Add a little more milk.
Mix and cook on a cookie sheet for 5 hours.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Press 1 package of rolls into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan (do not grease).
Beat well the cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and egg yolk.
Spread evenly over rolls.
Evenly roll out second package of rolls; spread over cheese mixture.
Beat egg white until frothy; brush on top.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Dissolve baking soda in buttermilk.
Add all other ingredients to creamed mixture and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: cheese rolls
directions: Separate egg yolk from egg white. Set white aside. Blend together egg, softened cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice and vanilla. Mix well. Grease a cookie sheet with margarine. Spread 1/2 of 1 package of rolls on one side of the sheet. Do the same with the second half. Spread cheese filling over the 2 crescent roll layers. Top this with the other package of rolls and pinch the top and bottom layers together. Beat egg white and brush on top of the 2 cheese rolls. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Dust with powdered sugar.

title: milk chocolate dipped pretzels
directions: Combine over hot (not boiling) water the chips and vegetable shortening.
Stir until chips mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat, but keep chocolate over hot water.
Dip pretzels into mixture and coat evenly.
Shake off any excess.
Place pretzels on wax paper-lined cookie sheets.
Chill in refrigerator until coating sets (about 15 minutes).
Gently loosen from wax paper.
Serve immediately or store in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: bailey's irish cream
directions: Combine in blender 30 seconds.
Pour in jar and refrigerate. Absolutely delicious.

title: stir-fried beef vegetables
directions: Over medium flame, heat vegetable oil in large skillet. Stir-fry sliced beef, then remove.
Cut
onions in thin wedges and mince garlic clove.
Stir-fry these briefly, then add broccoli and cauliflower and stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Add mushrooms and replace beef.
Now mix crushed bouillon cube and soy sauce in.
Blend cornstarch in 3/4 cup water and add to skillet.
Stir and cook for 5 minutes more.
Serve along with cooked rice or mixed vegetables.

title: monkey bread
directions: Spray a Bundt pan with Pam. Cut biscuits into fourths and roll in sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg mixture.
Throw into Bundt pan. Melt butter into remaining sugar mixture and pour over top of biscuits.
Bake at 400° until done and pour out onto plate. Enjoy!

title: potato chip surprise
directions: Boil chicken, set aside to cool. Debone and cut into bite size pieces. Cook vegetables. Cook stuffing according to package. In a large bowl, mix broth, chicken, vegetables, stuffing and soup. Spray 9 x 13 pan with Pam. Crush the whole bag of chips. Put half the chips in the pan and spread evenly. Spread chicken mixture over chips, and top with remaining chips. Bake at 300° for 35 minutes. Makes 8 servings.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: orange-cottage cheese dessert
directions: Mix dry jello in Cool Whip and mix good.
Add cottage cheese and oranges, keeping some for top.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add flour.
Mix. Add apples and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into greased and floured 8 x 12-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle butterscotch morsels on top of cake.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: ham dip
directions: Mix all of the above.
Serve on crackers.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix whipped potatoes with eggs, vanilla, salt and sugar. Put in 9 x 12 greased casserole dish.

title: west texas hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; mix in remaining ingredients in order. Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook noodles; drain and rinse in cold water.
Saute onion in margarine; add Accent, celery salt and lemon pepper.
Mix well. Add soup, broth, noodles and chicken.
Mix well after each addition.
Add peas and pimento.
Mix thoroughly.

title: aunt ruth's potato salad
directions: Prep time is 1 hour plus overnight.

title: hannah's carrot cake
directions: Beat oil and sugar together well.
Add eggs and beat well. Sift flour, cinnamon, soda and baking powder together; blend with egg mixture.
Fold in carrots and nuts.
Bake at 350° until done about 30 - 35 minutes.
Insert toothpick in center to check for doneness.
If toothpick comes out clean, cake is done.

title: corn custard pudding
directions: In a small saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender, but not brown.
Drain corn.
In a bowl, combine eggs, corn, milk, sugar and 1 teaspoon salt.
Add the onion mixture.
Turn into an 8 x 1 1/2-inch round baking dish.
Place in a large baking pan. Place on oven rack.
Pour boiling water into large baking pan to a depth of 1-inch; bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until a knife inserted near center comes out clean. Makes 6 servings.

title: roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Put all ingredients in a large plastic bag and shake until all potatoes are evenly coated.
Empty potatoes into a large casserole dish. Bake 40 minutes, stirring occasionally, until potatoes are tender and brown. Sliced or grated cheese can be added the last 10 minutes and allowed to melt.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix all together to make a stiff batter.
Put in greased bowl and grease top also (I use Pam).
Cover with towel and let rise for 8 hours at room temperature.
Divide into 3 equal parts. Place in greased loaf pans.
Let stand at room temperature 8 hours.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: kahlua smith and kerns
directions: Pour Kahlua and cream over ice.
Add a splash of soda, ginger ale or cola (your favorite).
Give it a quick stir.
Enjoy.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Freeze Heath bars and use all 8.
Grease and flour 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix sugars, butter, buttermilk and egg
in mixer.
Add flour with soda and vanilla; mix.
Pour into prepared pan.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and cream cheese.
Add half flour and 3 eggs to butter mixture.
Mix well, then add remaining eggs and flour.
Mix well.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 325° about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: oatmeal-chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and brown sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Fold in oats and chocolate bits.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and salt together.
Set aside. Blend sugar, oil and eggs.
Slowly add dry mixture.
Blend until smooth and creamy.
Beat in carrots.
Pour batter into two 8-inch greased and floured cake pans.
Bake until center springs up when touched.
Cool layers.
Put filling between layers and frost top of cake.

title: hot mexican bean dip
directions: If salsa is not available, use chili powder to taste.

title: crowd pleaser casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and bell pepper.
Add following ingredients: sour cream, soups, corn, egg noodles, salt and pepper.
Turn into 2-quart Pyrex dishes; top with grated cheese.
Bake for about 30 minutes at 350°, until cheese is melted.
Can be frozen to use at a later date.

title: chicken-reuben
directions: Place in baking dish in order given and cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
May add parsley for decoration if desired.

title: simple pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients. Put in bundt or angel food cake pan in cold oven. Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour 40 minutes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix water and yeast; let stand while you mix dry ingredients together.
Add yeast mixture and oil to dry ingredients.
Grease another large bowl and put mixture in it.
Cover and let rise in warm place.
Knead down and place in rolls.
Let rise again.
Cook at 400° for about 25 minutes.

title: angel whip
directions: Drain pineapple and mix all ingredients together.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in the blender and then add enough ice cubes to fill to top line.
Blend on high speed until well beaten.
Serve in chilled glasses.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs and milk together and corn and sugar; mix well. Cut bread into 1/2-inch cubes and put in greased 9-inch pan.
Pour egg mixture over bread.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.

title: recipe for a happy home
directions: Blend together one cup of God and a cup of Jesus, mixed in half a cup friendship and a cup of thoughtfulness.
Creamed together with a pinch of powdered tenderness.
Very lightly beaten in a bowl of loyalty with a cup of faith and hope, love and charity.
Be sure to add a spoonful each of gaiety that sings and also the ability to laugh at little things.
Moisten with the sudden tears of heartfelt sympathy.
Bake in a good-natured pan and served repeatedly. Servings should last a lifetime.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind all ingredients small.
Add 3/4 cup sugar.
Let stand and refrigerate.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix all together and bake in a greased pan at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine ingredients in casserole.
Sprinkle with shredded Cheddar.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: mama's jam cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together and add the rest one at a time.
Mix very well.
Pour into greased and floured cake pans and bake at 400° or until done.
Only takes about 15 minutes per layer if you do them thin.
If not, bake as you would a normal cake. Can be done as 3 layer cake or in a 9 x 13 cake pan.

title: loobia pola(rice with green beans)
directions: Clean and wash rice.
Soak in salted water approximately 2 hours before cooking.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and sugar together and pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: majeskas(christmas candy)
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients to 240°.
Add gradually 2 1/2 cups heavy cream and boil to 230°.
Add vanilla and cook to 240°.
Add pinch of salt at any time.
Cover 80 (1 1/3 pounds) marshmallows and cool.
Wrap individually in wax paper.

title: tacos in pasta shells
directions: Cook beef until brown; drain fat.
Reduce heat to medium.
Add cream cheese, salt and chili powder.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Toss shells with butter.
Fill with beef mixture.
Arrange shells in buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour taco sauce over each shell.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Uncover.
Top with cheese and chips.
Bake 15 minutes.
Top with sour cream and onions.
Garnish lettuce, tomatoes and olives.

title: creamy tamale pie
directions: Prepare dinner as directed.
Add tomatoes, olives and sour cream.
Mix lightly.
Combine remaining ingredients, mix well. Spread into 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Drain.
Top with dinner mixture.
Continue baking 20 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in oven.
You may leave bacon uncooked and bake the beans until bacon is done.
Also can be cooked on a smoker.

title: thanksgiving dressing
directions: Bake 2 iron skillets of cornbread as per directions on back of Martha White package.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and green pepper; drain.
Bring noodles to a boil, then simmer for 15 minutes.
Mix the first 7 ingredients together.
Layer a dish with noodles, then meat mixture alternately.
Spread cheese on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pretzel jello salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Press into 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Stir and mix well in bowl.
Bake in muffin tins at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Will keep in refrigerator for days.
Can bake as you need them.

title: chocolate brownie balls
directions: In saucepan melt chocolate and shortening together.
Add sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Add egg and beat thoroughly.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to chocolate mixture. Blend in milk and nuts.
Mix well.
Chill dough several hours. Form dough into small balls and place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
While warm, dust each ball with powdered sugar.
Makes 36 balls.

title: oso buc
directions: Dust chicken lightly with flour, saute in olive oil until browned slightly on each side.
Dump onion, parsley, basil, rosemary, and garlic onto chicken.
Pour chicken broth on the spiced chicken.
May need to use more or less, depending on how much chicken you cook.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer on the lowest heat possible for 1 1/2 hours.
One half hour before serving, pour mushrooms in pan. Simmer 1/2 hour more.
Serve hot over linguine, topped with parmesan cheese.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix sugar, pineapple and cranberries. Set in refrigerator overnight.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well 1 hour before serving.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will need an 8-inch flower pot lined with foil.

title: pecan crispies
directions: On a well-greased board, sprinkle each roll with chopped pecans.
Roll out flat to form circle.
Turn over.
Sprinkle with more pecans, and roll again.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Garnish center of each with icing and pecan half.
Makes 8 servings.

title: macaroni and cheese from scratch
directions: Cook macaroni.
Place onion and 2 tablespoons margarine in small saucepan over medium heat and cook.
Stir in flour, mustard and pepper.
Cook 1 minute, slowly stir in milk, stirring until smooth.
Add about 3/4 of cheese to macaroni and mix with fork to coat macaroni.
Put in baking dish; top with rest of cheese.
In small saucepan over low heat, melt 1 tablespoon margarine.
Stir in bread crumbs.
Sprinkle crumbs on top of macaroni and bake, uncovered, 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chilies-cheese quiche
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat eggs slightly in large bowl.
Add flour, baking powder and salt and blend.
Add rest of ingredients and mix until just blended.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 400° for 14 minutes and then at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Cut in squares and serve hot.
Yields 16 or more large servings.

title: coriander potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in 1/2 or 1/4 for faster cooking.
Place in steamer basket for 15 to 20 minutes until tender.

title: green pea salad
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Add bacon and cashew nuts.

title: sour cream sugared nuts
directions: Mix sugar and sour cream

together. Let come to a full boil that you cannot stir down. Boil on medium heat for 2-3 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat, add vanilla and stir 2 or 3 times. Add nuts and stir rapidly until nuts are well coated and sugared. Pour out on cookie sheet. Separate nuts so they will not stick together. You must use pure granulated sugar for the nuts to sugar properly.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Place chicken in baking dish. Bake, covered, for 15 minutes in preheated 425° oven; drain. Combine next 4 ingredients in a saucepan; cook, stirring constantly until sauce is thickened. Pour heated sauce over chicken; top with cheese. Bake 5 minutes, uncovered. May garnish with fresh parsley.

title: layered vegetable casserole
directions: Arrange vegetables in layers in buttered casserole (except tomatoes). Combine tomatoes, tapioca, sugar and seasonings.
Heat and pour over vegetables. Cover with buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 350°, uncovered, about 1 1/2 hours. Allow to stand 3 to 5 minutes at room temperature. Serves 8.
Enjoy!

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Set oven at 375°.
Grease 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.

title: frozen banana punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in water and bring to a boil. Cool. Mash bananas by hand or in a blender.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in large roaster, except for cornstarch. Cook over medium to low heat for about an hour.
Add cornstarch, mixed with another 1/2 cup water; stir in to thicken.
Add a small bottle white Karo syrup ad if you want it hotter, you can add some crushed red pepper.
Cool and pour into jars; store in refrigerator.
Makes about a gallon.

title: fudge caramel sundae cake
directions: Bake cake mix as package directs. While still hot, punch holes in cake with handle of wooden spoon. Pour milk over cake while still hot. Heat hot fudge sauce and caramel sauce in microwave until it is warm enough to pour over cake. Let cool. Whip the whipping cream with sugar and vanilla added. Top cake. Sprinkle crushed candy bar over the whipped cream.

title: fruit cocktail icing
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients until mixture comes to a boil. Remove from heat.
Add the chopped pecans and vanilla.
Spread on cake.

title: summer sausage soup(large recipe)
directions: Put all ingredients in big pot or crock-pot. Heat thoroughly until bubbling and serve.

title: deviled hot dogs
directions: Soften onion and green pepper in butter.
Add rest of ingredients.
Lightly score hot dogs and simmer in sauce for 15 minutes.
Serve hot dogs in buns with extra sauce.

title: wade's chicken & dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until tender and meat is falling off bones. Save broth.
Combine flour, shortening and milk.
Roll into thin dough and cut into short strips.
Combine chicken broth, cream of chicken soup and butter in boiler.
Bring to a boil.
After broth has come to a boil slowly add strips of dough.
Reduce heat to simmer, cover and cook for 40 minutes. Do not stir or peek.

title: sweet milk hot cakes
directions: Beat eggs in mixing bowl.
Add milk and shortening; mix good. Measure and combine dry ingredients.
Stir into egg mixture.
Drop batter by spoonful onto dry, hot griddle or heavy skillet.
As soon as hot cakes are brown on underside, turn over.
When puffed, fill with butter or margarine while hot.
Add syrup or honey on top.

title: california potatoes
directions: Combine cheese, onions, soup, melted butter and sour cream. Mix well.
Add mixture to the hash brown potatoes.
Spread in large buttered casserole dish or 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: corn pie
directions: Beat eggs and add all other ingredients.
Pour into 1-quart buttered casserole dish and bake uncovered 45 minutes.
(Cream- style corn may be substituted, but gives a different textured pie.)

title: cheese shrimp bites
directions: Mix cheese, flour, baking powder, dill and onion.
Add eggs and mix until the cheese is evenly distributed in batter.
Stir in the shrimp.
Heat oil in electric frying pan to 375°.
Drop battered shrimp by teaspoonfuls into oil.
Cook until golden brown (about three minutes) and turn over.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot.

title: wonderful holiday drink
directions: Use any amount of zucchini; peel, cut into 1-inch pieces. Place in blender.
Set blender to liquefy.
Blend until liquefies. May be used in place of milk in any recipe.
Low in calories and nutritious.
Stores or freezes well.

title: indian pudding
directions: Mix together cornmeal and salted water.
Stir in scalded milk. Bring to a boil, stirring.
Boil 10 minutes.
Blend egg, sugar, molasses, butter, cinnamon and ginger.
Pour into buttered 1 quart casserole and bake 1/2 hour.
Stir in 1 cup of cold milk.
Bake 2 hours at 300°.
Serve warm with cream or ice cream.

title: easy casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in 1 tablespoon of the butter.
Place meat in
bottom
of
casserole.
Put
rice,
peas, onions and potatoes in layers on top of meat.

title: vegetable lasagne
directions: Cook lasagne noodles as directed; drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain and lay flat on paper towels in single layer until needed.

title: beth whittemore's zucchini bread
directions: Combine zucchini,
oil, sugar and eggs.
Mix well.
