Add sifted dry ingredients.
Fold
in pecans.	Pour into 3 greased and floured (8 1/2
x 4 1/2-inch) loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let cool 1 hour.
Remove from pans.

title: seasoned rice
directions: Melt oleo in a casserole dish; add onions, rice, bouillon and 2 to 3 cups water.
Mix.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir once in a while and add water as needed.

title: no fat or eggs easy cake
directions: Select a flavor of cake mix.
Spray tube or other pan.
Add 1 tablespoon flour to cake mix; add applesauce and water (no oil or oleo).
Add egg whites instead of whole eggs.
Cool in pan(s) on rack.
Remove when completely cool.
Frost if desired or sprinkle on powdered sugar.
Bake at 350° until springs back when touched, about 45 minutes.

title: carameled cheerios
directions: Heat and stir the brown sugar, corn syrup, butter and salt until bubbly.
Stir in the soda.
Add the Cheerios, peanuts and raisins.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan; bake at 250° for 15 minutes.
Stir, cool for 10 minutes, loosen and let stand until cool.
Great snack!

title: sweet potato balls(great with baked ham jubilee)
directions: Drain potatoes very well and mash with a fork.
Add the beaten egg and dash of salt and pepper.
Cut firm bananas in 1 to 1 1/4-inch pieces.
Make a ball of the mashed potatoes around a piece of banana.
Roll in the crushed corn flakes.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350° on a greased cookie sheet.

title: date pudding cake
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool.
Top with topping.

title: crayfish etouffee
directions: Melt
butter
in
skillet.
Add
flour
and
stir until blended.
Add
chopped
onion, bell pepper and garlic and cook until tender.
Add
Ro-Tel tomatoes and cream of mushroom soup and let
cook
about 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Then add the crayfish
tails
and
cover.
Let this cook about 15 to 20 minutes on low heat, stirring occasionally.
Add salt, pepper and cayenne pepper
to
taste,
green onion tops and parsley. Simmer a while until seasonings blend.
Serve over rice.

title: very good meat loaf
directions: Lightly mix ground meat, bread crumbs, egg, onion, salt and pepper and form loaf.
Place in shallow pan and bake at 350°.

title: hickory nut cake
directions: Cream the Sugar and Butter.
Add Milk, Yolks of eggs (well beaten).

title: coconut crunch
directions: Crumb
first
ingredients.
Put
half
of mixture on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan and brown in 350° oven until golden. Into bowl,
prepare pudding according to package instructions and put on crumbs in pan.
Put Cool Whip on top of pudding and remaining crumb mixture on top of Cool Whip.	Chill and serve. May be prepared day before.

title: pineapple squares
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening and add sugar.
Blend together.
Beat egg and add to the mixture.
Spread 3/4 of mixture in a 9 X 13 baking pan (or other pan with sides) and top with applesauce and pineapple. Spread remaining 1/4 mixture on top.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and top with pats of butter.
Bake at 350 degrees in oven until golden brown.

title: chocolate chip cookie mix
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt and sugar in very large bowl.
Mix in shortening.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Store in airtight container for 6 months in cool, dry place.

title: crispy bacon coleslaw
directions: Mix mayonnaise and sugar in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; mix and refrigerate.
Makes about 10 servings.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Pour melted margarine over flour and mix well.
Stir in nuts. Press into the bottom of a 9x13-inch baking dish.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt butter; stir all together very well.
Stir in corn muffin mix last.

title: gourmet chicken
directions: Rinse chicken.
In a nonmetallic container, combine next 5 ingredients.
Add chicken and coat well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight, up to 24 hours.

title: croissants
directions: Stir butter with a wooden spoon until smooth; spread on waxed paper into a 10 x 8-inch rectangle. Chill until needed. Scald 2/3 cup of milk; cool to 105° to 115°. Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large bowl. Stir in scalded milk, 2 cups flour and next 4 ingredients; beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until smooth. Gradually stir in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough. Turn dough out onto a floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic (8 to 10 minutes). Place in a well greased bowl, turning to grease top. Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°), free from drafts, 1 hour or until doubled in bulk. Punch dough down. Cover and refrigerate 1 hour. Punch dough down and place on a lightly floured surface; roll into a 24 x 10-inch rectangle. Place butter on half of dough. Fold other half of dough over butter to form a 12 x 10-inch rectangle; pinch edges to seal. Roll dough into an 18 x 10-inch rectangle. Fold rectangle into thirds, beginning with short side. Cover and chill 1 hour. Repeat rolling and folding process (roll into an 18 x 10-inch rectangle and fold into thirds) 2 additional times, covering and chilling dough 30 minutes between procedures. Wrap dough in aluminum foil and chill overnight. Divide dough into 4 equal portions; chill 3 portions. Roll 1 portion into a 12-inch circle on a lightly floured surface; cut into 6 wedges. Roll up each wedge tightly beginning at wide end. Seal points and place point side down on greased baking sheets, curve into crescent shapes. Repeat with remaining dough. Refrigerate 30 minutes. Combine egg yolk and 1 tablespoon milk; brush over croissants. Bake at 425° for 14 to 16 minutes or until golden brown. Yields two dozen.

title: nutty no-sugar brownies
directions: Blend together the first 5 ingredients.
Add the melted butter. Press 2/3 of the mix onto bottom of greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Spread the raspberry preserves over the mix.
Add the almonds to the remaining 1/3 of the original mix and spread over the raspberry; press lightly.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Shred all vegetables through food processor (together or individually).
Mix together in a bowl.
Add vinegar, sugar, salt, and spice.
Put into a boiling pan, and boil until transparent. Relish is now ready to be canned.
Yield: 4 pt.

title: bessie's chicken casserole
directions: Bone and chop chicken.
Add salt and pepper.
Put chicken in the bottom of the casserole dish.
Mix celery soup, chicken broth and oleo.
Pour over chicken.
Make a topping with flour, baking powder and milk.
Pour over entire mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 425°.

title: danish orange cake
directions: Cream 1 cup of sugar and shortening.
Add beaten eggs; beat until smooth.
Squeeze juice from orange; save.
Grind rind and raisins in food chopper; add both alternately to the rest of the ingredients.
Pour mixture into a lightly greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
As cake comes from the oven, pour mixture of 1 cup of sugar and orange juice over it.
Cake is best when allowed to sit overnight.

title: sugared nuts
directions: Dissolve the first 4 ingredients over medium heat.
Add peanuts.
Leave on medium heat; stir occasionally.
Cook until sugary and liquid is on 10 to 15 minutes.
Spread on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Roast at 300° for 30 minutes.
Stir 2 or 3 times.
Do not double recipe.

title: gingerbread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients, except sugar.
Cream sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Add egg and molasses to butter; blend.
Stir into dry ingredients.
Pour hot water in.
Beat until smooth.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: grandma leones' raisin and nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time and beat.
Add half of milk and one cup flour and beat.
Add rest of milk, one cup flour and beat.
Add vanilla.
Wash raisins and soak in hot water for 20 minutes.
Drain water and mix with nuts.
Add one cup flour and mix until flour is in all the nuts.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl, mix thoroughly. Allow to set 10 to 15 minutes, covered.
Roll into 1-inch balls. Place on cookie sheet; flatten with a fork.
Bake in a 350° oven for 7 to 10 minutes.
May place on wax paper when cooking to help from sticking.

title: easy chicken parmesan
directions: Pour sauce in a 13 X 9 in. baking dish. Carefully stir in 4 tbsp.

parmesan cheese. Add chicken, turn chicken breast over to coat both sides. Cover with foil. Bake at 375 degrees for 30 minutes. Uncover, top with mozzarella cheese and remaining 2 Tbsp. parmesan cheese. Continue baking 5 minutes or until chicken is cooked through and cheese is melted.
Serve over hot Pasta.

title: no egg ice cream
directions: You will need a 5-quart freezer.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt butter, mix with crumbs and press into a glass baking dish.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Put shredded lettuce in a bowl.
Layer diced green pepper, chopped celery, chopped onion and peas on top of lettuce.
Spread yogurt completely over the top of the salad.
Sprinkle with sugar, Parmesan cheese and bacon bits.
Garnish with tomato wedges. Cover tightly and chill, preferably overnight.
Toss thoroughly before serving.
Serves 10.

title: miracle whip cake
directions: Sift together the five dry ingredients.
Add the other ingredients.
Stir together and beat until smooth.
Bake in cake pan at 350° for 25 minutes.
Frost.
Very moist.

title: no bake club cracker bars
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer with whole Club crackers (Waverly Wafers).
Over low heat, bring to boil and boil for 5 minutes the crumbs, white sugar, brown sugar, milk and margarine. Pour this over crackers.
Add another layer of crackers.

title: "preach" cobbler
directions: Pour margarine into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put all dry ingredients into a big bowl and mix.
Pour in milk and whisk to a thick batter.
Pour onto the margarine.
Put pie filling on top (just scoop on top; don't stir).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Place eggs in a gallon jar.
Combine remaining ingredients and heat to simmer.
Pour over eggs.
Let stand 4 or more days.
Keeps for weeks.

title: snack goodies
directions: Just mix all ingredients together in a bowl. If you have a plastic bowl with a lid, just turn it upside down several times. Ready to serve.
If it sets overnight, it is better.

title: kara's super eggnog
directions: In a blender, add ingredients.
Fill blender with prepared eggnog (purchase at grocery store) and blend until smooth.
Serve with a sprinkling of cinnamon on top.

title: mexican pasta salad(yields 12 servings)
directions: Cook noodles.
Then add all other ingredients (except Velveeta) and mix.
Melt Velveeta, then pour over noodle mixture. Chill before serving.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour into unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° until firm.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate (10 1/2 x 1/2-inches). Cook and stir ground beef and onion in skillet until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Spread in pie plate.
Beat milk, eggs and Bisquick mix until smooth.
Pour over beef mixture.
Bake 25 minutes.
Slice tomato and arrange on top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until knife comes out clean, about 5 to 8 minutes. Cool 5 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix thoroughly butter, sugar and eggs.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt; stir in.
Roll into balls the size of small walnuts.
Roll in mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until lightly browned but soft.
These cookies puff up at first, then flatten out.
Bake at 325° in a moderate hot oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: date sticks(date sticks are a special treat.)
directions: In a large bowl, mix shortening and sugar.
Add milk and baking soda; mix well.
Sift dry ingredients into a bowl; stir well.
Fold in nuts and dates.
Pour into a shallow pan and bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
While still warm, cut into strips and roll in powdered sugar.

title: easy baked chicken
directions: Spray 2-quart baking dish.
Place chicken pieces in and sprinkle with pepper and garlic.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Combine soup and water and pour over chicken.
Continue to bake for 30 minutes.

title: amish cookies
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients together, then add 2 eggs and beat again.
Sift flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt together.
Then add to first mixture.
Roll in roll in wax paper and refrigerate. Slice and bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cook and stir onion in butter in 2-quart saucepan until onion is tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth and bubbly; remove from heat.
Stir in half and half and 1 1/2 cups of cheese.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Place potatoes in ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Pour cheese sauce on potatoes.
Bake, uncovered, until top is brown and bubbly, 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
Mix remaining cheese and the bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Set oven control to broil.
Broil 3 to 4 inches from heat until top is crusty and light brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hot rolls
directions: Prepare yeast and set aside to double.
Add all ingredients to cool milk and mix well.
Add yeast mixture and mix.
Pour out on well floured board.
Knead well (about 8 minutes).
Place in well-greased bowl and pat the top of the dough with shortening. Cover; let rise 1 hour and 15 minutes in a warm place until double.
Knead down and make into rolls.
Cover and let rise about 1 hour.
Bake in hot oven (375°) for 18 to 20 minutes.
Serve with butter while hot.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously grease and flour loaf pans. Sift dry ingredients into a small bowl and set aside.

title: pasta bake
directions: Cook onion, green pepper, hamburger meat, salt, black pepper and red pepper until meat is done; drain. Cook pasta half done; drain. In 9 x 13 pan, mix sauce, pasta, meat, pepperoni, cottage cheese and 1/4 of Mozzarella. Spread the rest on top, then bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cool 'n easy pie
directions: Stir boiling water into Jell-O until dissolved.
Add enough ice to water to make 1 1/4 cups.
Stir into Jell-O until slightly thickened.
Stir in topping until smooth.
Refrigerate about 10 minutes.
Spoon into crust.
Refrigerate until firm, about 4 hours.
Garnish with topping.

title: seven-up pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter until fluffy. Add eggs one at a time, blending well after each addition. Add flour and baking powder. Beat in lemon extract and seven-up. Pour batter into a greased and floured bundt pan. Bake at 325° for 1 to 1/4 hours. Take cake out of pan and wrap tightly in plastic wrap, allowing cake to sweat.

title: equal strawberry cream pie
directions: BEAT cream cheese, vanilla and 1 3/4 teaspoons Equal| for Recipes in a small bowl until fluffy; spread evenly in bottom of crust.

title: onion-roasted potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Wash potatoes; cut into large wedges.
Put all ingredients in large plastic bag; close bag and shake until potatoes are well coated.
Empty into baking dish.
Discard bag and bake for about 40 minutes, or until potatoes are tender. Serves 6.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add egg yolks and bananas and cream until smooth.
Alternate, adding flour, buttermilk and soda.
Then add vanilla and beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: cinnamon oat pancake mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; stir well.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Yields about 8 cups of mix or 4 batches of pancakes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, corn syrup, water and salt to 250°.
Add 1 pound peanuts; cook to 280°, then add 1/4 cup butter and vanilla.
Cook to 285° to 290°.
Remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon baking soda. Pour onto 3 buttered baking sheets.
Pull out thin as mixture cools.
When completely cooled, break into pieces and store in airtight containers.

title: calvin's squash
directions: Slice squash about 1/8-inch thick.
Cut up onions including tops.
Slice sausage about 1/2-inch thick.
Slice pepper in small strips.
Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Cover the bottom of a skillet or wok with enough Mazola corn oil to sufficiently cook the ingredients.
Heat oil to the desired temperature, pour in the ingredients and cook on medium to high heat, stirring occasionally.
Serves 4.
For added zest, may top off with a little Prego sauce.

title: persian rice
directions: 1. Put the rice in a bowl and run the water over it for 3 minutes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook roast and bones in pressure cooker at 10 pounds of pressure for 1 1/2 hours.
Cut up cabbage into bite size pieces. Put in different pot with some water and carrots, onion and tomatoes.
Boil for 1 hour.
Add frozen vegetables.
Cook 15 minutes.
After it starts to boil, add drained canned vegetables. Add broth and cut up meat to pot; cook for 1 hour.
Add salt and pepper.

title: candied crisp pickles
directions: Wash and slice cucumbers.
Cover with lime water (1 cup lime to 1 gallon water).
Let stand overnight.
Wash.
Put in enamel container.
Cover with vinegar and sugar (equal amounts).
Add pickling spices to suit your taste.
Cook for 3 hours, just barely boiling.
Put in sterile jars and seal.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a bowl, stir together flour and baking soda.
In a large mixing bowl, beat butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Gradually add flour mixture; beat well.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes. Cool slightly.
Place on wire rack until cooled completely.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: tea cake
directions: Combine buttermilk and water.
Set aside.
Combine flour and soda.
Set aside.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla. Add butter, milk and flour alternately.
Drop on cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: apple dessert
directions: Peel apples and cut in quarters. Roll each biscuit out thin and cut in half. (You will have 20 pieces of apple and 20 pieces of dough.) Roll each piece of apple up in dough. Place in baking dish or pan. Heat sugar, water and margarine until boiling. Pour over apples and sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 350° about 35 minutes or until brown.

title: rustler hot chili
directions: Cook ground beef, onions, green pepper, celery and garlic in large pan until meat is browned.
Do not drain.
Stir in undrained tomatoes and remaining ingredients except kidney beans.
Simmer uncovered for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Stir in beans and cook another 30 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in skins until just tender.
Cool and peel. Grate cooked potatoes into mixing bowl.
Add melted margarine, sour cream, chopped onions and grated cheese; mix well.
Put into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chicken in orange and wine(serves 4)
directions: Sprinkle salt and pepper on chicken and place in shallow baking pan.
Make sauce by mixing sugar and flour; add egg, orange juice and wine and cook over low heat until slightly thickened. Pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° about 1 hour or until done.

title: gay's spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook, covered, for 30 minutes; then simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes. Serve over pasta.
Serves 4.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 10-12 minutes.

title: sesame wheat crisps
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; stir well. Cut in butter with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal. Sprinkle water evenly over surface; stir with fork until all dry ingredients are moistened. Shape into a ball. Roll dough to 1/8 inch thickness on a lightly floured surface. Cut dough into 3X 1 1/2 inch rectangles, and place on ungreased baking sheets. Bake 375 degrees for 12 to 14
minutes or until golden brown.

title: candy crispix mix
directions: Bring sugar, salt, margarine and corn syrup to a boil. Remove from heat and immediately stir in baking soda. Pour cereal into a brown paper bag.

title: posh squash
directions: Cook squash in boiling salt water to cover for 10 to 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain and cool slightly.
Combine mayo, cheese, onion, eggs, salt and pepper.
Then stir in squash gently. Put mixture into a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Combine bread crumbs and butter and spoon over squash.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken riviera
directions: Place 8 halves of chicken breast between Saran Wrap and pound down to 1/2 the thickness.
Spread each piece with softened cream cheese, mixed with chives. Roll each piece jelly roll style and then wrap with one piece of bacon.
Brown each piece in saute pan until bacon looks nearly done.
Transfer chicken to large Pyrex dish.
Pour bottle of dressing evenly over all pieces.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serve with egg noodles or rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: play dough
directions: Cook over medium heat until it sticks together (about 10 minutes).
Recipe can be doubled.

title: 3 day yeast rolls
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Set aside.
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm (not hot) water.
Set aside.
Melt margarine in 1 cup boiling water and add sugar and 1 cup cold water and eggs.
Mix well.
Stir in yeast and margarine mixtures.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
This dough may be kept for 3 days in the refrigerator.
Pinch off small portions and place in baking dish. Bake at 425° until lightly brown.
Brush with butter.

title: lemon cookies(diabetic)
directions: Cream shortening in a small mixer bowl on high speed.
Add Sucaryl, egg, water, lemon juice, peel and vanilla.
Beat until blended well.
Mix in coconut.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to creamed mixture, mixing thoroughly.
Form dough into a roll 2 inches in diameter; wrap in wax paper and chill until firm.
Cut into thin slices and bake on ungreased cookie sheet in oven at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: mississippi sin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice off top of bread and hollow out inside, reserving chunks of bread.
Mix all filling ingredients together.
Pour on bread and wrap in foil.
Place on cookie sheet and bake 1 hour.
Use chunks of bread for dipping or serve with crackers or chips.

title: peanut patties
directions: Put sugar, water and Karo in large pan. Let boil over medium-high heat until it comes to a full rolling boil. Add peanuts and food color. Boil to hard ball stage. Remove from heat; add salt and margarine. Beat 5 to 7 minutes until it begins to thicken. Pour into buttered or sprayed (using Pam) small aluminum tins or pour onto cookie sheet and break into pieces when cooled.

title: wild rice baron
directions: Gently cook rice, water and 2 teaspoons salt (covered) for 45 minutes.
Drain.
Brown beef.
Rinse mushrooms; cut tips off stems. Slice and saute with onion and celery in butter 5 to 10 minutes. Combine soy sauce, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Add cooked rice, beef, onion, mushrooms and celery mixture and almonds.
Toss lightly.
Place in 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Add water, if needed.
Season to taste.
Stir several times and garnish with few almonds.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: mexican chef salad
directions: Brown hamburger, then add kidney beans and dressing until all is warm.
Chop lettuce, onion, and tomato.
Crush Doritos into small pieces.
In a large bowl, mix lettuce, onion, tomato, cheese and Doritos.
Add the warm mixture before serving, and stir all together.

title: chili beef stew
directions: Salt and pepper beef cubes; roll in flour and shake off excess.
Brown beef, then brown onion in same pan.
Add garlic, salt, chili peppers, tomatoes and their liquid and green chilies. Simmer until beef is tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Mix in beans and cook 20 minutes more until slightly thickened.
Top with cheese.

title: string beans and glazed tomatoes
directions: Combine tomatoes, sugar and vinegar in a cast-iron skillet. Bring to a boil.
Lower heat; simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Mix with hot cooked string beans.
This dish is very good with roast beef and mashed potatoes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Combine all ingredients except paprika.
Cover and chill. Sprinkle with paprika before serving with crackers.
Yields 2 cups.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix dry ingredients, vanilla and milk.
Stir well to make creamy.
Bring to boil over medium.
Remove; add butter and serve hot.

title: date pudding
directions: Chop nuts and dates fine, then mix and pour above ingredients in bottom of a large baking dish.
Mix brown sugar, butter, boiling water and white sugar and pour over batter.
Bake in slow oven for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: darlene's creamed corn
directions: Melt cream cheese in saucepan.
Add chilies and corn.
Mix and heat.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower in 3/4 inch squares. Chop celery in 1/8 inch cuts. Slice tomato into strips, dice bell pepper. Add together with mayonnaise in a serving bowl. Must be fresh. Garnish with the cheddar cheese and crushed olives. Serves 8 to 10.

title: minted peas and carrots
directions: Slice carrots 1/2-inch thick on diagonal.
In 1-inch of boiling water in medium saucepan, cook carrots with salt, covered, 10 to 15 minutes, or until fork-tender.
Also, cook peas as package directs.

title: double chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients, including flavor packet; stir until well mixed.
Drop from a teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 11 to 13 minutes.
When cookies have just lost their gloss, yet still feel soft to a light touch, remove from oven (do not overbake).
Let cool 2 to 3 minutes, then remove from cookie sheets to cooling racks.
Store in airtight container.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and put in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and put on top of first 3.
Refrigerate.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Combine ingredients.
Drop large spoonfuls on cookie sheet to make thick cookies.
Bake at 350° for 14 minutes.

title: banana bran muffins
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients and raisins.
Moisten with Egg Beaters, molasses or honey, milk and butter or margarine. Stir only enough to blend.
Bake in Teflon or well-greased muffin tins at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Dice or cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Roll each piece in egg, then flour.
Fry in vegetable oil until pieces are golden brown.
Lay chicken on napkin to soak up extra grease.
Cut onion, peppers and pickles into small pieces.
Put chicken in wok with sweet and sour sauce.
Add juice from pineapple chunks.
Let cook and simmer about 10 minutes.
Add pepperoni, onions and pickles to chicken.
Cook 10 minutes.
Then add pineapple and cherries, cook 5 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Coat wings thoroughly and marinate 2 hours in refrigerator.
Bake in same pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Baste occasionally.
Serve hot or cold.

title: baked potato skins
directions: Bake potatoes at 400° for 1 hour or until tender.
Cool slightly; cut in half lengthwise and scoop out pulp, leaving 1/4-inch of pulp still attached to skin.
(The potato pulp you remove can be refrigerated for use later.) Cut skins into strips or halves; brush skin sides with melted butter and place on a baking sheet.
Sprinkle pulp sides with salt and paprika; cover with the green onions, bacon, ham or shrimp and chopped peppers. Top with cheese.
Bake at 450° until cheese is melted and skins are crisp, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Garnish each skin with a dollop of sour cream.
Serve immediately.

title: hamburger with guacamole topping
directions: Mix the avocados with remaining ingredients except hamburger patties and buns.
Chill.
Grill the hamburger patties over hot coals to desired doneness.
Place on buns and top with avocado mixture.

title: basic bread pudding
directions: Scald milk and butter in top of double boiler over boiling water.
Cut bread into 1/2-inch cubes.
Add to milk.
Cover and remove from heat.
Beat eggs until frothy; add sugar and salt. Stir hot milk and bread into egg mixture.
Add nutmeg and vanilla, mixing well.
Pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole or baking dish, placed in pan of hot water.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° about 1 hour or until a knife inserted comes out clean.
Makes 6 servings.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and nutmeg together. Add oleo and beaten eggs, saving 1 egg white and fold in last and other ingredients. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake until a knife comes out clean when inserted in the middle of the pie.
Bake at 325°.

title: lemon pineapple pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and pineapple.
Cook until thickened. Add jello powder. Stir until jello is dissolved.
Cool, then add whipped Carnation milk. Pour into 3 graham cracker crusts. Chill.

title: onion salad
directions: Make as much as you want; adjust dressing to amount.
Chop Spanish onion fine.
Add equal amounts of crushed Ritz crackers. To onions, add lemon pepper seasoning and mayonnaise to desired taste.
Add Ritz crackers to onion when ready to serve.
(If added too soon will be soggy.)

title: blueberry banana pie
directions: Cut up bananas in pie shell.
Then mix cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip together.
Put on top of bananas.
Open can of fruit filling and put on top.

title: country baked beans
directions: Cook bacon and crumble into a large bowl.
Add rest of ingredients, stirring until well blended.
Pour into an ungreased 9x13-inch baking dish.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook and drain carrots.
In small saucepan mix sugar, nutmeg, orange juice and cornstarch.
Cook until it starts to thicken, stir constantly.
Pour over cooked carrots, serve hot.

title: sweet and sour green beans
directions: Cook bacon with onion until crisp.
Drain off all but 1/4 cup drippings.
Beat together eggs, vinegar, water, salt and sugar. Add to cooled drippings in skillet.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Pour over beans in dish; crumble bacon over beans.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Add powdered sugar until right thickness, about 2 to 2 1/2 cups.
Beat.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash the tomatoes and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Soak for 1 hour in cold, salted water.
Add the sugar, pepper and salt to the beaten egg.
Dip each tomato slice into the egg mixture, then into the bread crumbs.
Fry on both sides in hot oil until brown.

title: caramel candy
directions: Put 1/2 cup sugar into a cast-iron skillet.
Cook at medium heat until sugar is caramelized.
Pour in milk and let cook until caramel is dissolved.
Add 2 cups of sugar and salt.
Reduce heat slightly and cook, stirring as little as possible, until candy thermometer reads 250° or until the candy reaches soft ball stage. Remove from heat.
Add butter and let cool to 120° on thermometer.
Do not stir at all during this stage or it will be grainy.
When cool, beat until candy loses its glossy appearance. Add nuts, if desired, and pour onto greased surface.

title: key west coconut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Beat in eggs and coconut extract, then sour cream. Add coconut.
Stir together flour, baking soda and baking powder. Add to batter, beating it in. Divide into 2 lightly greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until bread tests done.

title: todd's hamburger and potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Season hamburger meat with pepper while browning.
Drain off grease.
In separate saucepan combine both soups and water over low heat.
Line potato slices in a 10 x 13-inch buttered baking dish.
Lightly salt and pepper.
Lay ground beef on top of potatoes.
Pour soup mixture over top.
Cover dish with aluminum foil, piercing a small hole in the center.
Bake covered for 25 minutes.
Remove foil and top with potato chips. Bake for 20 minutes more.

title: crab-cheese pie
directions: Drain and slice crab meat.
Combine with cheese, beaten eggs, milk and onions.
Line a 9-inch pie plate with 5 triangles of dough.
Press together to form crust.
Spoon in crab mixture.
Top with remaining triangles.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper with butter.
Combine sausage, onion and pepper.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 50 minutes.
Uncover; bake for 10 minutes.

title: catfish relish
directions: Boil sugar, vinegar, mustard seed, celery seed and chopped jalapeno peppers.
(This is very hot.
You may want to cut down on peppers.)
Put vegetables in boiling solution until tomatoes change color.
Do not boil further.
Put in jars and process in water bath for 10 minutes.

title: summer squash skillet
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Stir in sugar, flour, salt and pepper.
Add squash and tomatoes.
Cook over low heat just until vegetables are tender.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Form in walnut size balls and roll in sugar.
Place on a cookie sheet (which has been greased), 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Arrange noodles in bottom of lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Layer remaining ingredients on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Serves 10.

title: chili sauce - uncooked
directions: Combine everything except vinegar and sugar.
Stir well and let stand for 4 hours.
Drain in a cloth bag overnight.
In the morning, bring to a boil the vinegar and sugar.
Add the vegetables and can in sterilized hot jars. Do not boil.

title: company's comin' cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt. Add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Stir in oatmeal and nuts. Shape dough in a roll 2 inches in diameter.
Wrap in aluminum foil.
Place in freezer for 2 hours.
Cut dough in 1/4-inch slices and place on ungreased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: chocolate candy
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients.
When done, add the vanilla and pecans.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Bake cookie dough as directed on package.
Let cookie dough cool, then spread softened cream cheese on dough.
Cut fruit in pieces and place on top of cream cheese.
Cut and serve.

title: easy chip dip
directions: Heat crock-pot on high.
Cut cheese into chunks and put into crock-pot.
Add ground beef, onions and sauce.
Heat all in crock-pot until cheese is melted and is hot.

title: mixed nut bars
directions: Heat until melted.
Pour over nuts. Bake at 350°. (Don't let it bubble.)

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Cream butter very well.
Gradually add 1/2 cup confectioners sugar and cream until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.

title: spider cookies
directions: Melt morsels over medium heat.
Remove from heat and stir in the noodles and nuts.
Drop onto wax paper and refrigerate until they set.
Easy and fun for kids!

title: blonde brownies
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter. Stir in brown sugar.
Cool 10 minutes, then add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir in flour, baking powder, salt, nuts and chocolate chips until well blended. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until center springs back when lightly touched.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Place chicken breasts between 2 sheets of waxed paper and pound until thin (1/4 inch).
Combine flour, salt, pepper and paprika in plastic bag; add chicken breasts and coat well.
Shake off excess. Heat butter and olive oil in large skillet until bubbling.
Saute chicken breasts, a few at a time, 2 to 3 minutes on each side; do not overcook.
Drain on paper towels and keep warm.

title: russian tea mix(microwave)
directions: Remove only 1/2 of husk from corn.
Trim small end.
Place in microwave oven for 3 minutes on High.
Remove husk.
Will be very juicy and tender.
Add butter if desired.

title: dried apple stack cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together molasses, sugar, sweet milk, eggs and melted shortening.
Add enough self-rising flour to make a stiff dough.
Pour onto floured board and knead.
Put a small piece of dough in bottom of round cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5 to 7 layers.

title: mother's creamed chicken
directions: Lightly brown green peppers and mushrooms in butter.
Add flour and blend.
Add milk and seasonings.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add chicken, egg yolk and pimento, cooking 10 minutes.
Serve on biscuits or hot buttered toast.
Serves 6.

title: peach salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze. Can be used as a salad or dessert.

title: chocolate sour cream cake
directions: Combine all ingredients well, pour into 9 x 13 pan, and bake at 350° 30-40 minutes.
Cool cake and frost.

title: applesauce date nut loaf
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add beaten egg.
Stir in hot applesauce to which soda has been added and dissolved.
Add dates, nuts and dry ingredients plus vanilla.
Put into loaf pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Sprinkle top with sugar.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour in preheated 325° oven or until lightly browned and toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: dried apple cake
directions: Mix apples and soda until smooth.
Add sugar and eggs, blending well.
Soften butter and add to mixture.
Fold in flour and spices. Mix well.
Grease and flour pans.
Pour in mix and cook at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Mix into pot of beans with other ingredients.
Simmer for about 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until brownness is barely visible.
